episodes.title: She's My Sister
episodes.description: Chloe Taylor has the biggest night of her career, and not a day later her husband winds up dead. Now cops are asking a lot of questions she doesn't want to answer, and even worse, they called her sister.

episodes.title: Lotta Sky
episodes.description: Chloe and her sister Nicky are back together but things are bumpy, and not just because Detective Guidry seems too interested in Ethan.

episodes.title: Incoming Widow
episodes.description: A day in court doesn't go as planned, and Chloe goes somewhere surprising for emotional support.

episodes.title: Gazpacho
episodes.description: Catherine throws a memorial for Adam that no one wants to go to. Chloe and Nicky have very different memories of just about everything.

episodes.title: Just Ask
episodes.description: Nicky tries to shake off a bad night. Chloe tries to figure out what Adam was up to when he died. And the trial is starting.

episodes.title: Steadying Hand
episodes.description: The sisters take the stand, but what truth will they tell? Guidry's temper flares.

episodes.title: Back from Red
episodes.description: Adam's darkest secret finally comes out, and it changes everything for Chloe and Nicky. Guidry and Bowen go back to basics.

episodes.title: They're in Their World
episodes.description: Chloe enacts a plan, Guidry takes a trip, Nicky explains a few key details, and the sisters try to figure out if being in each other's lives is even possible.

episodes.title: When Dimple Met Rishi
episodes.description: Hopeless romantic Rishi hopes to woo Dimple at a summer course after seeing her photo on a matrimonial website — but marriage is far from her mind.

episodes.title: Hot Summer, Cold Vibes
episodes.description: Dimple learns why she was really allowed to come to Jaipur. Bonding with Dimple during a class assignment, Rishi hopes they'll be paired for a project.

episodes.title: Message Deleted
episodes.description: After a less-than-fun dinner with Celina’s friends, Dimple’s walk home with Rishi proves enlightening. Celina and Namrata both hide secrets.

episodes.title: Making Moves
episodes.description: Namrata confides in Rishi about her crush. Emotions run high when a wild house party at Zeenat’s brings surprises and misunderstandings.

episodes.title: It's Not a Date
episodes.description: Rishi and Dimple go on a platonic date, but confessions and secrets raise the stakes. As Dimple’s app idea is approved, Anmol poses a challenge.

episodes.title: Games We Play
episodes.description: Dimple devotes herself to her app before a dramatic gaming showdown with Anmol. Multiple betrayals risk relationships, including Dimple and Rishi’s.

episodes.title: When Dimple Met Rishi.. Again
episodes.description: Dimple and Harsh seek credit for their app. Namrata faces the aftermath of her secret spreading, while Rishi tries to salvage their friendship.

episodes.title: Girl in the Middle
episodes.description: With Namrata and Rishi back on campus, Celina’s anxieties run high, while Dimple and Harsh’s closeness sparks jealousy.

episodes.title: 100 Reasons to Hate You
episodes.description: Dimple’s search for the data leak’s source proves challenging. Zeenat offers Sid a home-cooked meal and Anmol makes a discovery that tests his trust.

episodes.title: Heartech
episodes.description: Sparks fly at the tech fest in Ajmer as new connections are forged and a dance competition turns heated.

episodes.title: Altair and Vega
episodes.description: Love and lust are in the air as a tech-free day on campus leads to new revelations. In therapy, Anmol grapples with the reason behind his anger.

episodes.title: You’re The One
episodes.description: As the wedding nears, family drama leaves Rishi anxious. Harsh weighs a major decision about his future, while Celina overcomes her fears.

episodes.title: It’s Not a Non-Date
episodes.description: Namrata contemplates her future as tensions run high at home. Serious consequences catch up with Celina and Anmol finds he isn’t alone.

episodes.title: I Love You More
episodes.description: A romantic date gets in the way of Dimple’s dream. While the farewell party brings remorse and resolution, Namrata takes a bold step.

episodes.title: When Dimple Didn't Meet Rishi
episodes.description: While navigating a long-distance relationship, Rishi’s career soars while Dimple’s life turns stagnant. Sid dreams big with a new educational institute.

episodes.title: For Better or For Verse
episodes.description: On Valentine’s Day, Rishi hosts a matchmaking event to test a new app. Tension marks Celina and Rith’s first meeting. Dimple and Rishi take a big step.

episodes.title: Chill vs Dil
episodes.description: Dimple’s frustration grows as Rishi splits his attention between the metaverse and Nandini. Zeenat makes a life-changing decision.

episodes.title: It Gets Better, Hon
episodes.description: Celina plans a dazzling pride event for the students. Vinny dives into student advocacy. Auditions begin for a new stage production.

episodes.title: Where Does The Love Go?
episodes.description: A visit to Hyderabad’s historic monuments sparks romance for the students. A surprise wedding brings the gang together. Dimple receives devastating news.

episodes.title: Growing Pains
episodes.description: Dimple struggles to focus but later finds inspiration. Anmol and Vinny spar over his past. Rith uses artificial intelligence to aid his transition.

episodes.title: Hello, Future Wife!
episodes.description: An impromptu engagement party sparks happiness and confusion. Celina learns of a major hack, while a remorseful Anmol tries to make amends.

episodes.title: Beginning, Middle and...
episodes.description: At Technovate in Mumbai, the launch of Betterverse hits a glitch. The couples face emotional decisions over their futures — together and apart.

episodes.title: three women
episodes.description: Gia, a grieving writer, sets out to write a book about female desire in America. She introduces us to three subjects: Lina, a homemaker in suburban Indiana; Sloane, a glamorous entrepreneur in the Northeast; and Maggie, a waitress in North Dakota.

episodes.title: lina
episodes.description: Lina kicks off her flight from a stagnant marriage and a body of pain. She joins a women's group at Doctor Henry's, attempts to reconnect with the love of her life—her high school boyfriend, Aidan—and begins a friendship with Gia that will change both their lives forever.

episodes.title: sloane
episodes.description: A difficult visit from her mother, Dyan, propels Sloane further towards Will. Richard, unusually resistant to giving Sloane what she wants, attempts to appease her desire in a different ill-fated way.

episodes.title: maggie
episodes.description: Maggie summons the courage to tell her parents and the police about the relationship with her teacher, Aaron Knodel, that transpired back in high school, and has been affecting her life ever since.

episodes.title: gia
episodes.description: Jumping back in time, Gia is in New York burning through her advance and missing deadlines as she struggles to write her book about sex in America. Embarking on an unexpected love story of her own with Jack, Gia processes the pain of her own losses, moves to Indiana and bonds with Lina. Their relationship solidifies the new focus of Gia’s book—female desire.

episodes.title: climax
episodes.description: Lina, Sloane and Maggie each finally connect with their hearts' desire, ecstatically unaware of the fallout that awaits them.

episodes.title: two women
episodes.description: In Indiana, Gia and Lina's bond is threatened by the sudden arrival of Jack and the telling of a long-held truth.

episodes.title: twilight
episodes.description: When Aaron Knodel is put on trial, Maggie is forced to accept a huge loss.

episodes.title: sex on drugs
episodes.description: Sloane hatches a secret plan to get everything she wants, culminating in an evening filled with intimacy and revealed secrets.

episodes.title: her name
episodes.description: Lina, Sloane, Maggie, and Gia all have to make monumental decisions about their future.

episodes.title: Episode 9
episodes.description: Episode 9 of Three Women

episodes.title: Hello It's Me
episodes.description: After discussing how to handle change, Carrie is challenged to be “sexually” open on Che’s podcast, Miranda has a disastrous first day of school, and Charlotte tries to impress a fellow mom. And then – another big change no one saw coming.

episodes.title: Little Black Dress
episodes.description: Miranda and Charlotte come to Carrie’s aid, proving what good friends are for. Anthony and Stanford vow to let go of petty arguments.

episodes.title: When in Rome…
episodes.description: Carrie learns of a surprising development involving Big’s ex. Charlotte worries about how to handle a daughter’s revelation. Miranda ponders the state of her marriage.

episodes.title: Some of My Best Friends
episodes.description: Looking to move forward, Carrie meets with self-made real estate broker Seema Patel. Meanwhile, Charlotte plans a high-stakes dinner party for LTW as Miranda and Nya connect over the frank realities of motherhood.

episodes.title: Tragically Hip
episodes.description: As Carrie recuperates from hip surgery, Charlotte learns surprising news about her daughter, and Che’s words help Miranda face some truths about her life.

episodes.title: Diwali
episodes.description: Carrie's giant leap for her future self helps her embrace the past, while Miranda makes a confession to a shocked Charlotte.

episodes.title: Sex and the Widow
episodes.description: Carrie’s publisher tasks her with injecting some hope into her new book, Miranda attempts to rekindle a spark with Steve, and Charlotte bristles when Harry imposes on her sacred space… tennis.

episodes.title: Bewitched, Bothered and Bewildered
episodes.description: After coming clean to Che, Miranda is spurred toward making a life-altering decision. Carrie attempts to learn more about her mysterious 20-something neighbor. Charlotte’s efforts to be more open with her kids about sex get derailed.

episodes.title: No Strings Attached
episodes.description: Carrie questions whether she’s ready to take another step toward letting go. Charlotte boasts that she’s finally finished menopause. Miranda’s spontaneity backfires.

episodes.title: Seeing the Light
episodes.description: Charlotte plans the ultimate rite of passage for Rock. Che throws Miranda for a loop. Carrie finds closure.

episodes.title: Met Cute
episodes.description: While Carrie questions whether she’s ready for more than a casual fling, Miranda starts to worry her relationship with Che is only about sex.

episodes.title: The Real Deal
episodes.description: While Carrie struggles with a podcast ad script, Charlotte tries to retrieve Lily’s designer clothes, and chaos ensues when Miranda loses her phone.

episodes.title: Chapter Three
episodes.description: Carrie conjures a spur of the moment excuse to get out of an emotional audiobook taping. Charlotte and Lisa try to get their hands on a “MILF” list.

episodes.title: ALIVE!
episodes.description: Carrie gets an offer to write a column for seniors. Charlotte and Lisa celebrate the start of summer camp. Miranda navigates life back in NYC.

episodes.title: Trick or Treat
episodes.description: Carrie has a run-in with a tech entrepreneur. Miranda and Che navigate conflicting schedules. Charlotte veers into stage mom territory.

episodes.title: Bomb Cyclone
episodes.description: Carrie asks Che to be her moral support at a conference for widows. Miranda broaches an uncomfortable conversation with Steve.

episodes.title: February 14th
episodes.description: Carrie ponders the significance of her upcoming dinner with Aidan. A newly single Miranda explores the possibilities of dating again.

episodes.title: A Hundred Years Ago
episodes.description: Carrie questions her past choices as she prepares to meet Aidan's sons. Meanwhile, Charlotte gets ready to go back to work full time.

episodes.title: There Goes the Neighborhood
episodes.description: Carrie makes a big decision for her and Aidan's future. Lisa attempts to keep up with the demands of her career and Herbert's political campaign.

episodes.title: The Last Supper: Appetizer (1)
episodes.description: Carrie preps for a dinner party farewell to her apartment – and both its good and bad memories. Miranda takes steps to make amends with her exes.

episodes.title: The Last Supper: Entrée (2)
episodes.description: As Carrie puts the finishing touches on her dinner party, Miranda reconnects with Steve, and Seema worries that she's been too vulnerable with Ravi.

episodes.title: Outlook Good
episodes.description: As Carrie navigates long-distance with Aidan, Miranda considers ghosting a hookup, and Charlotte tries to redeem Mr. Burton.

episodes.title: The Rat Race
episodes.description: Carrie tries to interpret Aidan's texting style. Seema reluctantly agrees to see a matchmaker. Charlotte and LTW stalk a college prep consultant.

episodes.title: Carrie Golightly
episodes.description: While Seema tags along on Carrie's trip to Virginia, Charlotte is caught between work and mom duties, and Miranda gets advice from her crush.

episodes.title: Apples to Apples
episodes.description: Aidan suggests Carrie spend some quality time with his sons after she extends her trip. Later, Miranda takes Joy's advice during an interview.

episodes.title: Under the Table
episodes.description: While Carrie and Miranda deal with noisy neighbor situations, Charlotte and LTW take their families on a glamping trip to Governors Island.

episodes.title: Silent Mode
episodes.description: As Miranda takes a tentative next step with Joy, Carrie connects with Duncan on their writing projects, and LTW butts heads with Lucille.

episodes.title: They Wanna Have Fun
episodes.description: Carrie throws Charlotte a party to boost her spirits. Anthony has an awkward first meeting with Giuseppe's mom. Seema and Adam's flirtation blossoms.

episodes.title: Happily Ever After
episodes.description: Carrie attempts to work on notes with Duncan while Aidan is in town for a visit. LTW tries to tamp down a growing attraction.

episodes.title: Present Tense
episodes.description: While Carrie is forced to confront lingering trust issues in her relationship, Miranda finally opens up to Joy. Later, Seema tries something new.

episodes.title: Better Than Sex
episodes.description: Carrie has a burst of creative energy. Brady drops a bombshell on Miranda and Steve.

episodes.title: Forget About the Boy
episodes.description: Carrie contemplates the ending of her book … and her own story. Charlotte navigates complicated feelings around Rock's school musical.

episodes.title: Party of One
episodes.description: As Carrie decides to work on accepting her next phase, Miranda hosts Thanksgiving for the first time in her new apartment.

episodes.title: Episode 1
episodes.description: When her father is murdered, Ana moves to Galicia to lead her own investigation into his past. Soon she meets Daniel, the heir to a drug empire.

episodes.title: Episode 2
episodes.description: The Padíns want to keep young Marco out of their business. After making a deal with Daniel, Ana begins digging into his numerous shady enterprises.

episodes.title: Episode 3
episodes.description: Ana goes on a fancy business trip with Daniel and has a rocky encounter with José Padín. The relationship between Marco and María worries the clan.

episodes.title: Episode 4
episodes.description: Samuel's release heightens tensions and intensifies police investigations. Ana assists the clan's next operation while keeping her true plan in mind.

episodes.title: Episode 5
episodes.description: José Padín is accidentally thrust back into the spotlight. A shooting disrupts the town and forces Ana to undertake a mission on Daniel's behalf.

episodes.title: Episode 6
episodes.description: While Daniel involves Ana in his future plans, Nazario pokes around the lawyer's past. The Padíns discover that there's a snitch among them.

episodes.title: Episode 7
episodes.description: It's all set for the big operation. As secrets continue to unfold, Ana is thrown into turmoil in an attempt to warn Daniel before it's too late.

episodes.title: Intro
episodes.description: Ankit Pandey enters hostel to ﬁnd that the room allotted to him is already occupied by Chirag and Jaat. He has to ﬁnd himself a room, and a bed that too in the ragging period.

episodes.title: Proving Identity
episodes.description: Ankit grapples with identity crisis as he ﬁnds himself pretty ordinary amongst his batch-mates.

episodes.title: F.O.S.L.A
episodes.description: Ankit is smitten by Akanksha, the most prized catch of not only his batch but entire college. Will a coy Ankit succeed?

episodes.title: GPL
episodes.description: Ankit tries to hide his birthday from his wing-mates to avoid the dreaded GPL. Will he succeed?

episodes.title: End Sem
episodes.description: With Chirag suddenly gone unavailable at the last moment, Ankit and Jhantoo have to survive the end-sems.

episodes.title: D.I.S.C.O
episodes.description: The gang is a year older and realises their authoritative role as seniors not realising that “breaking ice” with the juniors could land them into trouble.

episodes.title: Love-Square
episodes.description: We have all been through love triangles. But when Jaat and Jhantoo end up falling for the same girl a love square is formed. With Ankit and Chirag as catalysts, both pursue Unnati, the heartthrob of the hostel.

episodes.title: Gandagi
episodes.description: Ankit does everything in his power to woo Akanksha by showing her how clean he is in a typical dirty boys hostel. Akanksha however doesn’t seem impressed leaving Ankit heartbroken.

episodes.title: Ghar Wapsi
episodes.description: The gang is all prepared to leave for their homes during the break except for Jhantoo who must stay back. Through the course of the days the boys discover if home is the place to stay or hostel, the place to be.

episodes.title: Episode 5
episodes.description: Episode 5 of Hostel Daze

episodes.title: Failed Experiments
episodes.description: In order to make their lives exciting in third year, the group put themselves through a series of experiments.

episodes.title: Wing Chor
episodes.description: Chirag turns detective to find a notorious thief in the hostel, meanwhile someone spills Akanksha’s secrets to her mother.

episodes.title: Lights Camera Cut
episodes.description: The team led by Chirag, gears up to make a short film in order to win the inter-hostel competition.

episodes.title: Dosti Ka Udhar
episodes.description: The group gets divided as a dispute ensues between two friends messing up their friendship.

episodes.title: G.S.H.A
episodes.description: Jhantoo contests election against a worthy opponent for the post of General Secretary of Hostel Affairs.

episodes.title: Dear Seniors
episodes.description: As the year ends, the group prepares to bid a final goodbye to their seniors, also introspecting their own relationships.

episodes.title: Single Room
episodes.description: As the seniors are allotted single rooms in the hostel, the gang refuses to get serious about their final year until reality hits them in the form of an unexpected event.

episodes.title: Curriculum Vitae
episodes.description: Ankit struggles to write his CV while Chirag and Nabomita have a difficult time keeping their relationship a secret.

episodes.title: Compromise
episodes.description: Jhantu tries to focus on his placements preparation but ends up getting involved in a hostel fight

episodes.title: Day Zero
episodes.description: Day Zero of placement is here and its a testing time for the group.

episodes.title: The Offer
episodes.description: Tensions rise high as the placement season is in it’s full swing and the gang must give it all to leave the hostel with a job in hand.

episodes.title: Hostel Departure
episodes.description: It's the end of a journey where everyone gets to say their final goodbyes to their beloved hostel. But each person does it in their own way.

episodes.title: Episode 1
episodes.description: In 1992, Ryu Eun-jung clashes with new student Cheon Sang-yeon out of envy. Years later, Sang-yeon returns with news of her illness — and a final request.

episodes.title: Episode 2
episodes.description: Upon rejecting Sang-yeon's request, Eun-jung revisits their past — from her complex friendship to her fondness for Cheon Sang-hak, Sang-yeon's brother.

episodes.title: Episode 3
episodes.description: Eun-jung meets Kim Sang-hak in her college photography club — a man who shares a name with someone from her past. Her timidness soon turns things awkward.

episodes.title: Episode 4
episodes.description: After years of no contact, Eun-jung and Sang-yeon meet again in college. But old shadows of insecurity soon resurface — rekindling old pain between them.

episodes.title: Episode 5
episodes.description: Sang-hak's enlistment sparks distance — for Eun-jung, ignored calls and secrets online begin to emerge, putting her friendship with Sang-yeon in danger.

episodes.title: Episode 6
episodes.description: Sang-yeon and Sang-hak grow closer as they bond over her brother, and Eun-jung's suspicions grow — leading her to a truth that changes how she sees them.

episodes.title: Episode 7
episodes.description: After Eun-jung confronts her about Sang-hak, Sang-yeon tries to ease the tension — but soon discovers a shattering secret about her brother.

episodes.title: Episode 8
episodes.description: Left out by Sang-hak and Sang-yeon's secret, Eun-jung feels alone and adrift — until heartbreak and hardship scatter all three in different directions.

episodes.title: Episode 9
episodes.description: Now a film producer, Eun-jung crosses paths with Sang-hak once again — but when disastrous news hits their project, Sang-yeon reappears.

episodes.title: Episode 10
episodes.description: As filming begins, Eun-jung and Sang-yeon clash over scripts, budgets, and creative style — while both hope to land Sang-hak as their cinematographer.

episodes.title: Episode 11
episodes.description: A remote location scout leaves Eun-jung and Sang-yeon isolated, and small setbacks and creative clashes spiral into an unresolved, tense standoff.

episodes.title: Episode 12
episodes.description: An on-set accident puts filming in jeopardy. Eun-jung and Sang-yeon must pull together to keep the project on track — relying on Sang-hak's expertise.

episodes.title: Episode 13
episodes.description: Sang-yeon's resentment for Eun-jung boils over, just as a violent on-set crisis throws the production — and their partnership — into chaos.

episodes.title: Episode 14
episodes.description: After their friendship ends in anger, Eun-jung shuts Sang-yeon out for good. Years later, Sang-yeon returns, hoping Eun-jung will grant her last wish.

episodes.title: Episode 15
episodes.description: As Sang-yeon nears her final journey, Eun-jung grapples with a difficult promise. On the eve of goodbye, they share memories from a lifetime of friendship.

episodes.title: Episode 12
episodes.description: Episode 12 of You and Everything Else

episodes.title: The Dead Never Lie
episodes.description: Sub Inspector Sanket Salelkar gets the first murder investigation of his career when Mala Coutinho, the owner of a 200-year-old Portuguese villa, is found murdered in her bed. The case looks pretty straightforward but his sister Sarla has other news for him.

episodes.title: To Be A Daughter
episodes.description: Sanket realizes he’s made a big career mistake and he has no idea how Mala Coutinho died, forget who killed her. Sanket enlists Sarla to help with the case and together they discover their first clue, a possible new murder weapon?

episodes.title: Echoes From The Past
episodes.description: The needle of suspicion turns to Mala’s daughter, Shalini. However, the truth is shrouded in different versions of the same incident. A new lead turns up with new information about Mala’s life but the cause of death remains elusive.

episodes.title: All That Glitters
episodes.description: Sanket discovers the true nature of Mala and Vishwas’s relationship even as Ignatius and Shalini continue to withhold information. A missing jewelry piece brings a new suspect and Sanket lays a trap hoping that the killer reveals themselves.

episodes.title: The Thin Line
episodes.description: Sarla’s past comes back to haunt her as Sanket’s trap yields a catch, but soon he realizes that he’s caught the wrong fish yet again. As he faces suspension, Sarla finally cracks the case and only to realise that it’s a perfect crime.

episodes.title: Wednesday's Child Is Full of Woe
episodes.description: When a deliciously wicked prank gets Wednesday expelled, her parents ship her off to Nevermore Academy, the boarding school where they fell in love.

episodes.title: Woe Is the Loneliest Number
episodes.description: The sheriff questions Wednesday about the night's strange happenings. Later, Wednesday faces off against a fierce rival in the cutthroat Poe Cup race.

episodes.title: Friend or Woe
episodes.description: Wednesday stumbles on a secret society. During Outreach Day, Nevermore's outcasts mingle with Jericho's normies in Pilgrim World. Fudge, anyone?

episodes.title: Woe What a Night
episodes.description: Wednesday asks Xavier to the Rave'N dance, sparking Tyler's jealousy — but Thing's got something up his sleeve. Meanwhile, Eugene stakes out the cave.

episodes.title: You Reap What You Woe
episodes.description: During Parents Weekend, Wednesday digs into her family's past — and accidentally gets her dad arrested. Enid feels the pressure to "wolf out."

episodes.title: Quid Pro Woe
episodes.description: Wednesday's friends throw her a surprise birthday party. They mean well... but she'd much rather mark the miserable occasion by solving the murders.

episodes.title: If You Don't Woe Me by Now
episodes.description: Kooky Uncle Fester pays a visit and shares his theory about the monster. Wednesday begrudgingly agrees to a date with Tyler at Crackstone's crypt.

episodes.title: A Murder of Woes
episodes.description: Wednesday lands in trouble with Principal Weems, but that's just the start of her problems. To fight an ancient evil, she'll need all her friends’ help.

episodes.title: Here We Woe Again
episodes.description: After a productive summer break, Wednesday returns to Nevermore as a grudging campus celebrity — and the target of a dangerous stalker.

episodes.title: The Devil You Woe
episodes.description: Chaos reigns on campus as Nevermore celebrates its annual Prank Day. Wednesday confronts an old enemy and gains an unwanted ally.

episodes.title: Call of the Woe
episodes.description: Stripped of both her ability and Goody's book, Wednesday is forced to do some old-fashioned detective work on a school camping trip.

episodes.title: If These Woes Could Talk
episodes.description: It's an Addams family investigation as Fester and Thing commit themselves to Wednesday's case. Trying to conceal one secret, Bianca stumbles on another.

episodes.title: Hyde and Woe Seek
episodes.description: With Tyler on the loose, Wednesday readies for a risky Día de los Muertos showdown. Slurp's growing hunger poses problems for Pugsley.

episodes.title: Woe Thyself
episodes.description: An encounter with a spirit from Nevermore's past gives Wednesday and Enid a new perspective on one another — and puts one of their classmates in danger.

episodes.title: Woe Me the Money
episodes.description: As the school gala looms, Wednesday digs up dirt on Dort, Enid tries not to wolf out and Morticia engages in a battle of wills with Grandmama.

episodes.title: This Means Woe
episodes.description: When buried family secrets are unearthed, Wednesday must race against time to prevent a dark prophecy from being realized.

episodes.title: Episode 1
episodes.description: At a society party, the staff of VivaLife Pharma learns about a drug scandal. Raji and Mala go property hunting to operate their tiffin business.

episodes.title: Episode 2
episodes.description: Sheila revisits her past. Preeti questions Shahida as Pathak travels to Amritsar for an investigation. A missing item causes an altercation with Chavan.

episodes.title: Episode 3
episodes.description: Varuna's Sitara is running into losses. Sheila and Chavan strike a deal as she hatches a plan with Moushumi on the side. Raji's Kitchen takes off.

episodes.title: Episode 4
episodes.description: Varuna receives a lucrative opportunity while Pathak makes a breakthrough in his investigation. Hari and Shankar devise ways to handle the Modella stock.

episodes.title: Episode 5
episodes.description: Varuna and Shankar get into an argument. A South American drug presents new opportunities. The women unite to pull out of their current predicament.

episodes.title: Episode 6
episodes.description: Bhowmick and Raji work together to create a “sweet” new drug. More details emerge about VivaLife's trials while a new threat to the cartel arises.

episodes.title: Episode 7
episodes.description: Raji and Sheila are at odds about their future. Preeti and Pathak make a startling discovery. Chacko has an offer for the gang.

episodes.title: Meet The Ba***ds
episodes.description: Aasmaan's debut film scores big, earning him a contract at a star-studded bash. At an actors' roundtable, he throws shade at nepo-baby Karishma Talvar.

episodes.title: ⁠⁠Movie Mafia
episodes.description: Aasmaan meets Freddy and later signs a commercial to fund his father's surgery. Ajay disapproves of the male lead cast opposite his daughter.

episodes.title: Barbaad Mohabbat
episodes.description: Parvaiz fanboys over Aasmaan and Karishma's new intimacy coach. A video of the leads goes viral for the wrong reasons. Freddy seeks Ajay's help.

episodes.title: Bullshit Party
episodes.description: Avtar's hit song catches Karan Johar's attention. Ajay objects to the film's intimate scenes. Karishma's birthday party brings a huge surprise.

episodes.title: My Hero
episodes.description: Jaraj shows Freddy an incriminating video of Aasmaan and pitches a plan. After falling out with Parvaiz, Aasmaan receives upsetting news.

episodes.title: The Filmfirst Awards
episodes.description: Avtar turns away an unexpected guest. At a glamorous awards show, Aasmaan faces a pleasant surprise — but soon finds himself in trouble.

episodes.title: Picture Ka Title Hoga…
episodes.description: As Aasmaan and Karishma try to elope with Parvaiz's help, Ajay chases after them. A shocking revelation threatens to upend Aasmaan's world.

episodes.title: Episode 1
episodes.description: The Professor recruits a young female robber and seven other criminals for a grand heist, targeting the Royal Mint of Spain.

episodes.title: Episode 2
episodes.description: Hostage negotiator Raquel makes initial contact with the Professor. Police grab an image of the face of one of the robbers.

episodes.title: Episode 3
episodes.description: Raquel suffers a personal crisis with her ex. The hostages are frightened by the gunshots they overheard. The thieves argue among themselves.

episodes.title: Episode 4
episodes.description: The thieves let a medical team enter the Mint, and an undercover policemansneaks in with them. Can the Professor stay one step ahead of Raquel?

episodes.title: Episode 5
episodes.description: Rio is disturbed by news he sees on the television. A break in the investigation puts the Professor at risk of being discovered.

episodes.title: Episode 6
episodes.description: Berlin seeks revenge once his identity is revealed in the press. Tokyo catches Alison chatting with Rio and confronts her.

episodes.title: Episode 7
episodes.description: Raquel enters the Mint to secure proof of life that all of the hostages are still alive and well. Nairobi gives Alison advice.

episodes.title: Episode 8
episodes.description: Arturo formulates an escape plan for a group of hostages. Ángel and Raquel question each other's loyalties. Mónica makes a move on Denver.
The Professor reveals who gave him the idea for the plan. At the Mint, the thieves offer the hostages a decision: money or freedom?
episodes.title: Episode 9

episodes.description: As forensic experts comb the Toledocountry house for DNA, the Professor loses control. Inside the Mint, the robbers' nerves reach a breaking point.
episodes.title: Episode 10

episodes.description: The police interrogate the first robber to be captured. Furious over Berlin's recent actions, Rio takes a stand against him.
episodes.title: Episode 11

episodes.description: Recognizing their plan isn't working out, the robbers instead aim to win over the public via the press. Raquel sets a trap to capture the Professor.
episodes.title: Episode 12

episodes.description: Arturo faces harsh consequences for trying to set another escape plan in motion. After making a confession, Moscow loses Denver's trust.
episodes.title: Episode 13
We're Back
episodes.description: When Rio is captured, a distraught Tokyo turns to the Professor for help. Armed with a bold new plan, they reunite the team in order to rescue him.

episodes.title: Aikido
episodes.description: The Professor recruits Martin to put his brother's plan into action and target the Bank of Spain. First step? Create total chaos.

episodes.title: 48 Meters Underground
episodes.description: Tokyo and Nairobi's efforts go drastically awry. The Professor recalls Berlin detailing how they'd steal the gold from the water-logged vault.

episodes.title: It's Dolphin Time
episodes.description: Tamayo's breaches of protocol surprise the Professor. Bogota calms Denver's anxieties. With time running out, Palermo initiates the "Flipper" plan.

episodes.title: Boom, Boom, Ciao
episodes.description: The Professor shocks officials with his latest stunt, but in response, a new inspector rattles Raquel. Palermo and Nairobi get into a heated argument.

episodes.title: Everything Seemed Insignificant
episodes.description: Just as Inspector Sierra orchestrates a plan to sneak a team into the Bank of Spain, the Professor and Raquel lose communication with Palermo.
Tokyo's happiness turns bittersweet. Angel closes in on a quarreling Raquel and the Professor. Authorities offer a multimillion-dollar reward for tips.
episodes.title: A Quick Vacation

episodes.description: Tokyo attempts to drown her sorrows. Sierra uses personal tactics to target a vulnerable Nairobi, while Suarez continues to hunt down Raquel.
episodes.title: Astray

episodes.description: Anger and grief heighten tensions between the group. The Professor, while in mourning, attempts to make a daring and dangerous escape.
episodes.title: Game Over

episodes.description: The Professor faces off with Sierra as Tamayo raises the stakes of the negotiations by calling the army. In the past, Berlin meets with a family member.
episodes.title: The End of the Road

episodes.description: Arturo seizes an opportunity to fight back while escalating a personal vengeance. Lisbon makes a crucial discovery.
episodes.title: Do You Believe in Reincarnation?

episodes.description: A betrayal and an emergency both catch Sierra by surprise. Palermo rallies the troops as the army closes in on the gang.
episodes.title: Welcome to the Spectacle of Life

episodes.description: With Helsinki's life in danger, the thieves mount a covert counter attack. Years earlier, Berlin and his son conduct their first heist together.
episodes.title: Your Place in Heaven

episodes.description: While surrounded by gunfire and trapped in the kitchen, Tokyo reminisces about her first love and her initial encounter with the Professor.
episodes.title: Live Many Lives

episodes.description: Sierra takes advantage of the Professor's grief and gains the upper hand. Meanwhile, the team deals with the emotional fallout of their dead friend.
episodes.title: Escape Valve

episodes.description: Tamayo mounts a manhunt in his neighborhood as his foes hide. In the past, Berlin and Palermo explain how they plan on getting the gold out of the bank.
episodes.title: Wishful Thinking

episodes.description: Tamayo hunts for the gold as the team races against the clock. Mónica worries she's having a psychotic break. Years earlier, Berlin is deceived.
episodes.title: The Elegance Theory

episodes.title: Episode 10
Sleep with the Fishes
episodes.description: Shukla, a power-hungry politician, plots to topple the government. Two luckless strangers find that they have a common enemy and a thirst for revenge.

episodes.title: Enemy of My Enemy
episodes.description: The team takes shape as Ansari and J.P. Yadav join forces with a bumbling cop and a wily con man — and hatch a plot to steal Shukla's ill-gotten cash.

episodes.title: Playing with Fire
episodes.description: A key member of Shukla's inner circle becomes a silent but vengeful ally. Ansari springs into action when a massive fire breaks out at Pathaani Tola.

episodes.title: Secrets Revealed
episodes.description: Shukla schemes to drive a wedge between Ansari and a rageful Baankeylal. Bela is caught in the crossfire when Ansari’s former allies seek revenge.

episodes.title: So It Begins...
episodes.description: An abduction pushes Bela to take matters into her own hands. The gang scrambles after a drunken Baankeylal puts their mission in jeopardy.

episodes.title: Et tu, Brute?
episodes.description: Disguised as an all-knowing seer, Triloki edges closer to Shukla. When Ansari's loyalty is questioned, plans for the heist spiral into crisis.

episodes.title: Caught Before the Act
episodes.description: On the day of the solar eclipse, the theft is set in motion. But unexpected bumps throw the team's carefully laid plans into major turbulence.

episodes.title: The Eclipse
episodes.description: A surprising development propels the plan forward. Will the stars align for these misfits — or will fortune fall in Shukla's favor?

episodes.title: Someone Has Betrayed
episodes.description: The life of Taj, a former boxing champion, is turned upside down after a failed assassination attempt on Colonel Joel of the French colonial army.

episodes.title: Under The Table
episodes.description: Nouran visits her ex-husband Taj to see their daughter Salma. Saleem offers Taj a risky mission. Later, Taj finds himself in a sticky situation after a gambling game.

episodes.title: The Suit
episodes.description: Struggling to find a way out of the financial bond dilemma, Taj reconsiders Saleem's offer.

episodes.title: In The Ring
episodes.description: Taj prepares to fight a Nazi boxer in the French barracks, putting in motion his and Saleem's plan to gain access to secret files on the informer.

episodes.title: The Archives
episodes.description: Following Syria's declaration of independence, Saleem tries talking Taj into giving their mission another shot.

episodes.title: The Allied Forces Are In Damascus
episodes.description: As Saleem attempts to hide the secret files in a secure location, Taj seeks Marion's assistance to rescue Subhi from the hospital.

episodes.title: In The Ministry Of Interior
episodes.description: Zakaria continues interrogating Saleem. Meanwhile, Taj tries to locate the files Saleem concealed before his arrest.

episodes.title: The German Airplane
episodes.description: Taj devises a plan to blackmail Zakaria into releasing Saleem from prison by taking compromising photos of him.

episodes.title: Jenny
episodes.description: Taj reveals to Saleem that Jenny stole the files. Colonel Joel pressures Zakaria to find out how Saleem managed to escape.

episodes.title: Little Secrets
episodes.description: Taj begins interrogating Jenny so he can get his hands on the secret files. Henry leaves the hospital with vengeance blazing in his eyes.

episodes.title: Episode 1
episodes.description: A demonstration ends violently. Tensions rise with the arrival of the riot squad's new leader and the protest's fallout.

episodes.title: Episode 2
episodes.description: Nobili tries to lead the team amid Mazinga's resistance, resulting in another injured agent. Investigations continue as someone questions loyalty.

episodes.title: Episode 3
episodes.description: The unit faces interrogation. Marta fears for her daughter. Nobili earns respect by defending a family during a riot — while a crisis erupts at home.

episodes.title: Episode 4
episodes.description: While Nobili opens up to Marta, Mazinga expresses his exhaustion with work. Salvatore's long-distance relationship triggers his insecurities.

episodes.title: Episode 5
episodes.description: Still unsure about what to do with the new evidence, Nobili takes the law into his own hands — and so does Salvatore. Pietro gets serious with Mazinga.

episodes.title: Episode 6
episodes.description: At a Christmas dinner, Nobili makes a final move to fit in with the squad. A notification from the prosecution puts everyone at risk of suspension.

episodes.title: The Sound of Metal
episodes.description: A brutal road accident that kills a young man. When the man’s mother, Chandana, tells Meenakshi that it wasn’t an accident and requests her to investigate it, Meenakshi refuses saying PI’s have no business investigating murders. But can she stay away?

episodes.title: The Death Freeze
episodes.description: Still unsure, Meenakshi starts digging. She starts suspecting that the dead man was somehow linked to a mysterious virus outbreak in the village of Littnong, Eastern Himalayas.

episodes.title: The Heart of Darkness
episodes.description: Now convinced that the young man was indeed killed, Meenakshi undertakes a reckless journey to Littnong, seeking to find the killer.

episodes.title: The Pretender's Bluder
episodes.description: Meenakshi starts building her theory around the virus. Soon realises that her own life could be under threat.

episodes.title: The Hidden Hazard
episodes.description: A virus starts breaking out around Kolkata. Meenakshi’s investigation picks up speed. A Central Intelligence officer warns Meenakshi to stay away from something that’s way beyond her comprehension.

episodes.title: The Live Data
episodes.description: Kolkata is gripped by the virus outbreak. Meenakshi links the Kolkata virus to the Littnong one. Unknown to her, games are being played by her own accomplices about the identity of the virus. She must go back to Littnong to find some light.

episodes.title: The Boat Called Ujaan
episodes.description: A few earth-shattering breakthroughs stab Meenakshi’s heart. She decides not to continue with her investigation any more only to be brought back to it by her friend. Because now it is not just a man’s death but the need to stop a genocide.

episodes.title: The Reckless Sister
episodes.description: When Meenakshi finally cracks her case, she needs to act. And act she does. Most recklessly.
