episodes.title: Pilot
episodes.description: Having her handbag stolen proves to be a blessing for Fiona when a handsome stranger named Steve comes to her rescue. Lip is shocked to discover Ian could be gay and decides his brother should pay a visit to the ever-accommodating Karen Jackson down the block. But the sudden arrival of her furious father Eddie ensures Ian's already-slim chances of happiness with Karen take a severe blow. Meanwhile, Steve buys Fiona a romantic gift, but for some reason she's less than impressed with it.

episodes.title: Frank the Plank
episodes.description: Drunk as a skunk, Frank has a run-in with Karen's father and returns home to take it out on Ian. The next day is Friday, and Frank is nowhere to be found, which is a bit odd since he never misses disability check day. The family starts a manhunt. .

episodes.title: Aunt Ginger
episodes.description: Fiona turns her attentions to Tony, a cop who has had a crush on her since childhood, but Steve isn't willing to give up without a fight; Ian is targeted by the brothers of a girl he spurned; the whole family searches for elderly Aunt Ginger, who owns their house.

episodes.title: Casey Casden
episodes.description: Debbie, sad and lonely after Aunt Ginger leaves, steals a little boy from a birthday party. In classic Gallagher style, the family hatches a plan to return the toddler safe and sound without attracting attention from the Chicago Police Department, who has made the kidnapping a top priority. Karen, in complete defiance of Eddie, starts to tease Frank sexually. Frank not knowing what to make of it keeps himself busy with booze, picking up Sheila'­s meds from the pharmacy and concentrating on finding the missing boy. What began as an innocent lie for Kevin to protect himself from a hot girl ultimately becomes a proposal of marriage for Veronica.

episodes.title: Three Boys
episodes.description: When the Gallagher's find out Veronica comes from a wealthy family, they try to scheme a fake wedding for the dowry. Meanwhile, Frank gets some bad news about his health.

episodes.title: Killer Carl
episodes.description: Fiona tries to prove the Gallagher home is suitable for rehabilitating a delinquent after receiving a letter from Carl's teacher; Lip gets busted taking the SAT for fellow students in exchange for cash; Kash and Ian are ashamed at their failure to stop a string of robberies at the Kash and Grab; Frank's poor business acumen continues to have negative consequences.

episodes.title: Frank Gallagher: Loving Husband, Devoted Father
episodes.description: Frank gets into trouble with two goons he owes money. Fiona asks Sheila to take care of Liam while she spends a night with Steve, and Ian tries to stop Mickey from bullying Kash.

episodes.title: It's Time to Kill the Turtle
episodes.description: Sheila fears to lose Frank when he gives up drinking. While Lip suspects their dad hasn't changed, Debbie and Carl enjoy having Frank back in their life. Meanwhile, Fiona tries to find a better paid job.

episodes.title: But at Last Came a Knock
episodes.description: Monica comes back when Frank needs her to sign documents and decides to take Liam with her. Meanwhile, Steve and Fiona move together.

episodes.title: Nana Gallagher Had an Affair
episodes.description: The children's paternity is put into question and Frank needs Carl's help.

episodes.title: Daddyz Girl
episodes.description: Tony comes closer to discovering what Steve is doing, while Fiona makes a new friend. In the meantime, Lip helps Ian look for his father.

episodes.title: Father Frank, Full of Grace
episodes.description: Steve tries to convince Fiona to skip town with him now that his true livelihood as been discovered; Frank and Karen's secret is revealed, forcing Frank to go into hiding; Fiona tries to figure out how to get Lip and Ian out of jail after their arrest for car theft.

episodes.title: Summertime
episodes.description: Fiona spends her summer with a new guy and bartending, while Debbie runs a daycare at their home. Meanwhile, Kevin realizes his extended weed-growing left him with a huge electrical bill and Frank borrows his youngest son Liam to help him pay a debt.

episodes.title: Summer Loving
episodes.description: As Sheila conquers her agoraphobia, a worried Frank finds a new financial plan in fellow bar patron Dottie, whose declining health and city pension make her an ideal match; Fiona juggles her job, the kids and her burgeoning love life, and Jasmine tries to help by setting up Fiona with a sugar daddy; Veronica takes some old folks from the home on an excursion; Lip worries about Karen's growing relationship with Jody; Ian tries to land a recently released Mickey a job at the Kash and Grab; Debbie wants her own room; Carl moves into the van.

episodes.title: I'll Light a Candle for You Every Day
episodes.description: Fiona hopes her moral compass isn't leading her astray when she reconnects with her married high school crush, but when she finds an abandoned purse with over five hundred dollars inside, she assumes her luck is finally changing; Frank is willing to do just about anything to stay in Dottie's good graces, even marry her; after Harry's passing, Debbie becomes obsessed with death; Kevin thinks about buying the Alibi; Lip meets with a colonel to glean information for Ian about West Point; Jody asks Frank for Karen's hand in marriage.

episodes.title: A Beautiful Mess
episodes.description: Fiona deals with the consequences of sleeping with Craig when his angry wife shows up at the door; Debbie develops a stress-rash and Fiona wonders if she's putting too much responsibility on the kids; Sheila has made it all the way to the hair salon and Frank realizes his days in the Jackson household are numbered; no longer having sex with Karen, Lip tries to dig up dirt on Jody; Ian continues on the path to West Point; Carl house-sits with his friend, Little Hank; Ethel meets Malik, a boy on Kevin's youth basketball team.

episodes.title: Father's Day
episodes.description: Frank tries to claim Eddie's insurance benefits and pension, despite being a prime suspect in his death; Fiona attends a ritzy wedding with Richard and lies about her background; Lip is devastated by Karen's rejection; Carl rents Frank's room to a hooker.

episodes.title: Can I Have a Mother
episodes.description: Grammy Gallagher shows up on a medical furlough and tries to track down a former meth lab protege that owes her money; Sheila plans Karen's wedding reception; Fiona double dates with Steve and his Brazilian girlfriend, and discovers that Steve is married; Ethel reacts to Clyde's death; Frank discovers the identity of Eddie's insurance beneficiary.

episodes.title: A Bottle of Jean Nate
episodes.description: Lip tries to get back in Karen's good graces by crafting a prenuptial agreement for her and Jody, while Ian continues to give Lip the silent treatment; Frank wants to kick Grammy out but Fiona resists until the basement meth lab explodes; Fiona is invited on a boat trip but doesn't realize Steve and his girlfriend are also attending.

episodes.title: Parenthood
episodes.description: With Grammy near death, Frank exits the house but walks in on Ian and Mickey locked in passion at the Kash and Grab; when Lip drops out of school, Fiona proposes a deal where they both earn their diplomas, but Lip acts out and gets himself expelled when he realizes that Karen plans to sell their baby to the highest bidder.

episodes.title: Hurricane Monica
episodes.description: Monica returns to party and plot scams with Frank, but the rest of the family suspects she hasn't returned to stay; Fiona reconsiders her decision to kick Lip out of the house; Grammy's death affects everyone differently, and leaves Frank determined to make sure he gets every last penny his mother left behind; Sheila and Jody think Eddie's ghost is haunting the house.

episodes.title: A Great Cause
episodes.description: Fiona starts to plan for her future now that Monica is back but her reprieve may be short-lived as Monica falls apart, spends the squirrel fund and gets arrested; Steve conspires to reunite Estefania with her true love so that he can be with Fiona; Lip and Ian learn the true identity of Mandy's baby; Sheila takes in a homeless crack addict.

episodes.title: Just Like the Pilgrims Intended
episodes.description: It's a typical Gallagher nontraditional Thanksgiving that includes a suicide attempt by Monica, Carl shooting a bald eagle, and Karen going into labor; Steve agrees to allow Estefania's boyfriend to steal his identity; Ian sleeps with a businessman named Ned; Frank tries to get his share of his mother's money from his brother Clayton.

episodes.title: Fiona Interrupted
episodes.description: A lonely Frank schemes to break Monica out of the psychiatric facility. Jimmy earns his way back into Fiona's good graces and she asks to meet his family while Ian runs into Ned again.

episodes.title: El Gran Cañon
episodes.description: Frank wakes up in a place completely foreign to him.

episodes.title: The American Dream
episodes.description: Fiona is stressed about the money she used for her club night; Frank makes his way home.

episodes.title: May I Trim Your Hedges?
episodes.description: Frank tells Carl he has cancer to scam a charity foundation; Lip hunts down pedophiles in the neighborhood.

episodes.title: The Helpful Gallaghers
episodes.description: Carl says his goodbyes; Frank is on babysitting duty; Sheila wants to introduce Jody to toy time.

episodes.title: The Sins of My Caretaker
episodes.description: The city of Chicago gives notice that they're doing work on the sewer main. The problem? Aunt Ginger's bones are still buried in the yard and Frank needs to find her before the city does. Meanwhile, Fiona is picked on at work for not satisfying her boss. When Fiona fails to provide the support Jimmy needs, he turns to Este. Molly learns that she's a boy and Ned asks Ian to rob his wife's house.

episodes.title: Cascading Failures
episodes.description: The Department of Family Services hauls the Gallagher children away, leaving Fiona desperate to get them back. With Monica nowhere to be found, Fiona is forced to find Frank and get him to make a "Father of the Year" appearance in court. It all goes well until Fiona discovers that Frank's not the solution to her problem - he's the cause. Meanwhile, Kev and Veronica recruit V's mother as a surrogate and Terry catches Mickey and Ian in a compromising situation.

episodes.title: A Long Way from Home
episodes.description: Frank and Fiona go to extreme lengths in court to claim custody of the kids.

episodes.title: Where There's a Will
episodes.description: The family gathers for the real Aunt Ginger's fake funeral.

episodes.title: Frank the Plumber
episodes.description: Fiona starts a new office job but has a hard time fitting in with the corporate culture. In an attempt to get medical coverage, Frank inadvertently becomes involved in the gay rights movement where he meets Abraham Paige, a powerful activist.

episodes.title: Civil Wrongs
episodes.description: Fiona's job has brought structure ito her life, but when Jimmy drops a bomb on her things fall apart. Frank is happy with his newfound celebrity as the face of the gay rights movement.

episodes.title: Order Room Service
episodes.description: Fiona takes the kids on a camping trip. Essentially homeless, Frank seeks out Carl who sneaks him into the Gallagher van for the night.

episodes.title: Survival of the Fittest
episodes.description: Fiona and the family prepare a surprise high school,graduation party for Lip. Frank wins a bet and uses the winnings to take Lip out for lobster and some quality father/son time.

episodes.title: Simple Pleasures
episodes.description: Frank returns, disrupting life; Lip attends college; Ian is missing; Fiona tries to connect with Debbie and Carl.

episodes.title: My Oldest Daughter
episodes.description: Fiona begins to enjoy the perks of living life just above the poverty line. She uses her newly activated health benefits to take the kids for checkups. However, when a road rage incident damages the company car, Fiona tells a much bigger lie about how it happened. Meanwhile, Lip seems to have lost his mojo as he struggles in school and with the ladies.

episodes.title: Like Father, Like Daughter
episodes.description: Frank stalks his previously unseen daughter, Sammi, and is surprised to find out she has a son, Chuck. Meanwhile, Fiona and Mike are getting serious. Also, Carl begins stealing dogs and holding them for ransom so that he can earn some drug money for Frank. Sheila has her first successful online date with Native American cowboy Roger Running Tree.

episodes.title: Strangers on a Train
episodes.description: Against her better judgment, Fiona continues her secret affair with Robbie. The situation nearly boils over when Mike shows up at Robbie’s apartment while Fiona is inside. Fiona is able to hide just in time before her infidelity can be exposed. Frank, in increasingly dire health straits due to liver disease, attempts to contrive an “accident” that will provide an ample insurance payout to cover the cost of a potential transplant.

episodes.title: There's the Rub
episodes.description: Fiona's series of bad decisions involving Robbie finally boil over. Meanwhile, Frank and Sammi pursue a cure for Frank's liver trouble and try to catch up on missed father-daughter time; and Lip gets a surprise visit at college from Army investigators.

episodes.title: Iron City
episodes.description: Fiona ends up in jail; the family waits for news about Liam; Frank wakes up in the emergency room.

episodes.title: A Jailbird, Invalid, Martyr, Cutter, Retard, and Parasitic Twin
episodes.description: Guardianship duties fall upon Lip - who gets some unexpected assistance.

episodes.title: Hope Springs Paternal
episodes.description: To prepare for a visit from her probation officer, Fiona must remove all paraphernalia from the house; Ian is kicked out of Mickey's house.

episodes.title: The Legend of Bonnie and Carl
episodes.description: Carl connects with a girl in detention; Lip and Amanda grow closer; Sheila returns with big plans; Fiona searches for a job; Mickey spends time with Ian.

episodes.title: Liver, I Hardly Know Her
episodes.description: Fiona violates terms of her probation, sending the family into search party mode.

episodes.title: Emily
episodes.description: Fiona is hauled off to a correctional facility. Amanda’s parents bribe Lip.

episodes.title: Lazarus
episodes.description: Fiona gets out of jail. Frank is feeling like his old self.

episodes.title: Milk of the Gods
episodes.description: Fiona juggles her job and a crush. Lip heads back home.

episodes.title: I'm the Liver
episodes.description: Sheila gets an offer to buy her home. Plus, Fiona is off house arrest!

episodes.title: The Two Lisas
episodes.description: Frank enlists Carl to scare off the lesbians. Debbie throws a wild party.

episodes.title: A Night to Remem... Wait, What?
episodes.description: Frank retraces the path of an epic bender. Fiona and Gus head to city hall.

episodes.title: Rite of Passage
episodes.description: Fiona's plans to announce her marriage unravel. Mickey asks for Lip's help.

episodes.title: Crazy Love
episodes.description: Fiona is thrown into chaos by the return of Jimmy. Ian takes Mickey's baby.

episodes.title: Tell Me You F**king Need Me
episodes.description: Ian finds himself at the psych ward. Fiona decides between Jimmy and Gus.

episodes.title: Uncle Carl
episodes.description: Gus tells Fiona he's leaving to go on tour. Frank seeks revenge on Sammi.

episodes.title: Carl's First Sentencing
episodes.description: Frank plays tour guide for his doctor. Fiona preps Carl for sentencing.

episodes.title: South Side Rules
episodes.description: Frank has a ball with his new sick friend and formerly uptight doctor.

episodes.title: Drugs Actually
episodes.description: Frank grows concerned as Bianca's behavior becomes erratic and dangerous.

episodes.title: Love Songs (in the Key of Gallagher)
episodes.description: Fiona reunites with Gus. Frank works to keep Bianca happy. Season finale.

episodes.title: I Only Miss Her When I'm Breathing
episodes.description: Frank's newfound appreciation freaks the Gallaghers out.

episodes.title: #Abortion Rules
episodes.description: Debbie carries a bag of flour around - determined to prove Fiona wrong.

episodes.title: The F Word
episodes.description: Frank teaches Debbie how to work the system. Kev and Veronica visit Yanis.

episodes.title: Going Once, Going Twice
episodes.description: Fiona confronts Patrick. Ian makes a discovery at the firehouse.

episodes.title: Refugees
episodes.description: Frank helps Erica as Debbie ups her game. Lip tries to protect Helene.

episodes.title: NSFW
episodes.description: Ian and Caleb get serious. Lip appears before a disciplinary committee.

episodes.title: Pimp's Paradise
episodes.description: Carl remakes the Gallagher home as his "crib." Debbie gets let go.

episodes.title: Be a Good Boy. Come for Grandma.
episodes.description: Sean catches Will with one of Carl's guns and Fiona bears the brunt.

episodes.title: A Yurt of One's Own
episodes.description: Fiona tries to make amends with Sean. Debbie and Queenie trek to a commune.

episodes.title: Paradise Lost
episodes.description: Sean moves into the Gallagher house as Fiona plans a traditional wedding.

episodes.title: Sleep No More
episodes.description: A confrontation between Sean and Frank quickly descends into a brawl.

episodes.title: Familia Supra Gallegorious Omnia!
episodes.description: It's wedding day and Frank shows up uninvited - and high.

episodes.title: Hiraeth
episodes.description: Frank wakes up after a month-long coma to find no one missed him. Worried she isn't a good mother, Debbie takes a criminal approach to making sure Franny grows up wealthy. Meanwhile, Lip successfully completes rehab and is determined to stay "sober;" Carl looks into surgery after learning he's the only uncircumcised brother; and Ian gets a bad feeling about Caleb's friend Denise.

episodes.title: Swipe, F**k, Leave
episodes.description: Ready to disown his family, Frank takes Liam under wing and starts a new life barricaded on the top floor of the Gallagher home. Fiona, meanwhile, adopts a new, relaxed attitude and starts running Patsy's Pies on her own terms. Debbie gets into trouble in the stroller business; Ian tries out heterosexuality; and Carl finds himself forced into abstinence.

episodes.title: Home Sweet Homeless Shelter
episodes.description: Kevin, Veronica and Svetlana start a topless maid service. At the shelter, meanwhile, Frank makes new friends to replace his old family - leading them to a for-sale house converted into the Gallagher Home for the Homeless. Plus, Debbie's new lifestyle comes to an abrupt end; Carl gets a syphilis scare; Ian struggles with a breakup; and with Fiona on the run to clean up after her siblings, business at Patsy's hits the skids.

episodes.title: I Am a Storm
episodes.description: Frank worries that he and his new family will lose their Home for the Homeless shelter, so he plans a little goodwill for the neighborhood. Meanwhile, Fiona drums up business by throwing a speakeasy party at Patsy's Pies.

episodes.title: Own Your Sh*t
episodes.description: Frank learns that a billionaire philanthropist has bought the homeless shelter and he and his clan can stay. Meanwhile, Fiona gets smart financial advice from a Tinder hookup as Ian struggles with his feelings for Trevor.

episodes.title: The Defenestration of Frank
episodes.description: Fiona sees opportunity in a laundromat for sale and decides to invest. Frank revels in the good fortune of his scam, but the troops catch a whiff of foul play. Meanwhile, Kev and V discover a shocking secret about Svetlana's father.

episodes.title: You Sold Me the Laundromat, Remember?
episodes.description: Fiona takes a DIY approach to renovating the laundromat. Lip agrees to go before the school board in hopes of getting reinstated. Meanwhile, Kev's trust in Svetlana wanes even further when the titty van goes missing.

episodes.title: Ouroboros
episodes.description: Monica is back! And her first task is to help Debbie get back Franny. Meanwhile, Frank tries to avoid her, Ian has his first fight with Trevor, Lip tries to mask his relapsing alcoholism and Fiona's laundromat gets a bad review.

episodes.title: Ride or Die
episodes.description: Fiona, facing mounting issues, contemplates Margo's offer to buy the laundromat. Meanwhile, Ian tries to deal with the fact that Mickey might be out of prison and Kev and V take matters into their own hands after Svetlana's betrayal.

episodes.title: Happily Ever After
episodes.description: Frank and Monica have an interesting proposal for the kids. Lip buckles under pressure from Debbie to get his sobriety under control. Meanwhile, Fiona sees a business opportunity as Kev and V attempt to start a new chapter.

episodes.title: Requiem for a Slut
episodes.description: The Gallaghers grapple with the loss of one of their own. As Lip takes steps to improve his future, Debbie, Carl and Liam get roped into Frank's new scheme.

episodes.title: We Become What We... Frank!
episodes.description: The Gallaghers find themselves with money to burn as Carl sells their inheritance from Monica. Fiona swears off random hookups to focus on her new apartment building. Lip deals with the sacrifice that comes with sobriety. Frank emerges out of a meth-induced haze to make amends for decades of depravity.

episodes.title: Where's My Meth?
episodes.description: Frank re-lives his 20s and joins the workforce for the first time! Fiona grapples with evicting someone from her building. Lip works out a plan to sabotage Charlie's chances with Sierra. Ian and Carl make a troubling discovery about Monica. Kev says his goodbyes as he prepares to go under the knife.

episodes.title: God Bless Her Rotting Soul
episodes.description: A violent meth dealer threatens the Gallaghers, forcing Ian, Carl, Lip and Debbie to find a way to pay him off without involving Fiona. Fiona battles it out with a vindictive tenant. Lip cares for a down-and-out Professor Youens. Frank - miraculously - attains something resembling sainthood.

episodes.title: F**k Paying It Forward
episodes.description: A blast from the past shakes up Fiona's view of her life. Frank gets involved with Liam's school and becomes the most popular dad in the PTA. Lip learns getting laid is harder than anticipated when sober. Ian crosses a boundary with a kid from the youth center. Kev and V take a trip to meet his birth family.

episodes.title: The (Mis)Education of Liam Fergus Beircheart Gallagher
episodes.description: As Fiona tries to raise the profile of the neighborhood, Ian helps Trevor to raise money for a new youth shelter. Meanwhile, Carl loses his scholarship and gets creative with securing the tuition, Lip stands up to a friend and gets hurt and Frank teaches the parents at Liam's school all about the working class.

episodes.title: Icarus Fell and Rusty Ate Him
episodes.description: Fiona is forced to reflect on her own life after a lonely tenant dies and the duty of cleaning out the apartment falls upon her. Meanwhile, Debbie has a pregnancy scare and winds up in a compromising position, Lip enlists Carl's help to search for his sponsor and Frank enjoys having his first-ever credit card.

episodes.title: Occupy Fiona
episodes.description: Ian tests Fiona's patience and resolve by bringing a messy “Occupy Fiona” movement right to her front door. Lip struggles to get Professor Youens to court for his DUI trial. Meanwhile, a now unemployed Frank goes on a job hunt and Carl gets a feisty new rehab client with a plan to help him get the rest of his tuition.

episodes.title: Frank's Northern Southern Express
episodes.description: Frank starts a booming import-export business. Fiona considers moving into her own place after Ford shows her a side of Chicago she's never seen. Meanwhile, Lip interviews new sponsors, Ian confronts a pastor trying to "pray the gay away" and Debbie deals with being unemployed while looking for a way to afford school and raise Franny.

episodes.title: The Fugees
episodes.description: Frank's business takes a turn for the worse, sending him on the run through the Great White North. Ian's run-in with a minister brings about some unexpected allies. Meanwhile, Fiona tries (and fails) to fit in with Ford's group of friends, Carl's new girlfriend suffers separation anxiety and Lip must decide whether to tell Sierra about Charlie's past.

episodes.title: Church of Gay Jesus
episodes.description: Ian's fame in the LGBTQIA community explodes but the sudden surge of 'followers' may be more than he can handle; Frank, however, finds a way to cash in. Meanwhile, Fiona struggles with her conscience when she learns about a worker who fell off her roof and Lip realizes his relationship with Professor Youens may not have been as special as he thought.

episodes.title: A Gallagher Pedicure
episodes.description: Fiona's homeless tenants barricade themselves inside her apartment. Lip takes in a terrified Sierra and Lucas when her father is released from prison. Meanwhile Ian, despite warnings, provides sanctuary to a runaway teen, Frank considers his retirement and Debbie must choose between paying for school and paying for surgery to keep her toes.

episodes.title: Sleepwalking
episodes.description: Fiona taps deep into her Gallagher roots to get the homeless family out of her apartment and dismiss their lawsuit. An explosive incident sends Ian and some of his followers into hiding from the authorities. Meanwhile, Lip makes a difficult decision in order to have the life he really wants, Carl looks for a way to go back to school without upsetting Kassidi, Debbie considers letting Derek back into Franny's life and Frank makes plans to take advantage of Liam's rich friend. Season finale.

episodes.title: Are You There Shim? It's Me, Ian.
episodes.description: Frank’s latest sexual escapades get him into trouble with the Hopkins Academy PTA. Fiona struggles with her decision to bail Ian out of jail, while he continues his Gay Jesus antics inside. Lip juggles taking care of Xan with a potential romance. Debbie fights for equal pay at work, and Carl has to prove himself at military school. Kev and V have trouble with the twins without Svetlana.

episodes.title: Mo White For President
episodes.description: Fiona makes a play for a risky investment opportunity, ignoring Ford’s advice. Frank discovers the financial incentives of local politics. Carl bolsters his West Point application in unexpected ways. Debbie struggles to find allies in her battle against sexual harassment. Ian is overwhelmed by the growth of the Gay Jesus movement. Kev and V try to find the perfect preschool for the twins.

episodes.title: Weirdo Gallagher Vortex
episodes.description: Frank faces obstacles in his new role as a campaign manager. Fiona prepares to close her real estate deal. Carl enlists V to help him get a West Point recommendation from a congressman. Xan’s medical emergency puts Lip in a compromising position. Debbie gets closer with her partner in crime. Ian embarks on a spiritual journey.

episodes.title: Do Right, Vote White!
episodes.description: Election day puts Frank and Fiona in a head to head battle as they each try to round up votes for their candidates. Lip has to make an important choice about Xan’s future. Debbie gets in over her head with Alex. Carl’s killer instinct is put to the test. With his trial looming, Ian struggles to decide how to plead. 100th episode!

episodes.title: Black-Haired Ginger
episodes.description: Frank’s new liver medication comes with tragic side effects. Ian tries to get away from Fiona’s hovering. Lip has to keep himself occupied during a day of temptation. Carl makes a connection at a West Point mixer. Debbie tries to repair things with Alex.

episodes.title: Face It, You're Gorgeous
episodes.description: Frank employs Liam to help him chase down a romantic connection; Fiona struggles to keep up with the demands of her new investment as Ford pushes her to get serious about their relationship.

episodes.title: Down Like the Titanic
episodes.description: Debbie finds Fiona at a low point and helps her pick up the pieces as Fiona continues to face pressure from Max Whitford on her investment hubris. Frank enjoys the honeymoon period of his relationship with Ingrid.

episodes.title: The Apple Doesn't Fall Far from the Alibi
episodes.description: Fiona's downward spiral continues and Debbie steps in to pick up the slack at the Gallagher house. Ingrid ropes Frank into fulfilling her lifelong dream. Tami shows Lip a different version of adulthood.

episodes.title: BOOOOOOOOOOOONE!
episodes.description: Frank searches for ways to finance Ingrid's vision for their future together. Fiona's anger issues cause problems at Patsy's. Lip is forced to confront his real feelings for Tami.

episodes.title: Los Diablos!
episodes.description: Frank meets his match in a fellow participant in the Hobo Loco competition. Fiona has a dark encounter at Patsy's that scares her into cleaning up her act. Debbie throws herself into home improvements as she gets closer with Kelly.

episodes.title: The Hobo Games
episodes.description: The finals of the Hobo Games have arrived, and Frank faces off against his friend and greatest opponent while Ingrid grows anxious about his commitment to their future family. Lip prepares to officially adopt Xan, but his plans collide with Fiona’s partying. Debbie starts developing feelings for someone surprising, and Carl excels at the shrimp shack.

episodes.title: You'll Know the Bottom When You Hit It
episodes.description: When a blackout hits the South Side, Kevin and Veronica come up with a plan to bring the neighborhood together. Carl grows suspicious of Debbie’s attempts to get closer with Kelly. Fiona receives guidance from an unexpected person and Lip has to deal with the fallout from Xan’s DCFS visit.

episodes.title: Lost
episodes.description: Frank’s injury gets in the way of everyone’s plans as Fiona attempts to get her life back on track and Lip grows frustrated with his relationship with Tami. Carl gets some bad news about his future, and Debbie finally makes a move on Kelly. Kevin and Veronica get in trouble at the twins’ preschool.

episodes.title: Found
episodes.description: As the Gallaghers decide what to do with a bedridden Frank, Fiona has to make a decision about her future. Carl and Debbie share their heartbreak together. Lip has to deal with a distressed Tami.

episodes.title: We Few, We Lucky Few, We Band of Gallaghers!
episodes.description: Frank milks his injury for all its worth as Debbie, now the self-elected leader of the Gallagher family, cooks up a scam of her own. Lip and Tami get a surprise. Carl returns home from military school and Liam faces an identity crisis.

episodes.title: Sleep Well My Prince For Tomorrow You Shall Be King
episodes.description: Feeling the pressure from Debbie, Frank sets out to make money to keep his place in the house, but Mikey has bigger plans for him. Lip is overwhelmed by the demands of a newborn, and Carl learns more about his mysterious new coworker at Captain Bob’s. Ian and Mickey struggle to keep the romance alive in prison.

episodes.title: Which America?
episodes.description: Liam gets to know his newfound family members as Frank revels in his new position in the Gallagher house. Lip looks for support as the pressures of fatherhood take their toll. Ian and Mickey make a decision about their future, and Carl tries to woo Anne despite Lori’s efforts to get in his way.

episodes.title: A Little Gallagher Goes a Long Way
episodes.description: Frank and Mikey set off on a day of adventure around the city in pursuit of Mikey’s dreams. Debbie discovers a new way to make money in the midst of a strike as Lip leans on his new friend for parenting advice. Carl gets more than he bargained for when he offers to help Anne. Liam grows suspicious of his seemingly perfect mentor.

episodes.title: Sparky
episodes.description: Frank hatches the idea for a new scheme when an unexpected visitor shows up at the Gallagher house. With Tami back in the house, Lip struggles to give up control of Fred. Debbie’s fight for child support escalates and Carl tries to juggle multiple romantic prospects. Ian returns home and is immediately thrown in with a corrupt parole officer.

episodes.title: Adios Gringos
episodes.description: Frank and Liam get wined and dined by potential baby buyers. Carl comes up with a strategy to protect Anne’s family business, and Ian gets on Paula’s bad side. Backed into a corner, Debbie fights to protect Franny from Pepa. A figure from Kev’s past makes him reconsider his childhood.

episodes.title: Citizen Carl
episodes.description: Carl embraces his civic duty while Debbie searches for her next payday. Frank meets the woman of his dreams, and Ian and Mickey get roped into a dangerous scam for Paula. When tragedy strikes at the Alibi, Kev and V go undercover to find new customers.

episodes.title: Debbie Might Be a Prostitute
episodes.description: Debbie weighs the pros and cons of a new career path. Frank uncovers the truth about Faye’s living situation. A miscommunication between Ian and Mickey has disastrous consequences and Lip and Tami disagree over who should be taking care of Fred.

episodes.title: O Captain, My Captain
episodes.description: Frank goes back in time to uncover his connection to Faye, as Debbie’s day with Claudia’s daughter goes awry. Carl takes extreme measures to toughen up his new group of cadets. Ian struggles to connect with Mickey after their blowup.

episodes.title: Now Leaving Illinois
episodes.description: An incident in the Tamietti family presents Lip and Tami with a new opportunity. Faye’s betrayal lands Frank in front of a judge. Mickey’s antics drive Ian to online dating. Carl makes an unexpected discovery at his new job.

episodes.title: Location, Location, Location
episodes.description: Frank finds a cushy place to make his new home. Lip gets cold feet when Tami moves forward with a plan for their future. Ian sees a new side of Mickey, and Debbie’s love triangle reaches a breaking point.

episodes.title: "Gallavich!"
episodes.description: Liam out-Gallaghers Frank, Lip works to convince Tami to stay in Chicago with their baby, Debbie turns over a new romantic leaf and Kev’s new business takes off, but V wonders where the money is going.

episodes.title: Episode 14
episodes.description: Episode 14 of Shameless

episodes.title: This is Chicago!
episodes.description: The Gallaghers adjust to life during the pandemic. Frank fears gentrification of South Side. Bar closures force Kev and V to get creative. Lip and Tami work to make their new house a home as Carl finishes his time at the police academy.

episodes.title: Go Home, Gentrifier!
episodes.description: Frank helps Kev and V's pot business. Debbie prepares a princess party for Franny while Mickey gets a real job. Lip runs into trouble with his new neighbors. Carl's first day on the force is not what he thought it would be.

episodes.title: Frances Francis Franny Frank
episodes.description: Debbie loses track of Franny, while Frank and Franny have a day of weed runs and adventure. Ian and Mickey question who is the "man" in their relationship. Carl gets a new training officer. Lip and Tami help Brad and Cami with their baby.

episodes.title: NIMBY
episodes.description: The Milkoviches move in next door and wreak havoc, leading Frank, Kev and Liam to scheme to get rid of them. Mickey embarks on a security gig for Kev and V and drags Ian along. Gemma and Franny compete in the Little Miss South Side beauty pageant.

episodes.title: Slaughter
episodes.description: Ian and Mickey get creative when the safety of their security gig comes into question. Dynamic duo Frank and Kev make a last-ditch effort to take down the Milkovich’s. V canvasses to get black people to the polls but realizes there’s barely any black people left on the Southside.

episodes.title: Do Not Go Gentle Into That Good... Eh, Screw It
episodes.description: A surprising twist of fate has left the Milkovich’s vulnerable, forcing Ian and Mickey to step in to help. Frank’s day takes some unexpected turns and Liam deals with inner turmoil after doing a bad thing. Debbie confronts Sandy on their relationship, while Carl enjoys the spoils of his day off.

episodes.title: Two at a Biker Bar, One in the Lake
episodes.description: The Gallaghers disagree on the fate of their childhood home so a stranded Frank tries to get back to weigh in on the matter. Realizing that they have none, Ian and Mickey embark on a journey to find gay friends. Carl is upset after his night with Tish, and Debbie and Sandy have another visitor from Sandy’s past.

episodes.title: Cancelled
episodes.description: Frank and Liam compete in a renaming contest of the Dennis Hastert Middle School. Debbie has a day of zero responsibilities, while Ian and Mickey take on all the responsibility for Terry. Veronica is depressed about her mom moving so Kevin tries to cheer her up, all while planning a special surprise.

episodes.title: Survivors
episodes.description: Frank wants to pull one last heist with the old gang. Debbie struggles with the idea of change and blames Lip, while Lip and Brad find out the new owners of BornFree are in the mob. Mickey and Ian learn a surprising truth about Terry’s past, and Liam tries to find a new place to live.

episodes.title: DNR
episodes.description: Lip has a million projects going on, and Frank is one of them. Liam is forced to watch Frank, so the two of them embark on a journey to take down Liam’s classmate in an effort to get Liam into STEM school. Carl’s disillusionment with the police force comes to a head.

episodes.title: The Fickle Lady Is Calling It Quits
episodes.description: Kev and V announce their big news. Lip has some promising leads on selling the house, forcing Debbie to reevaluate her future and her history of regrettable love interests. Ian and Mickey try to adjust to a vastly different life on the West Side. Carl’s commitment to the force is challenged when he’s reassigned to an unglamorous police unit. Liam reminds Frank of everything that makes Frank, Frank.

episodes.title: Father Frank, Full of Grace
episodes.description: Ian and Mickey shop for furniture for their new place and Kev and V look for a buyer for the Alibi. While Lip settles for a new job, Carl finally finds his calling in a new role on the police force. Debbie plunges into a treacherous world when she meets someone new. Frank comes to terms with his own mortality.

episodes.title: Episode 1
episodes.description: 1996. In Philadelphia, world chess champion Garry Kasparov competes against Deep Blue, IBM's high-performance computer.

episodes.title: Episode 2
episodes.description: World chess champion Garry Kasparov only hesitated for a long time before agreeing to play against a supercomputer.

episodes.title: Episode 3
episodes.description: Garry buys a dozen chess computers to study their playing style and that of Deep Blue.

episodes.title: Episode 4
episodes.description: The chairs in front of the chessboard remain empty, there is no information. Will the rematch be canceled?

episodes.title: Episode 5
episodes.description: Garry plays unusual moves that push his "opponent" to his technical limits.

episodes.title: Episode 6
episodes.description: Behind the scenes, pressure on Helen from the company's top management is growing...

episodes.title: Know Thyself
episodes.description: A rebel jumps the wall as a new girl enters campus. Old friends huddle with their gang in hopes of winning the secret shed and with it, the right to rule the Vandana Valley campus.

episodes.title: Ready to Fight
episodes.description: A new drama teacher holds auditions for the annual play as love brews on campus. An important basketball game could seal the fate of two hearts.

episodes.title: Love Lies
episodes.description: A campus divides and loyalties are tested when a scandal erupts. Temperatures soar further when boys visit for the hotly anticipated Socials dance.

episodes.title: Phir bhi udd gaye
episodes.description: Midterms, baby! Secrets are spilled and characters are tested when the girls head into nature for their class camping trip. A mysterious stranger cooks up a feast.

episodes.title: Masoom nahin hoon mein
episodes.description: Tension mounts as the whole campus prepares for the 75th Annual Day event. Hearts break over opportunities missed, and new resolutions are formed.

episodes.title: The Perfect Woman
episodes.description: Everyone puts their best foot forward as the school’s Diamond jubilee celebrations unfold. The illusion of perfection is challenged as truths are discovered and a long lost friend returns.

episodes.title: Together We Win
episodes.description: The term comes to an end as our girls are tested in more ways than one. A protest erupts as our girls struggle to define which truths are worth fighting for.

episodes.title: Prequel
episodes.description: Sarah and her son, Bibin, live an isolated life. As loud cries of infants haunt Sarah, she scribbles names on her walls. What secret is she keeping?

episodes.title: Sequel
episodes.description: Twelve years later, CI Aji Kurian, investigating the mysterious death of actor Ancy, finds himself drawn to the name Bibin. Sanjeev Krishna is devastated by his wife's death.

episodes.title: Legacy
episodes.description: Merlin's revelations lead Aji Kurian to Sarah's letters. After unravelling Sarah's most twisted secret, Aji finds himself pulled into a dark vortex of truth.

episodes.title: First Half
episodes.description: The unravelling of Bibin's cryptic letters begins. Clues lead Aji and his team to Bangalore towards another death. The mystery tightens its grip.

episodes.title: Interval
episodes.description: Bibin's puppeteering of human lives takes him to a prominent politician. As Aji digs deeper, he meets with fresh challenges and dreadful questions.

episodes.title: Second Half
episodes.description: A tapestry of truths, theories and mysteries woven together by Aji reveals the scary extent of Bibin's killing spree. However, Aji faces a threat more perilous than Bibin. What is it?

episodes.title: Anti-Climax
episodes.description: The endgame. The ultimate gamble. Aji and his team are locked in a deadly game where the stakes are high. In this life-or-death showdown, whose truth will prevail?

episodes.title: Free for All
episodes.description: Benício teams up with Suellen for their first case together. Meanwhile, Rossi greenlights unorthodox methods to solve crimes in his police station.

episodes.title: Traces of the Night
episodes.description: A new agent joins the team, and Benício explains the dynamics of organized crime. Soulless reunites with his former colleagues.

episodes.title: Animal Man
episodes.description: After discovering two new DNA samples, Suellen and Benício follow Roleta. But they're not the only ones tracking the suspect down.

episodes.title: Convoy
episodes.description: While Suellen recovers, Benício leads the investigation and hears word of a major upcoming heist. This requires Soulless to change tack.

episodes.title: Everything for the Family
episodes.description: Benício and Suellen collect additional DNA samples from other suspects. Yuri and Rossi discuss the Ghost Gang, and Moreira is reassigned.

episodes.title: At Home
episodes.description: Yuri relocates to Brasilia. Suellen and Benício uncover Soulless' real name and his past. A maneuver by the Ghost Gang turns deadly.

episodes.title: Hacienda
episodes.description: Isaac and Soulless argue. Benício and Suellen deal with pressing family matters. A traitor causes trouble for Rossi and his department.

episodes.title: The End and the Beginning
episodes.description: While Guilherme succumbs to pressure and Maria Clara gets revenge, Benício and Soulless have a dramatic showdown.

episodes.title: Game On
episodes.description: Plans for an audacious bank robbery pit Suellen's team and the Ghost Gang against each other in a lethal battle of wills — and high explosives.

episodes.title: The Hunter and the Hunted
episodes.description: A tragedy on the team leaves Suellen craving payback. Soulless changes his plans to keep a low profile in prison after his loved ones are put at risk.

episodes.title: Shangri-La
episodes.description: As the Ghost Gang hits a jewelry auction, time is running out for Suellen and Benício to get results. A showdown in a brothel ends in bloodshed.

episodes.title: Hostages
episodes.description: As the criminal group prepares an ambitious double bank hit, Suellen and Benício organize a counterattack at the heart of the Ghost Gang's operation.

episodes.title: Family Matters
episodes.description: Suellen and Benício investigate what clues Gabriel's tattoos might hold — but Suellen soon becomes a target for Isaac and his men.

episodes.title: Unlikely Duos
episodes.description: Suellen has to face family issues in the wake of a traumatic event. In Paraguay, Isaac shows the Ambassador no mercy.

episodes.title: Flash of Stash
episodes.description: After capturing a member of the Ghost Gang during a shoot-out, Suellen uses all possible tricks to make sure she extracts some useful information.

episodes.title: King of the Border
episodes.description: The Feds inflict serious losses on the Ghost Gang, while matters come to a head for Benício, Suellen and Soulless in the port of Santos.

episodes.title: The Legend of Lady Rose
episodes.description: When her fiancé is implicated as the prime suspect in a murder, Charulata 'Charlie' Chopra rushes to his family home in Solang Valley to uncover the mysteries around this death and the secrets of this sleepy hill town.

episodes.title: Sansani
episodes.description: After the explosive arrival of Nikki leaves the entire family reeling, Charlie begins to dig into their secrets, aided by a reluctant partnership with Sitaram.

episodes.title: Keh Do Ki Ye Jhooth Hai
episodes.description: When Solang Valley is rocked by a second death in a matter of weeks, Charlie’s investigation kicks into an overdrive, as she reopens questions that others thought were already answered.

episodes.title: Organic Honey
episodes.description: After a personal betrayal, Charlie becomes obsessed with unearthing the truth no matter the cost, but her reckless pursuit gives way to more enemies than answers.

episodes.title: Main Phuddu Aan
episodes.description: Narrowly escaping a close call with death, Charlie reunites with Sitaram. Together they race against time to find the murderer, because now they’re next on the list.

episodes.title: Look Within
episodes.description: More lives are lost, secrets unearthed, and betrayals come to light in the final chapter of Charlie’s investigation.

episodes.title: Wolferton Splash
episodes.description: A young Princess Elizabeth marries Prince Philip. As King George VI’s health worsens, Winston Churchill is elected prime minister for the second time.

episodes.title: Hyde Park Corner
episodes.description: With King George too ill to travel, Elizabeth and Philip embark on a four-continent Commonwealth tour. Party leaders attempt to undermine Churchill.

episodes.title: Windsor
episodes.description: With Elizabeth in a new role, Philip tries to assert some power. Churchill wants to delay the coronation. King George’s disgraced brother arrives.

episodes.title: Act of God
episodes.description: When dense smog cripples London for days and creates a serious health hazard, Churchill’s inaction leaves him vulnerable to his political enemies.

episodes.title: Smoke and Mirrors
episodes.description: Elizabeth rejects protocol by appointing Philip to coordinate her coronation, but his ideas create conflict. The Duke of Windsor returns to London.

episodes.title: Gelignite
episodes.description: Margaret and Peter come to Elizabeth with a request. With a royal scandal about to break in the newspapers, the Queen Mother intervenes.

episodes.title: Scientia Potentia Est
episodes.description: As the Soviets test the H-bomb, both Churchill and Eden have major health crises. Angry about her inadequate education, Elizabeth hires a tutor.

episodes.title: Pride & Joy
episodes.description: Elizabeth and Philip go on an exhausting world journey. Margaret takes over some of her sister’s official duties and tries to liven things up.

episodes.title: Misadventure
episodes.description: As Philip leaves for a long tour, Elizabeth makes an upsetting discovery. Prime Minister Eden wants to strike back after Egypt seizes the Suez Canal.

episodes.title: A Company of Men
episodes.description: Elizabeth feels disconnected from Philip. Eden copes with international pressure and ill health. An interview stirs up harrowing memories for Philip.

episodes.title: Lisbon
episodes.description: Palace insiders try to prevent a scandal that could reflect poorly on Philip. Eden faces censure from his cabinet and the press.

episodes.title: Beryl
episodes.description: When Elizabeth and Philip throw a grand party for their 10th anniversary, both Margaret and the new Prime Minister experience romantic tribulations.

episodes.title: Marionettes
episodes.description: After Elizabeth makes a tone-deaf speech at a Jaguar factory, she and the monarchy come under public attack from an outspoken lord.

episodes.title: Vergangenheit
episodes.description: A secret World War II document opens Elizabeth's eyes to grim realities about a family member. The Duke of Windsor campaigns to re-enter public life.

episodes.title: Episode 1
episodes.description: Glamorous Laura Sanderson's beloved son, Daniel, confides that he's met someone special. Wanting to impress, Laura meets the beguiling Cherry but soon catches her telling lies and starts to investigate. Cherry hides her humble beginnings as she works and plays amongst London's elite. She does everything to win over her new boyfriend's mother, Laura, but the more she tries the worse it gets.

episodes.title: Episode 2
episodes.description: Cherry joins the Sandersons' family holiday, intimidated by Daniel's bond with Laura. As Cherry seeks alone time with Daniel, Laura grows suspicious of her secrets. The tension peaks until a yacht incident unexpectedly brings the women together. Just as they form a genuine connection, Laura witnesses something she was never meant to see and threatens Cherry, who in turn gives her an ultimatum.

episodes.title: Episode 3
episodes.description: Laura digs deeper into Cherry's past as they continue to tussle for Daniel's affection. When Daniel confronts his mother over her behaviour, they have a vicious argument and Daniel spends his birthday with Cherry. With no support at home, Laura turns to her former lover for comfort before a phone call changes her and Cherry's lives forever.

episodes.title: Episode 4
episodes.description: Laura finds proof that her instincts were right about Cherry, and she whisks her family to Spain, spinning a web of lies to explain Cherry's sudden disappearance. Back in London, Cherry's life starts to unravel and she’s forced to move in with her mother. Upset the Sanderson's are callously ignoring her, it's not long until Cherry's plotting to get her life back.

episodes.title: Episode 5
episodes.description: An explosive revelation shatters Laura and Daniel's relationship, as Cherry must decide if reclaiming him is worth re-entering Laura's toxic orbit. But she's done being pushed around and she and Daniel are more in love than ever. Laura's desperation to win back her son and her obsession with Cherry spiral out of control, as her life unravels, their mutual hatred reaches new heights.

episodes.title: Episode 6
episodes.description: Cherry and Daniel seem blissfully in love, but cracks are starting to show. As Cherry fights to hold on to her new life, Laura discovers their relationship is progressing quickly. A tense visit to Cherry's family brings the evidence Laura thinks she needs to take Cherry down. It looks like Laura's won until the tables turn and a bitter showdown erupts, with Daniel caught in the crossfire.

episodes.title: Missing
episodes.description: Homicide detective Om Singh is tasked with the case of media mogul Amar Roy's missing daughter. But he soon finds out that there is something more sinister at play.

episodes.title: Doubt
episodes.description: An unexpected lead cracks open a new dimension in the case. Om finds himself diving further into the mystery in order to solve it.

episodes.title: Loser
episodes.description: Om is caught in a web of lies and deception. As secrets buried underground threaten to resurface.

episodes.title: Silence
episodes.description: As the insidious plan enters its final phase, Om must choose whether to succumb to it or fight.

episodes.title: The Invitation
episodes.description: After news of his death, Dr Viswak Sen's staff reaches out to his long-lost family members, inviting them to his mysterious private island.

episodes.title: Island Recci
episodes.description: Vicky, Viswak's forgotten son, is on a mission to learn about a father he never knew. Will Grandmother Meena shed light on that?

episodes.title: Family Matters
episodes.description: Jhansi's life gets upended. While Nikhila goes missing, Arun is startled to learn shocking details about his son Akash. Will that rage consume him?

episodes.title: Grandma Tales
episodes.description: The revelation about Meena's life with Viswak Sen causes uproar among the family members. She is now face to face with her biggest fear.

episodes.title: Lab Rats
episodes.description: The family members turn against each other with a vengeance. Trapped underground, Nikhila makes a startling discovery about the island.

episodes.title: No One is Safe Here
episodes.description: As Vicky searches for the missing Jhansi, he encounters a strange forest creature. Who will triumph?

episodes.title: Science Matters
episodes.description: The family reunites for dinner, and some startling revelations change their perceptions of each other. Now it's a survival of the fittest.

episodes.title: Mind Bending
episodes.description: The pursuit of science comes at a price. With lives at stake, who will finally triumph? What will happen to the legacy of Dr Viswak Sen?

episodes.title: The Reservoir
episodes.description: Along with a bitter legal fight over her child's custody, Rosa Peral receives unsettling news when her boyfriend's remains are found in a burnt-out car.

episodes.title: Two Rosas
episodes.description: As the investigation moves forward, Rosa insists on the culpability of her former husband, Javi. Glimpses of her past start taking a disturbing shape.

episodes.title: The Fall
episodes.description: Rosa downplays her bond with Albert to the police, but a violent incident from the past hints a complex and obscure connection between them.

episodes.title: Christmas
episodes.description: Rosa and Javi's breakup turns out more layered than expected as Pedro's role emerges in the reconstruction: the love triangle is now a square.

episodes.title: Love
episodes.description: The evidence on Pedro and Rosa puts together an unhealthy relationship. As the pieces get connected, the investigators seem to have a strong lead.

episodes.title: The Impossible
episodes.description: The law strikes and Rosa captures the press' attention, while she still has one last card to play. A past incident between Pedro and Javi comes to light.

episodes.title: Face to Face
episodes.description: The trial begins and the pressure builds up as new evidence and key testimonies are scrutinized before the district attorney. Javi agrees to speak on TV.

episodes.title: May 1st 2017
episodes.description: The police reconstructs the last hours of Pedro, and how they impacted the lives of Rosa and Albert. Everything is ready for the jury to issue a verdict.

episodes.title: Episode 11
episodes.description: Episode 11 of Burning Body

episodes.title: Episode 1
episodes.description: When an elite assassin carries out a kill, it catches the attention of an intelligence officer, who starts to hunt him down.

episodes.title: Episode 2
episodes.description: With his client backing out of payment, the Jackal's reputation is on the line, and he starts to plot his revenge.

episodes.title: Episode 3
episodes.description: Armed with the knowledge of his wayward client's identity, the Jackal tracks him down in Munich, determined to settle the score.

episodes.title: Episode 4
episodes.description: His vengeance fulfilled, the Jackal flees Munich and tries to quell Nuria's suspicions. Bianca follows a new lead in her hunt.

episodes.title: Episode 5
episodes.description: The Jackal visits Norman with a special commission... but with Bianca also tracking Norman down, she is starting to close in on him.

episodes.title: Episode 6
episodes.description: Following his shootout with Bianca, the Jackal must escape his captors and regroup ahead of his next hit, as Bianca follows his trail.

episodes.title: Episode 7
episodes.description: The Jackal and Bianca head to Tallinn before UDC's announcement. The Jackal must use all his wiles as he prepares to take his shot.

episodes.title: Episode 8
episodes.description: Bianca gains insight into a secret file. She learns the true identity of the Jackal and how he became a contract killer.

episodes.title: Episode 9
episodes.description: With the release of River imminent, UDC believes himself safe. As time runs out, the Jackal must use all his skills to reach his target.

episodes.title: Episode 10
episodes.description: A wanted man, the Jackal is on the run, desperate to get back to Nuria, but Bianca is given one last shot to bring him to justice.

episodes.title: Episode 1
episodes.description: The Bennets have five daughters, all without dowries, so they have limited chances of marrying. Then the rich Charles Bingley arrives in the district and takes a keen interest in Jane Bennet. At Bingley's house, Jane's sharp-tongued sister Elizabeth sees more of his friend, Fitzwilliam Darcy - but she finds him too arrogant for her.

episodes.title: Episode 2
episodes.description: A visit from the Bennets' cousin, Mr Collins, throws the family into disarray, while Elizabeth's acquaintance with Wickham solidifies her distrust and dislike of Darcy.

episodes.title: Episode 3
episodes.description: Bingley and his household return to London suddenly, leaving Jane to suppose he does not care about her after all. Lizzie discovers who was behind the separation and receives another surprising offer.

episodes.title: Episode 4
episodes.description: Darcy defends himself against Elizabeth's accusations, and later they meet at his house, Pemberley. While there, Elizabeth makes an astonishing discovery about Darcy which changes her feelings about him.

episodes.title: Episode 5
episodes.description: Elizabeth meets Darcy's younger sister, Georgiana. Then news comes that Lydia has eloped with Wickham, and the Bennets fear she is lost. Darcy decides to help Lydia - but without telling the Bennet family or Elizabeth.

episodes.title: Episode 6
episodes.description: Mrs Bennet is delighted to have one of her daughters married at last. Elizabeth sees Wickham in his true colours when she meets him again after his elopement. There is great excitement in the neighbourhood when Bingley returns to Netherfield, bringing Darcy with him.
