episodes.title: Induction
episodes.description: Despite a rocky start at Yullim Law Firm, Kang Hyo-min joins Yoon Seok-hoon's team — and impresses him when she finds a discrepancy in their first case.

episodes.title: Hot Water Is the Test for Tea and Love
episodes.description: Seok-hoon and Hyo-min take on a case involving a man who broke into a fertility clinic — earning trust in a tangled battle of love, health and injustice.

episodes.title: Butterfly Chrysalis
episodes.description: A complex no-contact car accident involving a child sends Seok-hoon and Hyo-min digging for clues. Seok-hoon receives a bold offer from Yullim's founder.

episodes.title: Lex Talionis
episodes.description: While defending a CEO accused of child abuse, Hyo-min and Seok-hoon clash over their morals. Soon, Seok-hoon's sudden disappearance worries her.

episodes.title: Salieri's Monologue
episodes.description: Hyo-min takes on her first solo case over a painting's copyright, leaning on Seok-hoon for mentorship — until a mid-trial revelation shakes her stride.

episodes.title: Love Is an Impairment
episodes.description: Seok-hoon and Hyo-min handle a tricky consent case for a client suing her ex. Meanwhile, Kwon Na-yeon's sudden appointment creates waves at Yullim.

episodes.title: Love in All Its Colors
episodes.description: After a man is arrested for aiding his wife's assisted suicide, Seok-hoon takes on the case. Meanwhile, Yullim's new performance system sparks fury.

episodes.title: Wonder Woman
episodes.description: At Yullim, Ko Tae-seop's plot to oust Seok-hoon escalates. When a famous news anchor is charged with assaulting her husband, Hyo-min digs for the truth.

episodes.title: The Right to Life
episodes.description: Seok-hoon and Hyo-min defend a doctor who faces possible murder charges for failing to save a man she abhors. Meanwhile, Na-yeon looks into a shady deal.

episodes.title: Bystander
episodes.description: After a murder suspect blames her for the crime, Hyo-min hunts for their connection. Na-yeon and Seok-hoon pursue the truth behind Yullim's CEO's ploy.

episodes.title: The Two-Legged Beast
episodes.description: When a personal privacy case spirals, Seok Hun's fury grows as the client crosses the line. Meanwhile, Na Yeon uncovers proof to back her suspicions.

episodes.title: Beyond Love's Vow
episodes.description: A divorce case turns complicated when the court contemplates their unusual relationship. Seok Hun and Na Yeon make their final move for justice.

episodes.title: Episode 6
episodes.description: Episode 6 of Beyond the Bar

episodes.title: A Celestial Event
episodes.description: When a woman fatally falls from El Capitan, special agent Kyle Turner suspects it wasn't an accident — and that the truth may lie deep within Yosemite.

episodes.title: Jane Doe
episodes.description: The mystery around Jane Doe deepens as Turner and Vasquez investigate a strange symbol and visit a remote encampment in the woods.

episodes.title: El-o'-win
episodes.description: Jane Doe's identity raises new questions about the life she left behind — and connects to an old case that has haunted Turner for years.

episodes.title: Gold Rush
episodes.description: A grim discovery in the mines makes Turner question the squatters' role in the case. Vasquez fights to protect her son when his father reappears.

episodes.title: Terces
episodes.description: Turner takes the investigation to new extremes — with serious repercussions. Jill gets caught up in Vasquez's conflict with her ex.

episodes.title: All Trails Lead Here
episodes.description: As the investigation comes to a close, Turner discovers the truth about Lucy's death — and the long-buried secrets that set it in motion.

episodes.title: Bhutte Bane Popcorn
episodes.description: It’s first day for Class 11 commerce students at KLPD. BBFs Anirban and Raman have their very first fight as Anirban decides to change his section to be with her all-time crush, topper Stuti. Meanwhile, Stuti is sad as principal announces that this year’s headgirl and headboy will be only from science section.

episodes.title: Stuti Ko Kaise Pataun?
episodes.description: Dreams come true for Anirban as Stuti chooses to sit next to him. In a hilarious act, Raman interviews candidates to replace Anirban from the position of his best friend. On the other hand, Stuti is shocked when she gets to know that her best friend Kudrat has been chosen as the perfect head girl.

episodes.title: Kisne Mara Atom Bomb?
episodes.description: Raman comes up with a 3-rule strategy to help Anirban impress Stuti, but Dimple doesn’t agree. Stuti is facing a difficult choice, and finally she. makes a radical decision to save her Head Girl dream.

episodes.title: POV: CCTV
episodes.description: Stuti’s decision to switch to Science has left Anirban in great turmoil. Stuti’s crazy plan ‘to have it all’ has Kudrat worried. Stuti pays the price of her bad choices but Anirban manages to save the day for her, and finally the ice is broken.

episodes.title: Masala Mass Bunk
episodes.description: An act of discrimination by Principal Shukla against commerce students pisses Dimple off and she decides to put him in his place, by planning a mass bunk. Stuti is against it, but Dimple lies to her and puts her in a difficult position.

episodes.title: Stuti Ko Kaise Manau?
episodes.description: After the whole bunking mess, Stuti is now ignoring Anirban. Anirban who really want to make things better, try all the things to make her feel better. While Mukund is now after Raman. He has decided to make his life hell.

episodes.title: Mistri Bane Kalakar
episodes.description: Anirban apologizes to Stuti but she is adamant. Mukund gets in a big fight Raman and Dimple. A crazy prank takes place in class, and Raman is wrongly pulled up.

episodes.title: 200 Ka Ek
episodes.description: Stuti forgives Anirban. Raman wants revenge from Mukund. Dimple makes a nasty plan, but at the time of execution, Raman screws up and their BIG plan to avenge their ‘image’ bites them back and how!

episodes.title: Surprise Test Pro Max
episodes.description: The principal drops the surprise test bomb on commerce students. Dimple ends up smuggling Topper Stuti’s notes to earn a quick buck! Mukund uses the ace up his sleeve to deal with the test. Anirban and Stuti are in for a surprise that may put a dent in their newly blossoming friendship.

episodes.title: Stuti Kahan Hai Yaar?
episodes.description: Stuti gives Anirban a serious dressing down, following which, he has a spat with Raman and Dimple. Determined to show students their place, Principal Shukla springs up a Surprise Test 2.0. A bizarre fallout of the test leaves Anirban, Stuti, Raman, Dimple and Mukund accidentally locked inside the store room with no network. The only way for them to get out is by working together as a team.

episodes.title: Who's the hottie?
episodes.description: The first parent-principal meeting doesn’t go well for Mukund. Raman decides to cheer up Mukund, realizing that the big bad bully is actually just a lonely kid. Stuti is missing from the school the next day after the meeting. Commode Raja’s news of her accident shatters Anirban.

episodes.title: Gaurav-Bhagao Andolan
episodes.description: As Cancel Commode Raja’s scoop on Stuti turns out to be fake, Cancel Commode Raja trends in school. Anirban finally musters courage and decides it’s time to tell Stuti how he feels. But hilarity ensues when his hopes are dashed by Mr Perfect – the new brawn with brains boy in school. While Dimple has finally cracked the formula for her start-up.

episodes.title: That's What Friends Do
episodes.description: Anirban and his buddies finally expose the new dazzling and discover what the handsome truth hidden behind his face is.

episodes.title: Dosti Ka Interval
episodes.description: Anirban is furious with Stuti, but Stuti makes every attempt to reestablish his friendship with Anirban, while mobile phones are still banned in school, which has a significant impact on Dimple's life. Finally, Stuti hands over her notes to Anirban, and the two share a moment together.

episodes.title: Analysis-e-Anirban
episodes.description: In this episode, unexpected emotions begin to surface within Stuti as she realizes there is a burgeoning affection for Anirban deep within her heart. Simultaneously, Dimple finds herself contemplating whether she has stumbled upon the love of her life

episodes.title: School Bani Pathshala
episodes.description: The school was thrown into chaos when the principal introduced a new rule segregating boys and girls, creating a deep division among the students. Dimple's heart shattered as she was affected by the consequences of this rule, feeling the pain of separation and loss.

episodes.title: Gender-Bender!
episodes.description: As a bizarre reaction to the canoodling couple, Principal tops the phone ban rule - Girls and boys can’t talk to each other! The school suddenly gives off a black and white era vibe. The only lucky one is Dimple, who can arrange a meet-cute with her crush with no fear of being caught – because her crush is a girl.

episodes.title: Head Girl Kaun Hai?
episodes.description: Dimple confesses her feelings to Harshita. Anirban, Raman and Mukund face the threat of suspension. The whole school turns up in support of them, but in a new avatar. Gender Bender it is! Meanwhile, Principal Shukla’s ad hoc actions are questioned by a well-meaning school board member.

episodes.title: Abey Yeh Kya Ho Gaya?
episodes.description: Anirban wants Stuti to stay back at any cost. But how? With both anger and hormones raging, he executes his amateur plan to get the principal sacked, and have Stuti become the head-girl. Surprisingly, he even succeeds well almost. Just as he’s about to confess his feelings to Stuti, things take an unprecedented turn.

episodes.title: Stuti Roko Andolan
episodes.description: When Anirban musters up the courage to confess his feelings to Stuti, she reveals that she is leaving the school, shocking everyone. Anirban and his friends hatch a plan to convince her to stay. Will they succeed in keeping their friend at school?

episodes.title: Stuti Roko Andolan 2.0
episodes.description: Despite their best efforts, Anirban and his friends fail to convince Stuti. Unyielding, Anirban initiates Plan B. These persistent efforts make Stuti realize how important her friends are to her, and she decides she cannot leave them behind.

episodes.title: RamBan Ka Jhagda?
episodes.description: While everyone is happy for Stuti, Principal Cholla has different plans for her responsibilities. Additionally, Cholla's announcement about new house allotments has left her school friends extremely worried. What are they planning next?

episodes.title: The House Of School Friends
episodes.description: When Gaurav cleverly separates everyone into different houses, Dimples uncovers his ulterior motive. Determined to thwart his plans and reunite her friends, she devises 'The House of School Friends' operation.

episodes.title: Aswachata Abhiyan
episodes.description: School friends plan to get revenge on Principal Cholla by meddling in ACIS visit, forgetting how it might negatively impact Stuti's position as head girl. Despite Anirban's efforts to stop them, it's already too late.

episodes.title: Honest Anirban
episodes.description: Zorawar gets angry seeing litter everywhere and notes it in his diary. Anirban uses paint thrown on a blackboard to create a painting. ACIS inspector Zorawar is impressed by Anirban's art, which covers Raman's mistake.

episodes.title: And The Oscar Goes To
episodes.description: The drawing teacher admires Anirban’s art. The group persuades Raman to audition, and he agrees to participate. However, Raman gets cold feet and disappears, prompting the entire group to search for him.

episodes.title: Stuti Is Punished!
episodes.description: All friends, exhausted from searching for Raman, are surprised when he enters the auditorium in a new avatar. Raman auditions but isn't selected. Dimple despite all the stress manage to celebrate Mukund's birthday.

episodes.title: Golgappa Overflow Ho Gaya!
episodes.description: Gaurav has forced the gang to do his work. Mukund devises a revenge plan against him. As a result, Gaurav is punished, and the gang is now plotting to remove him from his position as head boy.

episodes.title: Head Boy Haye Haye!
episodes.description: The gang learns Gaurav is forging the Principal's signature and devises a plan. Caught on CCTV, Gaurav is demoted from Head Boy. Anirban decides to help Nilesh.

episodes.title: And The Head Boy Is…
episodes.description: Principal appoints Anirban as Head Boy, shocking the gang. Stuti reveals she convinced the principal. Mr. Mehta informs us about the quiz. Stuti, initially upset, changes her mind seeing Principal using the stress bag.

episodes.title: Dimple Ki Toh Lag Gayi
episodes.description: Stuti preps the auditorium for the quiz while Anirban, confused and panicked, is taken to the stress relief corner by her. Raman and others sing to welcome Mr. Zorawar, who starts the quiz with the audience.

episodes.title: Unit Test Ya Picnic?
episodes.description: Students of KLPD face unconventional punishments after a surprise inspection by Mukund's strict mother. With the school at risk, they must choose between a picnic or saving their 11th and 12th grades.

episodes.title: Padhai-Vadhai Sabh Dhokha Hai
episodes.description: Facing pressure from upcoming exams and a retest, students discuss their struggles and strategies. The results bring mixed emotions, and attention shifts to the cultural fest, a crucial factor in the school's evaluation.

episodes.title: Movie Kaun Kaun Dekhega?
episodes.description: To convince their strict principal for movie, students turn a surprise celebration into an appreciation event. However, the movie is a dull documentary, prompting students to sneak out, leading to unexpected twists in relationships.

episodes.title: Haww, Kiss???
episodes.description: After the video emerges, Raman, Mukund, and Dimple confront Anirban and Stuti, triggering chaos. Stuti grapples with the fallout while Anirban tries to repair their friendship amid school tensions and peer judgment.

episodes.title: Clash Of The Genders!
episodes.description: Stuti's rejection of Anirban sparks a dare-filled rivalry between boys and girls. Rising tensions lead to pranks and challenges that strain friendships and reveal underlying emotions.

episodes.title: Rehearsal Time!
episodes.description: In a chaotic library escape, Mukund injures himself, prompting the group to rally around him. This leads to heartwarming moments and a reconciliation between Stuti and Anirban.

episodes.title: Kya Phata Raman!
episodes.description: In the school auditorium, cultural performance rehearsals create tension when Raman is excluded. Ananda Ma'am pairs Kudrat with Gaurav, but Raman's return in high-heeled shoes surprises everyone. Tables turn when he injures his ankle.

episodes.title: Stuti, Yeh Tune Kya Kiya?
episodes.description: In the school auditorium, chaos ensues when Ananda Ma'am falls ill during cultural performance preparations. Anirban steps up to create a last-minute background, but backstage revelations of Chola's deceit spark a student rebellion.

episodes.title: New Girl In Class
episodes.description: Stuti and Anirban's almost-love story faces new hurdles, while Principal Bhola's ban on extracurricular activities stirs up tension. In the midst of canteen laughter, they cross paths with a new girl, Yashika.

episodes.title: Mission: Who Is Yashika?
episodes.description: A new student, Yashika, joins the school, quickly catching Anirban's attention as he begins to show genuine care for her. Stuti, noticing Anirban's growing interest in Yashika, starts to feel a pang of jealousy. As these emotions surface, tension brews between Stuti and Anirban, complicating their friendship.

episodes.title: KLPD Mein Junk Food Ban
episodes.description: Principal Cholla implements a strict ban on junk food in the school canteen, replacing it with healthier options in an effort to promote student well-being. However, not everyone is on board with the new rules. Raman and his group of friends, unhappy with the change, secretly smuggle in junk food, distributing it among the students.

episodes.title: Business Girl Dimple Rocks!
episodes.description: Chaos erupts in the school as several students begin vomiting, seemingly due to food poisoning. Concerned and determined to find the culprit, Dimple takes it upon herself to investigate the canteen's ingredients, suspecting foul play. Her suspicions quickly fall on Raju, and she sets out to trap him, believing he's responsible for the incident.

episodes.title: Kebab Mein Haddi?
episodes.description: Students in class were asked to do a marketing survey in pairs, Since Yashika is a new student, she was given the previlege to chose her partner first, she picked Anirban. Stuti was seen being jealous of this. Then Mukund chose Dimple, which left Stuti with no choice but Raman. They all head to Agarwal sweets for survey where Stuti and Anirban are seated next each other.

episodes.title: And The Best Jodi Is...?
episodes.description: Students had a presentation after the market survey wherein Yashika was seen having panic attacks. She was feeling uneasy, Anirban noticed it and tried to console her by holding her hands. She eventually started feeling better. Stuti was sitting with Raman, she noticed them holding hands which made her feel jealous.

episodes.title: Fight For Seat!
episodes.description: Cholla punishes the students and replaces the benches with mattresses. The students jump over it and have fun, Stuti sees it and tries to stop everyone, Anirban is dragged away by Yashita, Stuti goes and sits next to gaurav. Anirban gets jealous. Students eventually are fed up of the mattresses. The canteen guy offers students to sit on a chair in exchange of money.

episodes.title: Tables Have Turned
episodes.description: Gaurav enters, everyone is furious. Everyone warns him not to tell Cholla, he replies that he himself is frustrated with his dad. Anirban says that they cannot trust him, Stuti takes Gaurav's side. Anirban is now jealous. Gaurav helps in cutting the wire. The power has been cut not only in Cholla's cabin but the whole school. Everyone blames Gaurav, Stuti takes his side and speaks on his behalf.

episodes.title: Walk Of Shame
episodes.description: Everyone tries to find Dimple, that's when they come across scrabble competition, Stuti and Yashika decide to team up for it. Cholla punishes Raman and Mukund. Stuti gets on stage for preparation, Anirban wishes luck to her. Yashika gets panic attacks seeing the stage, Anirban tries to comfort her, Stuti sees it and is jealous.

episodes.title: May The Best Girl Win
episodes.description: Anirban finds the owl gifted to Stuti on floor. Raman and Mukund finally reach Dimple in the hospital. They all chill together. Stuti and Yashika win the 1st round. Gaurav and his partner win too. Now it is Stuti vs Yashika and Gaurav vs his partner. Gaurav makes it look like his partner is cheating, Principal bans all extra curricular activites.

episodes.title: No More Masti In KLPD!
episodes.description: Stuti tries to convince Cholla to remove the ban but he ignores her request. Anirban comes on stage and blames Gaurav for falsely accusing his partner, Stuti interferes and asks Anirban to stay out of their fight. Everyone leaves Anirban alone on stage, except Yashika, she thanks Anirban for being there for her. She is shown admiring Anirban. Everyone gathers and welcomes Dimple.

episodes.title: Matter Ab Serious Hai
episodes.description: Principal walks out of his office and observes furious students protecting by performing a street play, Cholla is still not convinced. Dimple warns Cholla if he doesnt lift the ban, Yashika would post the street play video online and everyone would blame Cholla. He then says that due to this, student's marks would be deducted. Stuti pleads him not to deduct marks.

episodes.title: Commode Raja's Face Revealed
episodes.description: Raman and Mukund's antics have finally exhausted the principal's patience, leading him to humiliate them by making them do a chicken dance in front of the entire school. Dimple, determined to expose the prankster Commode Raja.

episodes.title: School Friends Ka Plan Backfired
episodes.description: Thinking they've caught Commode Raja, the students ambush a figure in a hoodie only to find it's Principal Cholla, sick and annoyed. Just then, Commode Raja sends a taunting message, prompting the group to try a seance.

episodes.title: Mission Red Flag To Green Flag
episodes.description: Anirban tries to impress Stuti, frustrated by her misunderstandings, and sets out to prove he's a "green flag." However, his attempts, including praising Yashika as a "whole green forest," only make Stuti jealous and push her further away.

episodes.title: Sitare vs Bechare
episodes.description: Dimple reveals Principal Cholla's truth to the trustee, exposing how Cholla had restricted extracurricular activities due to their seniors' poor performance. Cholla, in turn, proposes a competition where extracurriculars will be allowed for the winning team. The students are divided into two teams: those who scored above 70 and those below.

episodes.title: My School Friends
episodes.description: After much turmoil, Stuti and Anirban finally reconcile, putting their differences aside and coming together as a team. Determined to set things right, they decide to approach Principal Cholla and convince him to lift the ban that has been troubling everyone. Just as their plan begins to take shape, an unexpected twist shakes things up.

episodes.title: Episode 20
episodes.description: Episode 20 of School Friends

episodes.title: Good Value Diet Soda
episodes.description: Molly leans on her best friend Nikki after receiving a distressing diagnosis.

episodes.title: Masturbation Is Important
episodes.description: Molly dodges her treatment plan and follows her own desires. Nikki struggles in her new role as Molly's caretaker.

episodes.title: Feelings Can Become Amplified
episodes.description: Molly tries to maintain a positive attitude despite disturbances from her new neighbor.

episodes.title: Topping Is a Sacred Skill
episodes.description: Molly and Nikki attend a sex party, and Molly's desires lead her to unexpected places.

episodes.title: My Pet
episodes.description: Molly's mother, Gail, comes for a visit.

episodes.title: Happy Holidays
episodes.description: Molly confronts her past, as Nikki struggles to find balance.

episodes.title: You’re Killing Me, Ernie
episodes.description: Molly has a visitor at the hospital.

episodes.title: It's Not That Serious
episodes.description: Molly reflects on her life.

episodes.title: Lesson 1: Never Fall in Love
episodes.description: Chaperone Elena Bianda works to earn the trust of Pedro Mencía's daughters — and his attractive godson. At a high-society ball, things go out of control.

episodes.title: Lesson 2: Do Not Tell Lies
episodes.description: Elena tries to support Cristina in the wake of her revelation. Sara shares her secret. A face from the chaperone's past makes an unwelcome appearance.

episodes.title: Lesson 3: The Past Is in the Past
episodes.description: Both with ulterior motives, Gabriel and Cristina flirt with each other and confuse Santiago. Elena must confront secrets from her rebellious past.

episodes.title: Lesson 4: Ward Off Temptation
episodes.description: After a night of indulgence, Cristina pleads with Elena to talk to Santiago, with unexpected results. Josefina and Esther struggle with their feelings.

episodes.title: Lesson 5: Stay True to Your Lady
episodes.description: Elena tries to discourage Santiago's feelings while dealing with a rival chaperone. A betrayal surfaces during a séance. Cristina hears from Eduardo.

episodes.title: Lesson 6: Your Desires Come Second
episodes.description: Complications almost expose Cristina's secret, and Elena resorts to asking Angustias for help. Santiago battles with doubts about Cristina.

episodes.title: Lesson 7: Maintain Proper Decorum
episodes.description: Elena is stunned when her own mother tries to interfere with the Mencías, while Eduardo's return makes things even more confusing for everyone.

episodes.title: Lesson 8: Make Your Lady Happy
episodes.description: After a shocking revelation, the sisters are furious with Elena. A professional opportunity for Santiago prompts Cristina to figure out her feelings.

episodes.title: A Little Detour
episodes.description: Runaway single mother Alba starts working on a flower farm, only to be named the prime suspect in an investigation when a murder occurs on the property.

episodes.title: Someone Knew
episodes.description: After an attack, the police probe further into Alba's past. Lucie discovers an incriminating weapon in the house. Béatrice pays Léo a visit.

episodes.title: Things Fall Apart
episodes.description: Béatrice tries to strike a deal with Alba as she and Valentin discover a disturbing hideout. An anonymous call tips police off about a suspect.

episodes.title: Relentless
episodes.description: Mathieu works out a new deal for the farm and hosts a party, which Alba attends in a frantic search for Léo under the watchful eye of a hidden stalker.

episodes.title: Talk to Me

episodes.title: The Break-Up Rule
episodes.description: Best friends Lizzie and Sam share a drink at their neighborhood dive bar. Sam is nervous: it's her third date with nice guy, Brad. And everyone knows about the the third date -- the sex date. Lizzie scolds her for not having had sex already, which is a violation of the rules passed down to them by their recently married friend, Sienna. Sam acts on Lizzie's advice and seduces Brad, only to have him dump her immediately after their encounter when his girlfriend texts him that she wants him back. Lizzie insists that Sam "get underneath another man" right away, and the two friends go prowling at an upscale club. Lizzie focuses on getting someone to buy them top-shelf drinks, while Sam makes the acquaintance of Jason, who turns out to be Lizzie's new co-worker. Lizzie breaks it up, saying that Jason is too clingy and moves on to her own quest -- the sexy, casually dressed guy sitting at the bar, reading a book. Lizzie's initial encounter with this man she dubs "Dirty Hot Guy" begins hot and flirty but ends in mutual insults. And when -- adding insult to injury -- her ex, Drew, comes in with another girl, Lizzie is determined not to let it get to her. She and Sam cruise a jiu-jitsu studio, but get little more than hot and sweaty. Afterwards, Lizzie encounters the Dirty Hot Guy in the dive bar and takes him home for sex. Sam learns that her current major crush, Richard, will be at the R Bar; she and Lizzie make a beeline for the place, hoping for a "chance" encounter.

episodes.title: The Last Woman Standing Rule
episodes.description: Sam starts stalking Richard and waits outside his apartment house so she can bump into him when he comes home. He's with his neighbor, Morgan, so Sam declines his offer to come inside. Lizzie scolds Sam for not accepting the invitation and outlasting Morgan, a violation of the "last woman standing" rule. Sam follows Richard on twitter and crashes a fantasy football party to be near him but Richard ends up leaving the party while Sam is in the bathroom. Meanwhile, Lizzie and Jason handle a sexual harassment case for Kyra, who was fired from a cupcake store when she refused sexual advances from her supervisor. Lizzie goes undercover, but can't get supervisor, Jessie, to come on to her, no matter how she flirts. Finally, she corners him in the back room and seduces him. She tells Kyra that she couldn't get the goods on her tormentor, only to learn that Kyra was harassed by Johnnie, the boss's son. Lizzie goes back to the cupcake store to get evidence against Johnnie, leaving Sam at the dive bar with Richard and Morgan. Sam out-drinks Morgan, who passes out; she takes Richard home with her, but he is too drunk to get it up and just falls asleep.

episodes.title: The Puma Rules
episodes.description: Richard cancels a date with Sam, who complains to Lizzie that she's tired of the game men and women play with one another. Lizzie suggests they find a place where the guys don't know the rules, and settles on a Mexican place on college night. The girls pick up Stevie and Len, business/finance majors, and go back to their place. Lizzie and Len have sex, but Stevie is so excited he comes before Sam can even get him undressed. In the morning, the girls discover that Len and Stevie are both just barely legal and living at home -- they graduated from the "University" prep school. Meanwhile, Jason is romancing Nicole, a marine botanist who picked him up with a candid line at the farmers' market. Thanks to Lizzie, he has some doubts about her sincerity, but Nicole's directness wins him over. He goes out with her and they end the night with an energetic sexual workout. In the morning, Nicole leaves, promising to call Jason. A few days later, he bumps into Lizzie and Sam at the farmers' market. They see Nicole using the same "candid" line on another guy, and Jason realizes that Lizzie was right -- fake sincerity is Nicole's game. Jason and the girls adjourn to a nearby joint to drown their sorrows.

episodes.description: Richard cancels a date with Sam, who complains to Lizzie that she's tired of the game men and women play with one another. Lizzie suggests they find a place where the guys don't know the rules, and settles on a Mexican place on college night. The girls pick up Stevie and Len, business/finance majors, and go back to their place. Lizzie and Len have sex, but Stevie is so excited he comes before Sam can even get him undressed. Meanwhile, Jason is romancing Nicole, a marine botanist who picked him up with a candid line at the farmers' market. Jason and the girls adjourn to a nearby joint to drown their sorrows.

episodes.title: The Bitch Rule
episodes.description: Lizzie and Sam are at the dive bar when the bitchy Mariposa sidles up beside them and intimidates Jason into buying her a drink. Afterwards, Lizzie and Sam overhear Mariposa on the phone and realize that Latin spitfire is just an assumed persona for Mildred, an ordinary girl who has learned how to channel her inner b**ch to get what she wants. The three women chat over coffee. Lizzie and Mariposa are both attracted to the same cute Waiter, and a challenge goes out – let the biggest b**ch win. Sam channels her inner b**ch with bike messenger Ryan and gets him to go home with her. They have wild, primal sex, but his interest fades in the morning when Sam inadvertently reverts to her nice girl self. Lizzie and Mariposa compete for the Waiter, but Lizzie can’t beat the master and Mariposa waltzes away with the prize. Later, a the dive bar, a Voluptuous Woman b**chily refuses to say where she bought her dress, so Lizzie cuts the label out of her garment. The dress is from a plus size shop - the Woman was embarrassed about shopping there. Lizzie feels guilty about her brazen behavior and apologizes. Sam goes home, and a deflated Lizzie stays at the dive bar. The Dirty Hot Guy sits down next to her, offers companionable silence, and buys her a drink.

episodes.title: The Magic Pussy Rule
episodes.description: Lizzie and Sam see a plain woman with a handsome younger man and wonder how she holds his attention. Someone suggests she has a "magic p**sy," something no one can define. Lizzie is determined to unravel the mystery. First, she and Sam attend a tantric yoga class, but are tossed out when they start laughing. The girls are talking things over when Cheyenne, Tyler's sub at the bar, volunteers that she once had a magic p**sy -- until she had a baby. Next, the girls try a special steam treatment for their nether regions at a Korean spa, but are horrified when they learn it's a fertility treatment. Two days later, they still don't have an answer to their question. Tyler, who is gay, suggests that maybe it's really a magic mouth, and tells them about the most popular girl in his year at the University of Illinois. The Dirty Hot Guy comes in and Lizzie ambles over to talk to him. He tells her he knows the secret to a magic p**sy -- it's confidence. Just then, his date arrives -- an older woman who exudes confidence and is not threatened to see him with Lizzie. Later, Lizzie tells Sam that she misses Drew, her ex, and wonders if he's happy with his pretty younger girlfriend.

episodes.title: The Fuck Buddy Rule
episodes.description: Sam and Danny have daytime sex, which alarms Lizzie -- Sam's falling for her f**k buddy, a violation of one of the top ten rules. Kaylie dates her new f**k buddy and doesn't find it a problem; Sam wonders if she can pull off the same trick. Her co-worker, Kate, thinks casual sex is folly and tells Sam so, but when her boyfriend dumps Kate, Sam sees the wisdom of remaining uninvolved. Despite her good intentions, Sam accepts Danny's impromptu invitation to the movies and afterwards, to grab a bite to eat. She invites him back to her place, but he declines. Lizzie tells her she had it coming for breaking the rules. Then Danny calls and invites Sam for drinks. He tells her that he has to keep his dating life and his sex life separate, and breaks up with her. Sam drowns her sorrows in a pint of ice cream. The sounds of Kaylie and Jordan having energetic role-playing sex as "Trinity" and "Neo" drives her from her apartment and into the dive bar. Lizzie tells her that horniness is the price she must pay for breaking the f**k buddy rule. Lizzie and Tyler get so hot thinking about Trinity and Neo that they rush out to a fetish joint, leaving Sam alone yet again.

episodes.title: The Cheating Rule
episodes.description: Kaylie is with Lizzie and Sam at the dive bar, where they see a guy who looks like Jordan pick up a busty Blonde. Kaylie is devastated. Lizzie and Sam tell her that all men cheat, and offer examples from their pasts. They urge her to even the score by making him jealous. Lizzie and Sam stalk Jordan, trying to catch him cheating. They follow him to the gym and to breakfast; that night, they watch as someone who looks like him enters his apartment building with the Blonde in tow. Sam uses a ruse to get them into Brad's apartment so they can spy from across the alley. Sam stays behind, has sex with Brad, and dumps him like he did her. Lizzie and Sam present their inconclusive evidence to Kaylie, and tell her it's time to make Jordan cry. Kaylie has Tyrone escort her to the dive bar. Jordan walks in, sees them together, and is heartbroken. When presented with the "evidence," he tells them that he moved that weekend and spent it unpacking -- he isn't the guy on the video. Kaylie and Jordan make up and leave together; Tyrone joins the busty Blonde; Jason tells Lizzie and Sam that their rules don't work, which is why they are alone. Sam goes home and listens to Kaylie and Jordan having sex on the other side of the wall.

episodes.title: The Bi-Guy Rule
episodes.description: Lizzie and Sam visit a gay bar with Tyler, and argue about Sam's penchant for unavailable men. Lizzie flirts with gay boy Mark and gets drunk; he takes her home and has sex with her. Lizzie tells Sam of the encounter and the two friends ponder how to tell if a guy is straight or gay. Sam is curious about Devon, a cute new co-worker, but picks up mixed clues to his orientation from his conversation, computer search history, and behavior. They host a launch party at a tattoo parlor for b**chy client, Fiona's, photo book. Sam invites Tyler to see if he can get a read on Devon, but even Tyler is stymied. Tyler is delighted with the b**chy Fiona, though, and surprises Lizzie and Sam by having sex with her in a back room. At the party's end, Sam flat-out asks Devon if he's straight or gay. He suggests she check his relationship status, which leaves the matter unsettled: Devon is involved with "Chris." Lizzie finally gets an answer to her questions about Mark when she discovers that he is actually straight, and masquerades as gay to get women. Sam resigns herself to never being sure about Devon. Both women are confused by Tyler, who says that despite having had sex with Fiona, he's absolutely sure he's one hundred percent gay.

episodes.title: The Unavailable Rule
episodes.description: Lizzie and Sam get a surprise visit from Sienna. Operating on the premise that men can't resist a woman who is "taken," they masquerade as Lizzie's bachelorette party and go on the prowl. Lizzie lets Marco pick her up, and takes him back to her place for one last fling. Sienna learns of Sam's interest in Richard and Jason, and insists that they attack the easier target -- Jason. They hack into his e-mail to find out where he will be, then follow him and his date, Lulu, to a movie theatre. When the film ends, Sienna creates a distraction, but Sam is unable to pry Jason away from Lulu. She and Sienna follow them to Jason's apartment building and spy through the window as they have sex. Lizzie tells Marco she's not engaged; he tells her he's married. Sienna says farewell to her friends and returns to the suburbs. Sam thinks her marriage is in trouble due to all her silly rules. She decides to get out of Jason's way and arranges to bump into Lulu to tell her what good man she's found. Sam feels pretty good about doing the right thing, but Lulu is appalled at the thought of dating a nice guy, and ditches Jason.

episodes.title: The Pill Rule
episodes.description: Sam is angry and distracted, so Lizzie sends her to see Dr. Feelgood. The doctor prescribes something for anxiety and depression, which Sam resents -- she just needs something to help her focus. Lizzie puts her in touch with Pill Pusher Patty, who trades some uppers for Sam's scrip. Sam takes the pills and turns into a model of efficiency. When she runs out of pills, she has Patty meet her at a house party she and Lizzie will be attending. Lizzie's ex, Drew, is at the party, as is Richard. When the girls arrive, Sam ignores Richard and makes a beeline for Patty; once she has her pills, Sam finds Richard, who is quite drunk, and takes him home with her. Lizzie finds Drew, who feels down because his new girlfriend is cheating. Lizzie gloats over this development, which only depresses Drew. He withdraws to a bedroom, which is where Patty finds him and consoles him with sex. Lizzie stumbles on them and realizes she's the only one at the party who didn't hook up. Back at her apartment, Sam manages to get Richard into bed. He passes out, penis erect, thanks to another of Patty's pills.

episodes.title: The Getting His Attention Rule
episodes.description: It's just another boring Sunday until Sienna breezes into the dive bar and announces she's staying until her husband apologizes for reading in the bathroom. She decides to show her protégés how to get a man's attention and gets aggressive with a Muscle-Bound Dude sitting at the bar. He's a cop, and he arrests her. Sam is sobered by the incident and thinks that Sienna's rules are guaranteed to keep them alone. She's ready for a change and asks co-worker Kate about her new boyfriend, Shermann. He's a public defender, and agrees to pull a few strings to try to get Sienna released. Sienna's husband, Nathaniel, visits her in jail. She apologizes, he forgives her, and she vows to try to stop sabotaging their relationship. Kate tells Shermann about her 10-date rule, and he suggests they have all 10 dates in one day; at day's end, they can then have sex within her rule. Sam types up all of Sienna's rules and shows Lizzie the ones she questions. Lizzie is reluctant to give up any of them. Sienna is released and bumps into the Muscle-Bound Dude at the desk. He talked to Nathaniel and has agreed to drop the charges. Nathaniel awaits Sienna in the jail's visiting room, where they have sex.

episodes.title: The Revenge Rule
episodes.description: Lizzie and Sam fight over Lizzie's acceptance of Drew's invitation to have drinks. Sam insists that this will lead to another reconciliation and break-up, and that it's time for Lizzie to end the relationship completely. It turns out that this time Drew just wants Lizzie to have her friend at the DMV fix some parking tickets for him -- he has reconciled with his cheating girlfriend. Sam bumps into Jason and lets it slip that she has a crush on him. Jason is free, since Lulu dumped him, and asks Sam out. As Sam readies for her date, Lizzie phones her to meet her at Drew's place, where they watch as a cop boots Drew's car -- Lizzie's revenge and a farewell to Drew. The girls celebrate at the dive bar, toasting their new rules: no more coercing guys to buy them drinks, no more young guys, no more b**ching, no more unrealized sexpectations, no more married guys, drinking contests or ex-boyfriends. Lizzie sees the Dirty Hot Guy and finally introduces herself; his name is Leo. Then Sam gets a text from Richard. She is torn, but opts for Jason. Lizzie and Leo also hook up for the night. Lizzie and Leo spoon contentedly after some hot sex, but sleeping in Jason's arms panics Sam, who gets up and leaves his place. She texts Lizzie to meet her -- she thinks she has just made a huge mistake...

episodes.title: The Girl on Girl Rule
episodes.description: Lizzie and Sam face a major crossroads in their friendship. Two new possible "depraved" disciples arrive on the scene: Sam's neighbor, Megan, and an old party pal, Jenna. Megan goes too far to please a date she met online. Jenna uses revenge sex to settle a score.

episodes.title: The Do Me Rule
episodes.description: Jason tries to get Sam out of her Lizzie-less funk. Megan becomes a "bad girl" to snag a "bad boy." Jenna's ex begs forgiveness and she gives him one night to make him forget about all the women who came before her.

episodes.title: The Bar Sex Rule
episodes.description: Sam makes a bet with her womanizing workmate, Dean. Jenna finds a sext on Ben's phone. Megan tries out The Rules of Depravity with a handsome client. Jason confronts Sam about her strange behavior.

episodes.title: The Morning After Rule
episodes.description: Sam and Jason adjust to their new status post-breakup. Megan tries to stick to The Rules -- in particular, the one about not texting the morning after. Jason's boss, Rachel, is looking for someone to do a little "overtime." Sam tries a new hobby and meets a handsome new friend; and her brother, Charlie, pops in for a surprise visit.

episodes.description: Ben takes romance to another level for his and Jenna's 5-year anniversary. Sam and her new classmate have a night that leaves his apartment in shambles. Jason gets lucky with a new approach. Rachel learns that size doesn't matter. Meg deals with a flirty client. Tyler gets himself a sexy new bartender.

episodes.description: When Sam realizes she is the only one of the gang who has never kissed a girl, Amy decides to take her and the ladies out to the local lesbian bar. Dean teaches Charlie the 'guy code.' Charlie goes on the prowl and runs into Megan, while Jenna finds a big surprise at home.

episodes.title: The Hos Before Bros Rule
episodes.description: Megan and Charlie give in to their mutual attraction -- several times -- despite Sam's disapproval. Sam enlists a pissed-off and single-again Jenna in a plan to bring Dean down while Ben asks Dean to keep Jenna occupied until he can win her back. Sam gets sage 'Rules' advice from Lizzie about Ryan., and Amy's hot one night stand shows up at The Bootleg.

episodes.title: The Basic Instincts Rule
episodes.description: Megan feels guilty about her hot new guy -- who isn't Charlie. Tyler needs a wife fast or he faces deportation, but first the gang needs to butch him up. Ben makes a confession and asks for Jenna's help. Jenna and Dean have started something they can't seem to stop, and Sam avoids defining her relationship with Ryan.

episodes.title: The Wingwoman Rule
episodes.description: Megan has a steaming hot dream about Charlie, but keeps it secret. Sam attends a sex addicts meeting with Jenna and Ben and makes a new friend. Amy moves in with Carrie. Sam sets up Dean with a sex addict on a mission. Jason sees a different side of Rachel.

episodes.title: The Breakup Sex Rule
episodes.description: Sam wants closure through breakup sex with Jason. Charlies ex-girlfriend is back but Jason realizes he already knows her. Tyler and Pill Pusher Penni seek domestic bliss while Amy and Carrie deal with domestic stress. Rachel and Jason bond over closing a big deal.

episodes.title: The Back Door Rule
episodes.description: Sam enlists Ryans help in spying on Jason. Jason and Rachel celebrate a business merger with a private merger. Megan meets a hot florist while planning Tylers wedding. Tyler and Penni have their immigration interview.

episodes.title: The Breaking and Entering Rule
episodes.description: Sam goes all out to pursue Ryan. Jason gets his ice queen to melt. Sam helps Megan with the fine art of stalking. Jenna enlists Deans help in some sweet revenge.

episodes.title: The Coming Together Rule
episodes.description: Dean gives Megan some tips to boost her confidence. Ryan responds to Sams love letter. Dean asks Jenna out on a real date. A surprise wedding has some unexpected guests.

episodes.title: Dharavi Main Bulaya Hai
episodes.description: Thalaivan has an empire worth Rs 30,000 crore in the heart of Mumbai’s Dharavi. CM Janvi Surve gets insecure about Thalaivan’s growing popularity and orders a police raid on this empire in order to threaten Thalaivan. Will the plan work? Can Thalaivan really be moved by such raids?

episodes.title: Thok Doonga Saale Ko
episodes.description: An officer of the JCP, Jayant Gavaskar decides to take on Thalaivan and makes it his mission to bring down him and his operations in Dharavi Bank. On the other hand, Thalaivan’s nephew- Mahesh comes to know about the news that is going to change the course of his life. What is the news? Will JCP Gavaskar succeed in his mission?

episodes.title: Veenu
episodes.description: Besides professional obligations, JCP Jayant Gavaskar also has personal motivations for hating Thalaivan and the past is revealed. Dharavi prepares to witness the big showdown. What lies ahead of the showdown? Will one of the two parties emerge victorious?

episodes.title: War Room
episodes.description: The leaks make Thalaivan furious and he is determined to find out who was behind the sabotage. Joe now has to prove his loyalty. JCP Gavaskar makes a big win and his war room is set in motion. Meanwhile, Mahesh and Sakeena meet. Will Thalaivan be able to find the source of the leak? What happens when he comes to know the truth?

episodes.title: Bhool Bhulaiya
episodes.description: JCP Gavaskar succeeds in attacking Thalaivan. But, can he take the man out of the maze of Dharavi? Will Thalaivan retaliate against the attack?

episodes.title: Family
episodes.description: In the latest development, a power struggle ensues between Thalaivan’s eldest son, Shiva and the rest of the family. Meanwhile, JCP Gavaskar and Jaanvi plan their next move. What are they planning to do?

episodes.title: Make Him Suffer
episodes.description: JCP Gavaskar becomes the new commissioner of Mumbai Police and the first agenda on his target is revenge. Though he remains unaware that a new sinister plan is brewing in the streets of Dharavi against him.

episodes.title: Withdrawal
episodes.description: The demands of people to close their accounts with Dharavi Bank grow louder and louder. At the same time, Micheal comes to know about Sakeena’s betrayal. How will he react to this? How will Thalaivan control the growing tension amidst the people?

episodes.title: Secrets
episodes.description: Shiva comes to know about the secret of his younger brother. Mahesh and Deepa decide to run away and leave the country. On the other hand, Thalaivan forges a new alliance and declares war on Gavaskar. How will Gavaskar respond?

episodes.title: Koi Bhi Nahi Bachega
episodes.description: How will the game end? Will Dharavi Bank really burn down? Who will be the culprit of the end of Dharavi Bank CM Janvi, commissioner Gavaskar or the mighty man himself- Thalaivan?

episodes.title: This Is Not Olympic Level
episodes.description: Zoe's arrival at the sports center ignites rivalry, while Olympo offers major sponsorships. Amaia pushes Núria to her limits — with severe consequences.

episodes.title: Crying or Winning
episodes.description: Wracked with guilt about Núria, Amaia struggles to control her emotions. Zoe lets loose at a house party in the woods and has an unexpected hook-up.

episodes.title: No, Not Again
episodes.description: Roque's sexuality costs him a place at an international rugby tournament. Unable to find Núria, a suspicious Amaia searches for evidence of doping.

episodes.title: It's Best If You Stop Now
episodes.description: As Cristian returns and Olympo offers its second sponsorship, an anti-doping raid causes panic. Amaia faces accusations of betraying her fellow athletes.

episodes.title: There's No Getting Through to You
episodes.description: Facing a downward spiral, HPC Pyrenees decides to get tough on the athletes. Cristian turns heads in the center as Amaia becomes increasingly lonely.

episodes.title: You've Always Been My Favorite
episodes.description: Olympo flaunts its chosen athletes to the media and Amaia spots a chance to uncover the truth about Núria. Meanwhile, Zoe faces a tricky dilemma.

episodes.title: It's Called Strategy
episodes.description: After a surprise return to the center, the world tournament tests take a toll on Amaia. The documentary about Roque becomes juicier than expected.

episodes.title: Amaia Is Always Right
episodes.description: It's crunch time for the athletes as they compete under a cloud of doping suspicion, which intensifies doubts around the true intentions of Olympo.

episodes.title: The Trap
episodes.description: Helena is the perfect wife — until her passionate affair with a younger man spirals into a dangerous scheme to obtain her freedom.

episodes.title: The Reunion
episodes.description: An argument escalates into a bloody scene. Iván's cover is blown as his trust in Helena wavers. Octavio tries to keep the police investigation hidden.

episodes.title: Desperation
episodes.description: Octavio is kidnapped by El Magic, who just wants Claudio. As Iván questions Helena's motives, Fer spirals. Octavio makes a startling discovery.

episodes.title: Under Suspicion
episodes.description: Octavio and Helena clash as Iván learns more about Claudio's secretive parties. Livia reunites with an old flame, and Fer makes a terrible confession.

episodes.title: Doubts
episodes.description: Octavio fights the clock as he executes El Magic's plan to find Claudio. Iván spins a tale for Pablo, and Livia makes a new online dating match.

episodes.title: False Death
episodes.description: Iván learns about Helena's dark side. Octavio and El Magic conspire to fool everyone. Claudio faces his captor.

episodes.title: The Prosecutor's Fall
episodes.description: A phone call gives Livia hope, and Iván's responsibilities catch up to him. When Pablo's secret comes out, he's forced to the edge of reason.

episodes.title: The Call
episodes.description: Claudio attempts an escape while Livia's suspicions about Octavio are fueled. As Helena recovers in the hospital, another video leaks.

episodes.title: Captured
episodes.description: Livia and Iván are kidnapped. Sofía turns her eye to Antonio. Rafael worries about a third video leak, and a derelict chapel yields a startling sight.

episodes.title: He's Alive
episodes.description: Claudio's return threatens to break the Martínezes. Another video leak threatens a high-powered executive. Helena plots a new escape.

episodes.title: Extortion
episodes.description: Fedra and Antonio adjust their plans as Montero files a claim against Claudio and Helena. Livia meets Rebeca, and El Magic pays Claudio a visit.

episodes.title: Secrets of the Past
episodes.description: Claudio exacts revenge on his enemies, starting with Helena. Fedra gets close to Octavio. Iván's secret comes out, as Rafael reaches out to Helena.

episodes.title: The Scandal
episodes.description: Claudio settles a score, and an online leak tears Helena and Iván apart. As Helena and Fer seek refuge in an unlikely place, Livia gets what she wants.

episodes.title: Disillusionment
episodes.description: Sofía's suspicions raise questions for Livia. Iván and Rebeca get a scare. Rafael and Dora are tested, as Claudio and Fedra have a dicey confrontation.

episodes.title: All Against All
episodes.description: A police investigation into Claudio's death leads to several suspects. Octavio discovers Fedra's deceit as Livia overhears Iván's shocking confession.

episodes.title: Revelations
episodes.description: Helena is arrested while Iván and Livia find clues to Fedra's past. El Licenciado plans a hit on Octavio. Fer unlocks a key piece to his past.

episodes.title: A Heavy Blow
episodes.description: Rafael gives Fer the truth, and Helena conceals it. Iván overhears Sofía and Benítez. Arcadia's revenge claims a life. El Licenciado comes calling.

episodes.title: New Life
episodes.description: As Livia and Octavio face El Licenciado, Helena has one more scheme up her sleeve. Sofía closes a case — but will another one open?

episodes.title: Pilot
episodes.description: Newly promoted writer Jane is unsettled when Jacqueline assigns her a big story – writing about why her ex broke up with her. Kat chases a story about outspoken photographer Adena, but is confused by her strong connection to the woman. Meanwhile, Sutton tries not to feel left behind by her best friends as she still toils in the assistant ranks. But she shocks them when they uncover a major secret Sutton has been keeping – her scandalous affair with lusted-after Scarlet magazine lawyer Richard.

episodes.title: O Hell No
episodes.description: Kat finds herself questioning her identity as she continues to spend time with Adena. Jane is horrified when she is tasked with writing Scarlet’s sex column – especially when her story turns intensely personal. And Sutton is given an opportunity to advance at Scarlet, but questions if it’s what she really wants to be doing with her life.

episodes.title: The Woman Behind the Clothes
episodes.description: Kat finds herself the victim of internet trolling when she stands up for gender inequality. Sutton thinks she may have found her dream job but worries she doesn’t have what it takes to make it work. And Jane pursues a story about a congresswoman but tries to find a different angle to make her voice heard.

episodes.title: If You Can't Do It With Feeling
episodes.description: Sutton is flustered when someone at Scarlet has the wrong impression of her professional background. Jane is determined to prove she can have a friends with benefits relationship without feelings getting in the way. And Kat and Adena continue growing closer.

episodes.title: No Feminism in the Champagne Room
episodes.description: Jane is stunned when the subject of her latest article, a woman who left a finance job to become an exotic dancer, threatens to sue Scarlet – and Jane. Sutton is excited when she thinks she’s making a step forward in her career. Kat questions whether she is ready for a real relationship with anyone, especially in light of recent events with Adena.

episodes.title: The Breast Issue
episodes.description: In promoting Scarlet’s breast health awareness campaign, Kat tries to be bold with her message, but is left wondering whether her competitive nature is hurting her cause. Jane confronts past issues and current anxieties when she is tasked with writing a controversial piece about BRCA gene testing. Sutton is determined to excel at her tasks at hand, but when things fall apart, it’s Alex who rushes to her rescue.

episodes.title: Three Girls in a Tub
episodes.description: Richard is determined to get to know Sutton’s friends outside of the office and invites the girls to dinner, but things don’t quite go as planned. Sutton attempts to network with a new social circle by attending a high tea. While on a date with someone else, Jane comes to a realization about Pinstripe; and Jacqueline is forced to intervene when Kat’s new staffer keeps damaging Scarlet’s social media presence.

episodes.title: The End of the Beginning
episodes.description: As rumors of layoffs at Scarlet sweep through the office leaving everyone unsettled, Jane learns of a potential opportunity at a rival publication. Sutton is given a big opportunity when a coworker buckles under pressure. Kat is tasked with organizing a “Readers Night” for Scarlet, but is distracted by thoughts of Adena – leading to a big decision.  And Jane talks Sutton and Kat into joining her on a dating app.

episodes.title: Before Tequilla Sunrise
episodes.description: Jane, Sutton, Alex, Pinstripe and Jacqueline are all trapped in the Scarlet offices due to a massive traffic jam. Forced to spend time together, Jane reexamines her feelings for Pinstripe. Sutton makes a surprising move.  And when she learns Adena is leaving New York, Kat makes an impulsive decision.

episodes.title: Carry the Weight
episodes.description: Jane gets an eye-opening experience when she is tasked with writing a piece about a performance artist/activist who is speaking out about sexual assault. Kat is distracted by thoughts of Adena while trying to throw a memorable NY Fashion Week party for Scarlet; and Sutton gets into an awkward situation with Richard.

episodes.title: Feminist Army
episodes.description: Jane is excited to publish her first big piece for Incite, especially since she’s writing about a female CEO she admires, and she knows Jacqueline will be reading it. Sutton is thrown when a new corporate policy seems to give her and Richard the green light on their romance. And Adena grows frustrated when Kat seems too eager to flaunt their burgeoning relationship.

episodes.title: Rose Colored Glasses
episodes.description: Believing it shouldn’t matter, Kat bristles when Alex recommends she highlights that she is black in her company bio. However, while introducing her parents to Adena, Kat is forced to confront how her avoidance of labels has affected her life. Sutton is horrified when she discovers her fellow fashion assistants think she was asked to organize a photo shoot featuring “honorable men” for reasons other than her talent. And Jane tries to defend herself after the fallout from her Incite article, which doesn’t go as planned.

episodes.title: The Scarlet Letter
episodes.description: Sutton is in an awkward position when she is put in charge of hiring a photographer for an accessories shoot, and Kat asks her to hire Adena. Jane follows around a cute and altruistic doctor named Ben for her latest article. Scarlet’s newest board member, Cleo, causes Jacqueline to defend her role at the magazine.

episodes.title: OMG
episodes.description: Jane crosses paths with Pinstripe, who inspires her to try a new style of writing. Meanwhile, she learns something new about Ben. Adena reluctantly brings Kat out to meet her friends, and Kat quickly immerses herself in the New York lesbian scene. Sutton fights for an in with a well-connected influencer named Brooke.

episodes.title: Stride of Pride
episodes.description: Kat sets out to hire someone for the social team, but is unhappy by the applicant pool’s lack of diversity. Jane, meanwhile, faces the financial realities of her freelance situation.

episodes.title: The Domino Effect
episodes.description: Jane is thrilled when her sexual assault article for Scarlet is nominated for a prestigious journalism award. Determined to prove herself to Jacqueline, Jane jumps at the chance to write a follow-up piece, until the story takes an unexpected turn. Kat struggles with whether to tell Adena a secret and Sutton is given a challenging assignment – styling Richard’s date.

episodes.title: Betsy
episodes.description: When Jane discovers that Sutton has been hiding a gun in the apartment, the girls realize they have polar opposite views on the subject. Meanwhile, Adena shocks Kat with her latest suggestion.

episodes.title: Plan B
episodes.description: After an intimate moment mishap with Ben, Jane evaluates if motherhood is in her future because of her BRCA gene mutation. Kat is eager to flaunt her social media influence by partnering with a beauty brand that offers her an opportunity to be their spokesperson. Meanwhile, Sutton makes her first major fashion department decision without Oliver.

episodes.title: Trippin
episodes.description: The girls take a trip to Sutton’s hometown and meet a few important figures from her past. Meanwhile, Jane struggles with planning for her future, and Kat feels a rift in her relationship with Adena. Guest starring Billy Magnussen.

episodes.title: We'll Always Have Paris
episodes.description: Sutton’s professional dreams come true when she jets off to Paris for Fashion Week, but while there she gains a new perspective on her situation. Jane moves forward with her fertility plan until she learns surprising news about her options and is faced with Ben and Pinstripe’s different solutions. Kat faces pressure from Jacqueline to make their Paris party a success while attempting to reset her relationship with Adena.

episodes.title: The New Normal
episodes.description: Scarlet Magazine brings in Patrick Duchand to run the digital branch, effectively knocking Jacqueline down to only running the print magazine. Meanwhile, Jane has picked her guy, but is frustrated that a man is put in charge of a women’s magazine. Kat struggles to keep up happy appearances on social media and as a speaker at the Scarlet Summit, while secretly suffering heartache, and Sutton and Richard enjoy their romance in the limelight and discuss moving in together.

episodes.title: Plus It Up
episodes.description: Jane begins her fertility treatments in preparation for freezing her eggs and is assigned an article to write about her experience, but with a very personal twist. Kat learns that a prominent lesbian bar is being closed down and replaced with condos and decides to throw a Queer Prom to fundraise its rescue. Sutton moves in with Richard but struggles to accept his help when Oliver’s mysterious absences force her to put in more hours at work.

episodes.title: Stroke of Genius
episodes.description: With Jane’s egg extraction on the horizon, she and her boyfriend can’t wait to have sex again and she challenges herself to be less “vanilla” and more “rocky road” in the bedroom. Alex examines his dating life in a piece for Scarlet digital when he realizes he was the subject behind a #MeToo story. Fed up after realizing that her councilman doesn’t have his city’s best interests at heart, Kat decides to channel her passion by volunteering for his opposition. Sutton considers a career shift into fashion design but debates how to break the news to Oliver.

episodes.title: The Deep End
episodes.description: Jane stumbles on the scoop of a lifetime, but Jacqueline turns down the pitch when her impending 10th-anniversary gala and continued power-struggles with Patrick force her to contemplate her future with Scarlet. Sutton preps a design seminar application for Oliver’s recommendation, but he remains distracted by things in his personal life. Kat decides to run for City Council but reconsiders when she learns what the opposition might spin about her past.

episodes.title: Technical Difficulties
episodes.description: Scarlet falls prey to a data hack, halting production of the dotcom and magazine and Jane and Jacqueline fear their investigation could be compromised as a result. Pressures escalate when Sutton and Richard host a dinner party. Meanwhile, Kat opens up to Tia as they begin her campaign.

episodes.title: #TBT
episodes.description: The Scarlet email hack brings up memories of the trio’s first meeting four years ago, reminding them that together they can overcome anything.

episodes.title: Mixed Messages
episodes.description: When Kat faces racial profiling while canvassing for office, she is tempted to call the woman out on social media in order to find justice. Sutton realizes that Richard is keeping something from her. Meanwhile, Jane and Jacqueline make headway on the workplace harassment investigation.

episodes.title: Revival
episodes.description: When Adena returns to New York, Kat debates whether she’s ready to see her, but quickly realizes she might not have a choice. Sutton is stretched in too many directions between styling for Oliver and designing for her seminar, causing friction with Richard.

episodes.title: Final Push
episodes.description: When Kat beings to doubt herself on the eve of her election, an unexpected person gives her the reassurance she needs. Jane and Jacqueline are confident about their workplace harassment investigation and decide to take action. Sutton coaches Carly through a difficult situation at school.

episodes.title: Breaking Through the Noise
episodes.description: When Jane and Jacqueline’s exposé makes an impact, Jacqueline takes a hard look at how she can make Scarlet an industry leader that practices what it preaches. Sutton celebrates the end of her design seminar with a fashion show but surprises herself with the results. Jane deals with an emotional fallout amidst a career high. Kat makes a choice not to run from her problems anymore.

episodes.title: Legends of the Fall Issue
episodes.description: Scarlet reels over their new dynamic, forcing everyone to adjust. Jane tries to cope with the changes to Jacqueline’s role at the magazine and joins forces with Kat and Sutton to make it clear how much she means to them. Sutton takes stock of her position at Scarlet, as Richard considers a world outside it. Kat butts heads with RJ Safford over his response to the new direction of the magazine.

episodes.title: #scarlet
episodes.description: Kat is faced with a past regret when she crosses paths with a closeted singer who asked for help coming out. Jane has her first mammogram and spirals into anxiety waiting for the results—and how Ryan fits into it. Sutton and Richard’s long-distance relationship hits a snag, and the trio discovers a secret about one of their coworkers.

episodes.title: Marathon
episodes.description: Kat goes out of her way to help a transgender runner get into the New York City Marathon, while Jane and Ryan try a different kind of marathon to rebuild their relationship. Sutton starts to feel she’s going backward in her career and looks for a way to improve her value to Scarlet. Jacqueline’s new situation at work leads to tension with her husband.

episodes.title: Babes in Toyland
episodes.description: Jane volunteers to write a story about a sex club in hopes of proving she is ready for the next step in her career. Kat’s latest crusade to save a female-oriented sex toy company could lead her to begin dating again, while Sutton has doubts about how to kick off her plan to get promoted. Meanwhile, Alex struggles with his new platform at Scarlet.

episodes.title: Tearing Down the Donut Wall
episodes.description: Jane’s in-depth look at millennial weddings comes to a screeching halt when she uncovers a secret about Jacqueline. Overwhelmed by her current assignment and against uniforms of all kinds, Sutton decides to focus her energy on helping Carly take on her school uniform policy, without running it by Oliver. Meanwhile, Kat thinks she can handle uncomplicated dating, only to find it’s more complicated than she thought.

episodes.title: To Peg or Not to Peg
episodes.description: Fresh off a wild night with a new fling, Kat considers flipping the script on preconceived gender roles in the bedroom. Jane’s tapped to speak at a wellness seminar, but the appearance of a sudden feminine health problem has her feeling like a fraud. Sutton tries to earn the respect of Richard’s mother while finding sponsors for her Instagram, and Alex challenges his notions about masculinity while dating a high-powered woman.

episodes.title: The Space Between
episodes.description: Kat and Adena need to work together on a Scarlet project, which becomes tense when Adena learns about Kat’s recent romantic relationships. Sutton earns her first solo styling gig, hoping it leads to being a fashion influencer. Jane makes a decision about her health concerning her BRCA-1 status.

episodes.title: Stardust
episodes.description: Jane is overjoyed when her brother Evan comes to town, and she introduces him to Ryan. Adena turns to Kat for help in dealing with RJ, which causes more trouble between Kat and the board. Richard returns from San Francisco, allowing him and Sutton to dive into wedding plans.

Jane decides to throw Sutton an epic bachelorette party, but the bride can’t quite bring herself to enjoy the festivities. Kat learns surprising info about RJ, which leads her to question the company’s morals. Jane gets career news while facing some devastating personal issues.

episodes.title: Some Kind of Wonderful
episodes.description: Sutton and Richard’s wedding day is here, and Sutton is faced with a big decision. Jane tries to celebrate her friends while struggling to process recent discoveries. Kat’s continuing crusade against the board has unexpected and life-altering consequences.

episodes.title: Leveling Up
episodes.description: Three months after surgery, Jane returns to Scarlet with new editorial duties. Kat faces a hard truth when she's forced to take some responsibility. Sutton goes to bat on her first shoot and gets some shocking news that upends her world.

episodes.title: Snow Day
episodes.description: A blizzard hits New York City, and Kat is trapped at her new job with her nemesis. Sutton struggles to balance her career and relationship. Jane tries to emulate Jacqueline's leadership with her new staff. Oliver comes face to face with his ex.

episodes.title: Lost
episodes.description: Sutton grapples with her complex reaction towards the massive changes in her life. At Kat's urging, Jane starts dating again. Kat plans her next move as she faces financial insecurity and turns to Alex for help.

episodes.title: The Truth Will Set You Free
episodes.description: Jane isn’t comfortable in her post-surgery body, but a visit from her dad may change her outlook. Sutton and Richard make plans for the future. Kat tries to move forward at work with a podcast, but her first episode comes with a price.

episodes.title: Love
episodes.description: In five short love stories, Kat, Jane, Sutton, Jacqueline, and Alex confront challenges in their various relationships, bringing newfound understanding of their partners or creating irreparable rifts between them.

episodes.title: Not Far from the Tree
episodes.description: Sutton visits her hometown, but falls into a familiar pattern while there. Jane finds a big story, but it could have serious ramifications for Jacqueline. Kat is reluctant to share her new romance with Jane and Sutton.

episodes.title: Trust Fall
episodes.description: Jane races to finish a high-risk expose that could have repercussions for Jacqueline. Sutton has a chance to shine at a Scarlet retreat if she can regain her focus. And Kat wants to stay true to herself while making a big decision.

episodes.title: The Crossover
episodes.description: All eyes are on Jane as she and Jacqueline combat a public inconsistency in her latest story. Kat runs into an old friend, sparking a new idea. Alex uses his podcast to make a statement. Sutton gets a career win but a personal blow.

episodes.title: Rolling into the Future
episodes.description: Jane faces unexpected performance reviews that shake her confidence in The Failing Feminist. Sutton’s attempts to move on from her divorce are thwarted by other’s opinions, and Kat reunites with Adena, who has a secret.

episodes.title: Day Trippers
episodes.description: Jane, Kat and Sutton, all overwhelmed with monumental work decisions, seek clarity in an unorthodox way.

episodes.title: Don't Turn Away
episodes.description: Kat struggles to get a movement off the ground and is faced with a life-changing opportunity. Sutton gets an unexpected call that threatens the progress she’s made at therapy, and Jane is faced with her biggest challenge ever at Scarlet.

episodes.title: I Expect You to Have Adventures
episodes.description: After a season of big changes and hard decisions, the future looks bright for the women of “The Bold Type” … but it’s always full of surprises. Jane, Kat and Sutton each face huge choices and evaluate their own paths.

episodes.title: Episode 16
episodes.description: Episode 16 of The Bold Type

episodes.title: Secrets
episodes.description: In 2019, a local boy's disappearance stokes fear in the residents of Winden, a small German town with a strange and tragic history.

episodes.title: Lies
episodes.description: When a grim discovery leaves the police baffled, Ulrich seeks a search warrant for the power plant. A mysterious stranger checks into the hotel.

episodes.title: Past and Present
episodes.description: It's 1986, and Ulrich's brother, Mads, has been missing for a month. Confusion reigns as past and present intertwine.

episodes.title: Double Lives
episodes.description: Bizarre occurrences give Charlotte a sense of déjà vu, and she suspects Peter is hiding something. Franziska snaps when Magnus confronts her.

episodes.title: Truths
episodes.description: Hannah takes her obsession with Ulrich too far. The stranger asks Regina to deliver an important package. Martha is torn between Jonas and Bartosz.

episodes.title: Sic Mundus Creatus Est
episodes.description: Ulrich looks to the past for answers and dredges up disturbing family secrets. Armed with new tools, Jonas probes the cave's murky depths.

episodes.title: Crossroads
episodes.description: Ulrich questions a frail and frightened Helge in the nursing home. Jonas searches for Mikkel, but the stranger warns him about meddling with the past.

episodes.title: As You Sow, So You Shall Reap
episodes.description: In 1953, the disfigured bodies of two boys are exhumed at a construction site, the future location of Winden's nuclear power plant.

episodes.title: Beginnings and Endings
episodes.description: Six months after the disappearances, the police form a task force. In 2052, Jonas learns that most of Winden perished in an apocalyptic event.

episodes.title: Dark Matter
episodes.description: Clausen and Charlotte interview Regina. The Stranger takes Hannah to 1987, where Claudia has an unnerving encounter and Egon visits an old nemesis.

episodes.title: Ghosts
episodes.description: In 1954, a missing Helge returns, but he'll only speak to Noah. In 1987, Claudia brings the time machine to Tannhaus, and Egon questions Ulrich again.

episodes.title: The Travelers
episodes.description: Jonas meets an ominous figure. While the kids comb the cave for answers, the adults gather in the bunker to share what they know about the travelers.

episodes.title: Lost and Found
episodes.description: In 1987, Ulrich seizes an opportunity. The kids return to the cave with the time machine, and Jonas learns of a loophole that could change the future.

episodes.title: An Endless Cycle
episodes.description: Armed with a plan to prevent the apocalypse, Jonas travels to 2019. During the Nielsens' anniversary party, Ulrich sneaks off with Hannah.

episodes.title: Bootstrap
episodes.description: When beer baron Vikram Walia, the man who destroyed her father's business, acquires the company Shikha works for, she does what she always does - grab a beer with her bestie Anahita and vent her woes. But when Anahita gets corporate-screwed herself, they hatch a plan to launch their own beer brand and give Walia a taste of his own medicine.

episodes.title: USP
episodes.description: Shikha and Anahita real hustle begins, and their hunt for a brewmaster leads them to an eccentric addition to their team. Stuck between sexist investors and government red tape, they realise that the unexpected solution to all their problems was hidden in plain sight.

episodes.title: Marketing
episodes.description: With the invention of their mysterious mentor David Jones, everything changes for Shikha and Anahita. Deals get done and their path seems to be easing, but maintaining their elaborate ruse is no easy task as the legend of David grows beyond their expectations.

episodes.title: Brand Ambassador
episodes.description: Bankruptcy looms after the latest disaster, forcing Shikha and Anahita right into arms of the shady Laila. But when Laila demands to meet David Jones in person, they rush to find the perfect candidate to bring their fictional mentor to life.

episodes.title: The Launch
episodes.description: The Jugaaro launch is finally here! Dylan steps into the spotlight as David Jones and the gang's marketing mayhem takes Delhi by storm. But when nemesis Walia crashes the launch party and Dylan drops an unexpected bombshell, Shikha and Anahita face a double crisis.

episodes.title: Silent Partner
episodes.description: Success tastes sweet as Jugaaro becomes the hottest beer in Delhi, even landing a sweet music festival deal. But when Walia strikes with a potentially devastating attack, Shikha considers making a dangerous deal with Laila, while unexpected sparks fly at the festival.

episodes.title: Friction
episodes.description: Jugaaro's success story turns into a nightmare as secrets explode everywhere. Trust shatters and partnerships crumble as Anahita's questionable romance is exposed, Shikha's dangerous dealings come to light, and Dylan is caught between it all.

episodes.title: Pivot
episodes.description: With a ticking clock to pay Laila back or face consequences, Shikha considers making the the ultimate sacrifice. Shikha and Anahita put their rising differences aside and rally together for one last desperate gamble to save their dream. Will the partners survive the latest storm?
