episodes.title: Facchas
episodes.description: Fresher Devika Kumari leaks a video during a sex-ed night at Matilda House, sparking controversy. Principal Datta advocates open dialogue but faces pressure to rusticate Paro Sarna. First-years Wallika, Devika, Tabassum, Vandana, and Trisha are caught in the chaotic excitement of their first semester as Matilda House faces a crisis it might not survive.

episodes.title: Paro Ki PG Party
episodes.description: To prevent the no-hostel-curfew policy from being reversed by their new Principal Lata Bakshi, Matilda House seniors, led by Paro and Shubhra, campaign against the referendum. Bakshi pushes for the vote to go her way to save Matilda House from the fallout of the "sex-education" incident. Vandana, Tabassum, Trisha and Wallika bond at Paro’s PG party, while Devika feels out of place and leaves.

episodes.title: Bhook Hadtaal
episodes.description: Bakshi’s referendum reverses the curfew, sparking opposition from Matilda House’s stalwart faculty and seniors. The freshers’ lives progress: Vandana moves to a PG, Trisha bonds with Tabassum and pursues hockey to impress Parth. Paro, devastated by Matilda House’s loss, starts a hunger strike. As friendships deepen, tensions rise.

episodes.title: Kuch Ziddi Ladkiyan
episodes.description: As their friendships deepen and they discover each other’s passions, Trisha, Vandana, Wally, Tabby, and Devika unknowingly take steps toward becoming Ziddi Girls. When wealthy socialite Anita Raghani challenges public education, Lata Bakshi surprisingly defends it, clashing with Raghani and Sihag. Meanwhile, Paro and friends secretly plan a performance at Masterpiece to defy Bakshi’s censorship.

episodes.title: Main Darna Nahi Chahti
episodes.description: The hunger strike ends, impacting our freshers. Life picks up: Tabassum lands a brand deal, Trisha focuses on hockey, Vandana faces challenges at Experimanch, Wallika joins Paro’s resistance, and Devika struggles financially. Bakshi offers Devika a scholarship, while urging her to spy on Paro, creating a loyalty conflict. As tensions rise, Devika infiltrates the resistance and must choose a side.

episodes.title: Apne Mann Ki Karungi
episodes.description: Tensions arise at Masterpiece as Paro’s resistance group recruits Devika and Wally, while Devika struggles with spying for Bakshi to keep her scholarship. Vandana is tricked into a shocking stage moment, leading to her suspension. Amidst friendship drama and sporting triumphs, Paro’s secret protest against Bakshi collapses. Vandana disappears, leaving our freshers wondering how to help her.

episodes.title: Kya Sabka First Year Itna Happening Hota Hai?
episodes.description: A faltered plan isn’t a failed plan. Paro and the seniors execute their resistance plan at Masterpiece and expose Raghani and Sihag’s agendas. Chaos erupts as PICA members invade Matilda House and attack Paro. Wallika rallies students for justice, while Devika feels betrayed after losing her scholarship. Bakshi must decide if she can save Matilda House from collapse.

episodes.title: Abhivyakti Ke Khatre
episodes.description: The finale presents Matilda House with its biggest challenge yet -privatisation. Many colleges rally in support of Matilda House, while Bakshi and team work to convince the board. Meanwhile, our facchas fight to protect Wally from Mayank Asthana and his men, strengthening their bond and Bakshi goes from fighting against Matilda House to fighting for it. But will it be enough?

episodes.title: Episode 1
episodes.description: When an army truck crashes outside a care home and turns the residents there into something nasty, four friends have to deal with the deadly consequences...

episodes.title: Episode 2
episodes.description: Charlie and Kelly must deal with Kelly's nan while Steff heads off on a dangerous side quest with Finn. Meanwhile the OAPs, led by Cecily, are hungry...

episodes.title: Episode 3
episodes.description: The army tighten their control over Dambury as Charlie, Kelly, Finn and Steff go on a rescue mission. Billy's return ruffles feathers. Reunited, Frank and Cecily seek out others to recruit...

episodes.title: Episode 4
episodes.description: Relationship problems and exams aren't the only life or death situation the gang encounters. A split breaks out among the OAPs as a newcomer turns Frank's head away from Cecily.

episodes.title: Episode 5
episodes.description: Charlie and Steff's friendship is tested. Billy sees an opportunity. Gil starts to realise that her task involves more than meets the eye. The residents of Dambury decide that enough is enough.

episodes.title: Episode 6
episodes.description: Billy takes over and heartbreaking revelations come out that threaten the town and her family. Meanwhile residents race against the clock to escape Dambury, but the army have other plans in mind.

episodes.title: Episode 9
episodes.description: Episode 9 of Generation Z

episodes.title: Pilot
episodes.description: A teen plunges into danger when he moves in with his wild relatives in a surf community.

episodes.title: We Don't Hurt People
episodes.description: The Codys must deal with the aftermath of the heist, as they discover all did not go as planned. Smurf dispatches her boys to tie up loose ends, but her efforts are complicated by Baz and Pope’s growing rivalry. As Pope gets increasingly volatile, J finds himself in the middle.

episodes.title: Stay Close, Stick Together
episodes.description: While Craig recovers from his wound, Baz and Craig deal with some old associates down in Mexico. Meanwhile, strapped for cash, Pope takes charge and ropes Deran and J into a job without Smurf's knowledge. Threatened by J's participation, Deran sends J a terrifying message.

episodes.title: Dead to Me
episodes.description: As the boys gear up for Pope's birthday, Smurf wants to know if they're playing by her rules. J learns more about his mother's estrangement from the family.

episodes.title: Flesh Is Weak
episodes.description: When Deran won't come home, Pope goes to extreme measures. Baz gets an idea for the Codys' next job. J goes out with his teacher, while Smurf confronts her past.

episodes.title: Child Care
episodes.description: When Pope tests positive for drugs, Smurf does what it takes to keep the family intact. Baz gets his brothers to rob a house as part of his larger plan.

episodes.title: Goddamn Animals
episodes.description: While Smurf takes care of unfinished business, Craig and Deran throw a party at the house. Forced to accelerate his timetable, Baz takes the final step in his long con. J makes a dangerous mistake.

episodes.title: Man In
episodes.description: Tensions run high as the Codys prepare for their big heist. Catherine gets a shock and must decide what's best for her family. J faces pressure from the cops.

episodes.title: Judas Kiss
episodes.description: While the Codys go after the biggest score of their lives, the cops put J in an impossible position. Catherine triggers Smurf's suspicions when she comes over to make amends. Smurf sends Pope to investigate.

episodes.title: Eat What You Kill
episodes.description: After a risky heist misfires, the boys blame Smurf, sending shock waves through the family. Baz copes with being a single parent, while Deran makes plans for the future.

episodes.title: Karma
episodes.description: As Smurf adjusts to being sidelined, the boys scope out their next job. Deran needs quick cash, and Pope and Craig lend him a hand while Baz investigates Catherine’s disappearance.

episodes.title: Bleed For It
episodes.description: Smurf takes J to the desert for an old friend’s wake. Baz visits Lucy in Mexico and Pope bonds with Amy from the megachurch while babysitting Lena. Deran considers what he’ll risk to get a liquor license for the bar.

episodes.title: Broken Boards
episodes.description: With the bar set to open, Deran frets about telling Smurf about it. Pope and Amy go on a date, while Nicky must choose between Craig and J.

episodes.title: Forgive Us Our Trespasses
episodes.description: As the boys put the megachurch heist in motion, Craig has second thoughts. Javi surprises Smurf with a visit.

episodes.title: Cry Havoc
episodes.description: As Javi ratchets up the pressure on Smurf, she enlists J to help her. Baz is confronted by a secret Catherine kept from him. Pope and Baz clash in the wake of the megachurch job.

episodes.title: Dig
episodes.description: The boys consider how far they’ll go to help Smurf eliminate Javi. Shaken by what’s happened, Nicky and J get closer. Baz shares new information with Pope about Catherine’s disappearance.

episodes.title: Grace
episodes.description: As cops press Amy about the church robbery, Pope diverts their suspicions. Craig plans an unusual heist of his own. Baz tails Smurf to find out what she’s really hiding.

episodes.title: Custody
episodes.description: When Baz bows out of the yacht heist, Craig and Deran consider their options. Meanwhile, Baz recruits J for a more personal job.

episodes.title: Treasure
episodes.description: As Craig leads the boys and Nicky in pirating the yacht, Smurf tries to find out who robbed her. Meanwhile, Baz considers what life would be like without Smurf calling all the shots.

episodes.title: The Leopard
episodes.description: Baz puts his plan to take down Smurf in motion as Marco cashes in a favor with Craig and Deran. Pope seeks the truth behind the reasons for Catherine's death.

episodes.title: You Will Be Gutted
episodes.description: With Smurf in jail, Baz makes his move to run the family, but his brothers have other plans.

episodes.title: Betrayal
episodes.description: When Smurf realizes she may be in jail a lot longer than expected, she pits her sons against one another, the consequences be damned.

episodes.title: The Killing
episodes.description: Baz fights for his life as the Cody boys figure out what their next move is in the aftermath of the shooting. Smurf gets some surprising news in jail and fields an offer from Pearce.

episodes.title: In The Red
episodes.description: J struggles to keep the family business afloat after Smurf enlists him to make sure all the bills get paid. Deran makes his own moves independent of the family. Pope learns the ins and outs of parenting as he cares for Lena, and Craig makes enemies in Mexico.

episodes.title: The Center Will Hold
episodes.description: Smurf navigates prison politics in pursuit of a potential job. J pulls the Cody boys together to keep the family enterprise going. Nicky gets into serious trouble when she tries to impress an old friend.

episodes.title: Wolves
episodes.description: With the cops on their tail, the Cody boys try to pull off their first heist without Smurf and Baz. They return to find unexpected guests waiting at home. Smurf demands that J get rid of them as she deals with a problem of her own in jail.

episodes.title: Prey
episodes.description: Deran gets to know his father Billy and helps J with a dilemma as Pearce closes in on Smurf's laundering operation. Craig uncovers a secret that sends him to Smurf and Nicky must decide whether she belongs in the Cody family or not.

episodes.title: Broke from the Box
episodes.description: J tries to make his relationship with Nicky work as he faces pressure from Smurf to clean up loose ends; Craig gathers the boys to defend the Cody's reputation in town when outsiders move in on their territory; Billy gives Deran an idea for a job.

episodes.title: Low Man
episodes.description: Deran leads the charge in planning the weed heist; Lucy calls Pope down to Mexico for some intel on Baz's murder; J reaches a breaking point with Smurf; Craig learns more about Billy's girlfriend, Frankie.

episodes.title: Incoming
episodes.description: The weed heist goes awry and leaves J and Deran stranded. Pope and Billy butt heads as Craig tries to keep the peace between them. Smurf learns about what J has been hiding from her since she's been away.

episodes.title: Libertad
episodes.description: A decision from Deran's past comes back to haunt him. J works to get back into Smurf's good graces as she tries to take away his control over the family business. Billy uses his past with Smurf to his advantage.

episodes.title: Off the Tit
episodes.description: Tensions run high as Billy pressures the family to give him what he's owed. Craig has a surprise meeting that makes him reconsider his future. The Cody boys struggle to hold onto the freedom they had when Smurf was in jail.

episodes.title: Jackpot
episodes.description: Smurf enlists the boys in a surprise job that results in devastating consequences; Pope is forced to confront the truth about Baz's murder as J steps up for the family in an unexpected way.

episodes.title: Homecoming
episodes.description: The Cody family picks up the pieces from their showdown with Lucy; Smurf becomes determined to reel Pope back into the fold at any cost; J goes to extreme lengths to protect a secret.

episodes.title: The Hyenas
episodes.description: J realizes the danger of balancing his role in the family with his personal ambitions. Deran wants to take his relationship with Adrian to the next level, but it’s not as easy as he hoped.

episodes.title: Janine
episodes.description: Season 4 starts as the Codys pull off a risky robbery. Smurf and Pope remain at odds even as Pope finds a new outlet for his anger. Deran involves Adrian in the family business, and J tests the waters of his new identity outside the family.

episodes.title: Angela
episodes.description: J reconsiders his relationship with Smurf after he gets bad news about Morgan's death. Frankie lures Craig with the promise of another big score. The arrival of an old family friend surprises Pope.

episodes.title: Man vs. Rock
episodes.description: As Craig feels the pressure of pulling off Frankie’s increasingly complicated job, J grows frustrated with Mia. Deran tries to get Pope out of the house, and Smurf decides she needs answers.

episodes.title: Tank
episodes.description: Smurf's increasingly unnerving behavior shows up in unexpected places. J realizes he needs to set his own plans in motion if he wants to lead the family. Deran gets disturbing news from an old friend; and Pope struggles to resist Angela.

episodes.title: Reap
episodes.description: Pope learns disturbing details about where Smurf has been, and the revelation puts Angela's spot in the house in jeopardy. Adrian's return to Oceanside leads to a confrontation with Deran, as J lays the groundwork for a new job.

episodes.title: Into the Black
episodes.description: Suspicion grows when Smurf learns of a new threat to the family. Craig tracks down Frankie in the wake of her betrayal, and Deran makes a dangerous decision to try and protect his relationship with Adrian.

episodes.title: Know Thy Enemy
episodes.description: J gains favor with Smurf as he puts together the plan for a new job, while Angela learns more about what Smurf’s been hiding. Craig explores his new relationship with Renn and Pope struggles with his changing role in the family.

episodes.title: Ambo
episodes.description: The Codys head out for a big job, even though Smurf is nowhere to be found. All eyes are on J as he assumes a leadership position in a risky heist.

episodes.title: SHTF
episodes.description: J faces the consequences of his missteps with Mia. Pope worries about Smurf's disappearance, while Smurf visits someone from her past. Craig grows frustrated with Deran's secrecy after Deran recruits him for a dangerous assignment.

episodes.title: Exit Strategy
episodes.description: Smurf orders the Cody boys to plan a dangerous job while she orchestrates an elaborate party at the house. J tries to ally himself with Pope, but learns he’s in way over his head. Craig responds to a challenge to his newly formed family with Renn.

episodes.title: Julia
episodes.description: Pope grows suspicious of J when Angela reveals the circumstances of her disappearance. As the threats against Adrian loom larger, Deran scrambles to find a way out. Craig navigates new complications in his relationship with Renn. Janine takes on a different role in the crew’s latest heist as she plans for her future with Colin.

episodes.title: Ghosts
episodes.description: The Cody family sets off on Smurf’s mysterious heist, unaware of the surprises that await them when they arrive, which will change the family forever.

episodes.title: Smurf
episodes.description: In the aftermath of Smurf’s heist, the Codys have to protect their reputation, while friends and enemies from the past close in. Deran realizes there is only one way to keep Adrian safe. Craig struggles to adapt to a new pace of life as Pope and J’s growing tension reaches a boiling point.

episodes.title: Red Handed
episodes.description: Dealing with the blowback from Season 4, the Codys are forced to tie up some loose ends with the cousins and figure out what the family looks like without Smurf.

episodes.title: What Remains
episodes.description: As Pope deals with Smurf's remains, Craig and Renn balance their old lives with being new parents. J finds a new job through an old contact, and Deran can't outrun his past with Adrian.

episodes.title: Freeride
episodes.description: J's business secrets come to light as Pope mourns the loss of Smurf. Deran distracts himself from his own loneliness. Craig and Renn struggle to find work-life balance.

episodes.title: Power
episodes.description: Deran follows up on Smurf's will and grows frustrated with J calling the shots. Pope's mental state is fragile and Craig must deal with being a solo dad as Renn goes back to work.

episodes.title: Family Business
episodes.description: As Deran and J compete for control of the family, Pamela presents the Codys with a risky proposition. Pope processes an additional loss by exploding in violence and Craig does business with Frankie.

episodes.title: Home Sweet Home
episodes.description: Tensions rise as Deran, J, and Craig do a job that risks everything the family has. Pope goes to the desert trying to outrun his grief.

episodes.title: Splinter
episodes.description: Pope confronts his demons with the help of a desert guru. Deran marks his territory as J handles business. Craig struggles with the demands of fatherhood and the temptations of his old life.

episodes.title: Gladiators
episodes.description: Pope helps a new friend. Deran, J, and Craig deal with the fallout from past mistakes as they make new friends and enemies.

episodes.title: Let It Ride
episodes.description: Local law enforcement turn up the heat on the Codys, as further secrets threaten to destabilize the family. Deran gets some news about Adrian. Craig discovers Renn has been keeping a secret.

episodes.title: Relentless
episodes.description: Desperate for cash, and with pressure mounting, the Codys discover what they thought was a solution to their problems may be the biggest threat of them all.

episodes.title: Trust the Process
episodes.description: J and Pope take a road trip to clean up the aftermath of some family business that went sideways. Deran and Craig scout a new mark with the help of Frankie.

episodes.title: Loose Ends
episodes.description: The Codys resolve unfinished business and plan their biggest heist ever without Smurf.

episodes.title: Launch
episodes.description: It's all hands on deck as the Cody family uses all their tools, tricks, and vehicles to pull off the job of their lives and settle all scores. A deadly secret from the past is also revealed. Season finale.

Gia visits the Codys with a job opportunity. J schemes finances. Deran learns new renters are disrupting the neighborhood. Craig struggles with sobriety and co-parenting Nick under Renn’s monitored visitation.

episodes.title: Rise
episodes.description: J holds a family meeting, on the hunt for a new attorney. Pope refuses to sell his vacant lot. Deran embraces his clout. Craig’s sobriety is challenged. In 1992, Smurf & Andrew meet with a lawyer. Julia struggles to be heard in the family.

episodes.title: Pressure and Time
episodes.description: Deran and Pope search for Craig. J tries to sell Gia’s diamonds. Much to Smurf’s displeasure, Julia gets a job at the mall and Andrew embraces Church.

episodes.title: Inside Man
episodes.description: J gets to know the new attorney while Craig scouts a potential new job. Deran hangs out with a guy from out of town. Pope helps a kid at the skate park. In 1992, Baz visits Andrew’s Church.

episodes.title: Covet
episodes.description: The Codys prep for the next job in present day. A reluctant Andrew, Baz, and Julia do a job for Smurf in 92.

episodes.title: Diamonds Are Forever
episodes.description: The Codys stage a jewel robbery. Craig and Deran are at odds. In 1992, Julia and Baz spend more time together.

episodes.title: Incognito
episodes.description: Pope prepares to see an old friend. Craig needs Deran’s help when Nick’s in trouble. J pursues Penny romantically. Andrew wants to be called Pope.

episodes.title: Revelation
episodes.description: Deran and J consider a small job. Craig, Renn, and Nick spend the day together as a family. Pope senses something is off. Andrew finds out about Julia.

episodes.title: Gethsemane
episodes.description: Pope is brought in for questioning. J, Deran, and Craig grapple with the truth. Julia tries to make amends with an upset Andrew.

episodes.title: Clink
episodes.description: Pope is self-destructive. J, Craig, and Deran must figure out what they’re going to do about him. Julia and Andrew work together on a job.

episodes.title: Hit and Run
episodes.description: Pope is sent to solitary confinement. Deran gets a visit from an old friend. J, Craig, and Deran decide what to do about Pope. Julia confronts Baz.

episodes.title: Exodus
episodes.description: Pope offers information on a cold case in exchange for a prison transfer. Deran says goodbye to the bar, J makes plans with Penny, and Craig chooses Renn and Nick. Smurf learns Julia has been dishonest.

episodes.title: Fubar
episodes.description: The Cody boys embark on their most dangerous job yet. Andrew commits the original sin that destroyed the family.

episodes.title: Episode 1
episodes.description: Anamika’s sudden disappearance launches an investigation. Flashes of the preceding weeks reveal her strained marriage and a troubling incident at home.

episodes.title: Episode 2
episodes.description: As public concern for Anamika grows, Avi suspects Nikhil while Shobha distrusts Manish. Amara recalls Anamika’s concern over her acting aspirations.

episodes.title: Episode 3
episodes.description: Shobha questions Nikhil’s film financier. In flashbacks, truths emerge about Anamika’s wealth and Manish’s diagnosis. Anamika wonders what Avi is hiding.

episodes.title: Episode 4
episodes.description: Earlier weeks reveal Anamika's growing defiance and an altercation that leaves Avi distraught. In the present, Billy begins his own search for Anamika.

episodes.title: Episode 5
episodes.description: Shobha’s alarming discovery spawns more arguments within the family. In the past, pressure pushes Amara near a breaking point and Anamika faces danger.

episodes.title: Episode 6
episodes.description: A visit to Manish’s farmhouse gives Anamika clarity. In the present day, amid news of a murder, a music launch for Anamika and Manish’s film turns tense.

episodes.title: Episode 7
episodes.description: The police team rushes to track down the site of an alarming clue. Shobha urges Avi to tell her what he knows — and he lets damning family secrets spill.

episodes.title: Episode 8
episodes.description: A sad development stokes public frenzy. While Shobha can't shake a gut feeling on Anamika's whereabouts, someone else knows more than they let on.

episodes.title: Episode 7
episodes.description: Episode 7 of The Fame Game

episodes.title: Pilot
episodes.description: Ray Drecker is a struggling high school coach in Detroit who is descending to all-time lows in his professional and personal life. He attends a self-help group in a desperate attempt to find a plan for financial success. Tanya, an old flame, is also attending the self-help group and she gives Ray inspiration in an unexpected way.

episodes.title: 'Great Sausage' or 'Can I Call You Dick?'
episodes.description: Tanya enlists the help of a former colleague Lenore, who is now a professional shopper, so Ray can offer his services to her clientele of rich older women.

episodes.title: 'Strange Friends' or 'The Truth Is, You're Sexy'
episodes.description: Ray's life continues to frustrate: His neighbor Koontz is on his case for urinating in the lake; he and Jessica continue to argue over the best way to parent the twins; and it turns out Lenore has disappeared, along with his wallet.

episodes.title: The Pickle Jar
episodes.description: The students of Lakefield vote for Coach Drecker as their recipient for the fundraiser but Ray finds it embarrassing. Tanya has other ideas to boost Ray's career as a gigolo.

episodes.title: Do it, Monkey
episodes.description: A client who is unhappy wants to revisit a role-playing fantasy; Ray promises a car for Damon and Darby, to capitalize on Jessica's frugality. Reluctantly, Tanya agrees to go on a date with Floyd.

episodes.title: 'Doris is Dead' or 'Are We Rich or Are We Poor?'
episodes.description: Tanya objects to the break in protocol after Jemma bypasses her to set up "dates" directly with Ray. Jessica confronts Ronnie about their finances, but he refuses to give her a straight answer. After Jemma prods Ray to open up about himself, he gives his basketball team an inspiring pep talk.

episodes.title: The Rita Flower or The Indelible Stench
episodes.description: Ray starts to fall for Jemma, which clouds their professional relationship. Tanya receives unexpected help for her writer's block. Jessica invites Ray to a family dinner.

episodes.title: "Thith ith a Prothetic" or "You Cum Just Right"
episodes.description: After standing him up, Jemma tells Ray they should take a break, and Ray seeks out Tanya for advice on women. Ray finds himself in an uncomfortable situation at Jessica and Ronnie's family barbeque.

episodes.title: This Is America or Fifty Bucks
episodes.description: Tanya pitches Happiness Consultants to other women in her office, with mixed results. Damon goes to detention to hang out with his androgynous friend, leaving Ray baffled. Lenore gives Ray some lessons in branding and, after a chance encounter at a department store, offers Jessica some lifestyle advice.

episodes.title: A Dick and a Dream or Fight the Honey
episodes.description: Tanya worries that Lenore may stage a coup for control of Ray, who is unnerved by rumors of layoffs at his school.

episodes.title: Just the Tip
episodes.description: Ray, Tanya and Lenore's new partnership starts inauspiciously when Ray "holds back" during a tryst with a pregnant client.

episodes.title: Tuscon Is the Gateway to Dick
episodes.description: Ray irritates Lenore and risks losing a client by giving Claire marriage advice. Tanya tries to prove she can land a big fish for Ray after being humiliated by Lenore during a meeting with a 60-year-old widow. Ray uses his sex earnings to pay for the school baseball team’s transportation to away games, raising Mike’s suspicions. Jessica embarrasses Darby by crashing an eat-in protest outside a fitness gym. At the end of a long day, Ray reconsiders accepting a gift delivered by his neighbor’s wife, Yael.

episodes.title: "Mind Bullets" or "Bang Bang Bang Motherfu**er
episodes.description: Spurred by criticism from Damon and Darby, Ray tries to prove he's not an insensitive ex-jock. Seething from the demands of her new boss at work, Tanya turns to Charlie for advice on how to deal with an even more irritable problem: Lenore. Meanwhile, Jessica feels the pinch of the economic downturn, but can't stomach Ronnie's remedy.

episodes.title: "Sing It Again Ray" or "Home Plate"
episodes.description: Ray gives Lenore an ultimatum, and probes Tanya about the possibility of cutting ties with her fellow pimp. Disturbed that Damon has defiled the school baseball diamond, Ray considers Tanya's suggestion that his son find a new hobby to shake him out of his recent doldrums. Ignoring Ray's warning, Lenore offers Jessica advice in dealing with Ronnie. On his way to meet a new client, Ray has to think on his feet when he runs into Mike in a hotel lobby.

episodes.title: 'A Man, A Plan' or 'Thank You, Jimmy Carter'
episodes.description: Tanya finally gets Francis to agree to dinner with Ray and Lenore is continuing to be a pest as usual. Ray can tell that Mike is struggling to not continue with his life and tells that he needs to look at himself and tell himself that he is wonderful. Damon goes back to the Poetry Bar and embarrasses Darby after which he has a performance "enhancing" scone and sees Jessica and Ronnie naked. Ray has to choose whether to cancel on the big client or his son who needs him.

episodes.title: Beaverland
episodes.description: Jessica turns to Ray for help with a rodent problem that may be imaginary. Rebuffed by Ray in her attempts to add Mike to her stable, Tanya gets guilt-management advice from Charlie (Lennie James), then goes to extremes to prove her success. Ray has difficulty thawing a client who is cold as ice.

episodes.title: The Middle East Is Complicated
episodes.description: Ray must choose sides between Yael and a new client; Tanya turns to Charlie for stress relief; Lenore learns of Tanya's duplicity; Liz surprises Ray with a revelation about her personal life.

episodes.title: "Third Base" or "The Rash"
episodes.description: Ray's unscheduled appointment with Claire threatens his participation in a student-alumni baseball game; Frances has doubts about her affair with Mike and her business relationship with Tanya; Ronnie delivers a stern message to Ray.

episodes.title: 'Fat Off My Love' or 'I'm The Allergen'
episodes.description: Mike accuses Ray of betraying him; Ronnie has a big fight with Jessica at the dermatologists' banquet; Tanya gets things off her chest when she goes into confessional mode and tells Ray, Lenore and Horny Patty exactly what she thinks of them.

episodes.title: 'Even Steven' or 'Luckiest Kid in Detroit'
episodes.description: Ray considers leaving the business; Tanya is emotionally frayed after encounters with Damon and Vera-Joan; Jessica makes a decision about the future.

episodes.title: 'Don't Give Up on Detroit' or 'Hung Like a Horse'
episodes.description: Ray and Tanya must convince a bank officer and her friend that their "Wellness Center for Women" idea is financially sound. Lenore discovers a new prospect to rival Ray.

episodes.title: 'Take the Cake' or 'Are You Packing?'
episodes.description: Tanya takes matters into her own hands after Jason steals one of Ray's clients. Lenore discovers some surprising news about Jason. Meanwhile, Jessica tries living on her own, and Charlie asks Tanya for a favor. Ray works with a new client who likes to dress up as a cop.

episodes.title: 'Mister Drecker' or 'Ease Up on the Whup-Ass'
episodes.description: Ray worries that his cover might be blown when he confuses one of his former students with a client. Tanya finds her self taking care of a convicted felon, and Jess takes a job working the Dr. Matt Kopylov's office, the husband of Ronnie's mistress. Lenore makes a deal with Jason's fiancée, Sandee.

episodes.title: 'F*ck Me, Mr. Drecker' or 'Let's Not Go to Jail'
episodes.description: Ray and Tanya conspire to get rid of an explosive client. Charlie advises Tanya to keep Lydia happy. Lenore manages Sandee's rising demands, and Matt and Jessica bond.

episodes.title: 'We're Golden' or 'Crooks and Big Beaver'
episodes.description: After Ray tells Lydia he's leaving the business, she takes Ray and Tanya on a ride they will never forget. Darby threatens to leave home, and Lenore confronts Jason about missing a date with a client.

episodes.title: 'Money on the Floor'
episodes.description: When his shoebox of cash goes missing, Ray goes after the prime suspect: Lenore. His investigation lands him a brand new client named Kyla. Meanwhile, Sandee offers Tanya the opportunity to expand her business.

episodes.title: 'What's Going on Downstairs?' or 'Don't Eat Prince Eric!'
episodes.description: Ray’s night with Kyla leaves him wondering who she really is; a competition develops at the Wellness Center; Tanya gets help from Charlie in finding out what happened to Ray’s money.

episodes.title: 'I, Sandee' or 'This Sex. Which Is. Not One.'
episodes.description: Tanya discovers that Charlie has skipped bail, and she asks Missy, the mother of Charlie's child, to help locate him. Lenore declares war on Tanya and the Wellness Center, and Sandee tries to position Jason to take Ray's spot. Ray faces concerns about his ability to satisfy women, particularly Jessica.

episodes.title: 'A Monkey Named Simian' or 'Frances is Not a Fan'
episodes.description: The guest list for Frances and Mike's wedding doesn't include Tanya; Ray takes back what was his after a physical confrontation with Jason; Tanya finds a connection with Charlie's kids.

episodes.title: The Whole Beefalo
episodes.description: The survival of Tanya and Ray's business depends on Charlie's whereabouts; Jessica is accused of negligence by Matt; and Lenore tries to get Sandee out of the picture for good.

episodes.title: Artist
episodes.description: To save his beloved grandpa's printing press from going under, brilliant artist Sunny comes up with an ingenious but dangerous plan. A determined officer, Michael, corners his arch-nemesis, counterfeiting kingpin Mansoor Dalal.

episodes.title: Social Service
episodes.description: Sunny's plan works, but there is no end to greed. Michael tries to get an anti-counterfeiting task force sanctioned. Megha’s passion project has no takers among the powers that be.

episodes.title: CCFART
episodes.description: CCFART is formed. Sunny and Firoz accept a deal almost too large for them. Michael gate-crashes his son’s birthday party even though he is not invited. Michael hires Megha, but she steps on a few toes trying to track down the ‘artist’ who made the sandwich note.

episodes.title: Dhanrakshak
episodes.description: Dhanrakshak is launched, a huge victory for CCFART. Michael’s attempts to reconcile with his wife only push her further away. A rattled Sunny looks for his missing Grandpa, with no help from the inept bureaucracy. Mansoor’s operations are threatened by Dhanrakshak, and he needs a new note that can fool the new scanner.

episodes.title: Second Oldest Profession
episodes.description: Sunny cracks the Supernote. Michael gets a breakthrough in Bangladesh. Mansoor feels pressure from his bosses, and wants Sunny to take on a bigger role in his organisation. Megha finally finds someone she might be romantically interested in.

episodes.title: Cat and Mouse
episodes.description: Sunny has a mole in CCFART. Michael has a mole in Mansoor's organisation. Sunny adopts a risky plan, "Trojan Horse" to smuggle a huge shipment of notes to India.

episodes.title: Supernote
episodes.description: Sunny and Firoz love living the high life, as Sunny finds himself falling in love with Megha. Megha uncovers an important secret about the Supernote. Michael does something unorthodox to spur Minister Gahlot into action. Mansoor desperately needs to bring the cash into market.

episodes.title: Crash and Burn
episodes.description: A trap is laid! Sunny and Firoz almost get caught. Michael, not one to give up, has yet another plan! Mansoor's very existence is at stake. Megha is very close to uncovering a devastating truth. Sunny pays a price too heavy for his tryst with crime.

episodes.title: Episode 7
episodes.description: Episode 7 of Farzi

episodes.title: Lawless Law Firm
episodes.description: Bong Sang Pil is known as the gangster lawyer. He is known to fight with his fist and the law. After hearing news that Cha Moon Sook was appointed as judge for the retrial of the murder of the mayor of Giseong, Lee Young Soo, Sang Pil decides to return to his hometown for the first time in 18 years. Meanwhile, Ha Jae I punches a judge for a wrongful verdict. She ends up getting suspended and returns home after getting fired from her law firm.

episodes.title: The Hearing
episodes.description: After returning to Kiseong, Sang Pil takes over the office that his mother, a civil rights lawyer, used to use. He keeps busy trying to get the chance to defend Hyung Man for the murder of Kiseong's Mayor, Lee Young Soo. Jae I begins to wonder why Sang Pil is so determined to work on this case. She begins to look into it to find out. The day of the hearing is finally here, and Jae I faces danger on her way to the courthouse. Will Sang Pil go to rescue her?

episodes.title: I’m Going to be Arrested Today
episodes.description: After saving Jae I, Sang Pil and Jae I arrive at the courthouse. Sang Pil reveals a shocking truth that changes the conditions of the trial. However, Sang Pil ends up getting arrested for disrupting the trial. While Sang Pil is in prison, Jae I begins to look into the truth behind Mayor Lee Young Soo's murder case. Jae I begins to see Sang Pil in a different light. Meanwhile, Sang Pil agonizes over how to tell Jae I the truth about her mother.

episodes.title: Prove It to Me
episodes.description: Sang Pil devises a plan to ruin An Oh Ju's chances of becoming mayor. Jae I begins to get suspicious of Sang Pil as he seems to be going overboard. She wonders why he seems to be targeting Moon Sook and Oh Ju for no reason. She goes to visit Hyung Man in prison and finds out a shocking truth. Meanwhile, Moon Sook attends an event for the unveiling of her father's statue at Kiseong District Court.

episodes.title: I Came Here For A Reason
episodes.description: Sang Pil and Moon Sook face each other after revealing who they are. Sang Pil tells Moon Sook that he will see this case through. However, Moon Sook is not affected by his declaration. Jae I sees the two of them talking and is shocked to hear the truth. She has a hard time believing what she saw and starts to look into Moon Sook on her own. Sang Pil feels bad about Jae I and keeps an eye on her. Jae I finally finds out the truth about what happened 18 years, but it ends up causing her more trouble.

episodes.title: I’ll Keep Your Promise
episodes.description: Sang Pil tells Jae I about the true face of Moon Sook. Sang Pil and Jae I work together to prove Young Man is not guilty of murdering the mayor Lee Young Soo. Young Man finds out Jae I is Hyun Joo’s daughter. Yeon Hee asks Moon Sook for forgiveness.

episodes.title: Wake Up
episodes.description: Oh Ju has finally accomplished his old desire. He starts to begin the Golden City redevelopment project. Meanwhile, he tries to take revenge on Hyung Man, who puts him in trouble. Sang Pil and Jae I try to stop Oh Ju from doing so. Sang Pil and Jae I versus Moon Sook and Oh Ju begins now.

episodes.title: Hold On
episodes.description: Jae I runs into Hyun Joo, her mother, in 18 years, but doesn’t recognize her. Dae Woong finds out that Hyun Joo has moved back to Kiseong, so he decides to move to Kiseong to meet Oh Ju. Meanwhile, due to Sang Pil's action, Oh Ju fails to keep his shares, so he decides to revenge on Sang Pil in a cruel way.

episodes.title: Fighting from the Inside Out
episodes.description: Sang Pil, who succumbs to Mayor An’s evil plot, now faces murder charges for Dae Woong’s death. Sang Pil and his supporters all fight to prove Sang Pil’s innocence but face unexpected circumstances in court that keeps Attorney Ha on her toes. To make matters worse, Sang Pil is confronted by an old acquaintance that puts him fighting for his life.

episodes.title: Keep Your Enemies Close
episodes.description: Jae I is torn to see her love, Sang Pil, sustain injuries and visits him frequently at the hospital. Sang Pil again faces adversaries and fights to see Jae I one more time. The war between the oppressor and the oppressed deepens while new alliances form. The trial for the murder of Choi Dae Woong continues with the most unpredicted witness taking the stand.

episodes.title: New Alliances
episodes.description: Sang Pil is acquitted of murder at Mayor An’s shocking testimony. Sang Pil is released with all charges dismissed and regroups with the Lawless Law Firm to carry on with his revenge. Meanwhile, Judge Cha’s acceptance of chief justice causes Nam Soon Ja, Judge Cha’s personal secretary, to worry about her daughter’s future. Judge Cha faces the onslaught of the media when an anonymously sent picture with her surfaces; possibly putting her in connection with the disappearance of Han Cheol Kyu, the union president of the Golden City Project.

episodes.title: Wars are Fought with Swords
episodes.description: After sustaining an attack from a defendant’s father, whose son was sentenced to death, Judge Cha slips out of the media’s suspicions regarding the photo. Meanwhile, Bong Sang Pil finds out the true identity of Mama and does not share it with Jae I. Bong Sang Pil finds crucial evidence linking Mayor An to the Choi Dae Woong murder case and uses it put Mayor An in quite the predicament.

episodes.title: Play Your Cards When You Can
episodes.description: Bong Sang Pil now knows who had sent him the notebook and who is playing what hand. He uses this knowledge and devises a plan to ruin Judge Cha’s escape and save Jae I’s mother from murder. Overnight, Mayor An becomes the main suspect in Choi Dae Woong’s murder case due to Gwan Dong’s recorded message and looks to team up with Jae I to bury the past. Meanwhile, Jae I is still upset with Bong Sang Pil for not telling her about her mother and unforgivingly pursues her mother’s whereabouts without him.

episodes.title: I Want to Make a Deal with You
episodes.description: Thanks to Sang Pil’s efforts, Jae I and her father are reunited with her mother after 18 years. Sang Pil’s final plan to bring down Chan Sook goes into effect. Soon Ja is arrested and facing trial when she realizes that Chan Sook has cut her loose. She gets a tempting offer from Sang Pil. Meanwhile, Oh Ju, who is on the run, faces off with Sang Pil after abducting Jae I.

episodes.title: Loyalty Means Nothing
episodes.description: An Oh Ju, who is still being chased by the police, kidnaps Jae I to draw Sang Pil to him. Sang Pil rushes to Jae I and confronts An Oh Ju with vengeance but not without a plan to win him over for his end game. Things heat up in the trial for the murder of the Thai accupressurist as Judge Cha sits as the presiding judge. The defendant, Nam Soon Ja, looks to Sang Pil and Jae I to show their skills as lawyers to bail her out of her predicament, but ultimately, it is her testimony that will determine her fate.

episodes.title: The Final Testimony
episodes.description: In the trial against Nam Soon Ja, Bong Sang Pil and Ha Jae I work together to finalize their revenge where the unthinkable takes place. New witnesses and evidence emerge as Judge Cha squirms to get free of any accusations thrown by the “lawless” couple. Judge Cha does all she can to remove those who can testify against her in and out of the courtroom—including Nam Soon Ja. But is that enough? At the turning point of the trial, Nam Soon Ja agonizes over choosing the right side that will determine her fate and the fate of her daughter.

episodes.title: A Runaway Life
episodes.description: Seher flees to Mumbai after a fight with Rana. She crashes an auction in Kamathipura, run by Resham and Habiba. Amid chaos over missing Neeti, Seher seizes her chance to present herself, defying Raju's earlier refusal.

episodes.title: Shadows At Play
episodes.description: Seher saves Neeti from Akram's men but is shot. Baburao wins auction. Dr. Anand treats Seher, warns her to flee. Suraiyya caught escaping village. Quadir bribes Inspector Satpute. Seher's fate hangs in balance.

episodes.title: Hunter And Prey
episodes.description: Akram hunts Seher. Dhananjay tortures Suraiyya for Seher's whereabouts. Baburao meets Ivy in Bangkok, plans to meet Chao Fa. Seher finds ally in Sattar. Raju bribes Inspector Satpute to eliminate Seher.

episodes.title: Tale Of Betrayal
episodes.description: Police raid brothels for Seher. Dhananjay torments Suraiyya as Rana's health worsens. Seher escapes, accidentally kills Gafoor. Champa sells Seher to Habiba. Quadir favors Akram in lane distribution, angering Baburao post-Thailand trip.

episodes.title: Secrets And Chains
episodes.description: Flashback reveals Baburao's rise in Kamathipura. Seher learns Champa sold her. Sattar takes ill Champa to Dr. Anand. Baburao starts massage parlor with Thai girls. Quadir investigates Gafoor's murder. Seher rescues minor children with Sattar and Inspector Prabha's help.

episodes.title: Battle To Survive
episodes.description: Minors' rescue revealed. Akram shoots Gotya, blaming Baburao for Gafoor's death. Dhananjay misinformed of Seher's death. Habiba bailed; Prabha warned. Sattar and Seher fall in love. Baburao claims innocence to Quadir. Seher finds Champa dead.

episodes.title: Memories And Scars
episodes.description: Flashback shows Seher-Champa bond. Seher informs Sattar of Champa's death. Dhananjay's men find Seher's photo. Baburao opens parlor with Ivy. Quadir requests meeting. Sattar shows Seher Mumbai. Seher calls Suraiyya; Dhananjay attacks her mid-call.

episodes.title: The Final Showdown
episodes.description: Dhananjay intercepts Seher's call. Power struggles in Kamathipura intensify. Sattar has accident. Dhananjay kills Raju, seeks Seher. Resham plots against Akram. At cremation, chaos erupts. Season ends with Seher, Akram, and Quadir in armed standoff.

episodes.title: The Puzzle
episodes.description: When Sagar the Chief Editor of ‘Samacharam’ newspaper, finds a crossword puzzle in a dhaba. The puzzle predicts a terrifying incident that would occur in his life.

episodes.title: Editorial Cartoon
episodes.description: Police Detective Kranthi Shenoy is given the suicide case of a popular journalist. While investigating she suspects foul play. Ajay Ghosh under Sagar’s instruction, interrogates Koti which leads to more problems.

episodes.title: Horoscope
episodes.description: Suicide investigation leads Kranthi to gun smuggling racket which eventually leads to the disappearance of Koti. Koti’s truck being involved in the accident, brings Sagar and Ajay Ghosh into the investigation’s purview. During the launch of ‘Samacharam’s’ first copy, Sagar receives a mysterious message in the form of old newspaper scrap.

episodes.title: Crime Report
episodes.description: While Sagar and Ajay Ghosh discuss recent events, they find a clue from the old newspaper scrap which drives their investigation further. Kranti and Ranga discover a connection between the case and Sagar’s farm house. The suspense continues to build.

episodes.title: Page 3
episodes.description: As Kranthi and Ranga continue the investigations they find an unexpected dead body. Sagar follows Kiran Reddy, the research head and host for the YouTube show "Ghost Shadows," and learns about Ravi’s research into journalist’s suicide. Sagar gets a newspaper scrap with yet another ominous prediction.

episodes.title: This Day, That Year
episodes.description: As Kranthi’s investigative net tightens around Sagar, he decides to visit Dhootha Publications in an attempt to unravel the mystery behind Sathyamurthy’s book. The story delves into a shocking past. With this information Sagar goes to the light house, closing in on the truth.

episodes.title: Continued on Page 6
episodes.description: As deaths continue, Sagar is forewarned about an impending danger to his family, he comes clean to Kranthi and together they race against time to stop the newspapers’ deadly prediction.

episodes.title: Headlines
episodes.description: Priya becomes the target of a mysterious killer. As the events unfold, Sagar’s past and family secrets comes to light, Kranti begins to connect the dots to uncover the truth.

episodes.description: Episode 5 of Dhootha

episodes.title: Super Sidey
episodes.description: On the first day of 9th standard, Samvidhan Sharma, the eternal sidekick finally gets a chance to speak to his crush and the school’s prettiest girl Jasmine. But things take a turn for the worse, when Jasmine’s best friend and sidekick Aadhya, accuses him of cheating.

episodes.title: Crime And Punishment
episodes.description: After a complaint to their strict school principal, Samvidhan and Prateek are not allowed to perform their rap on the Founder’s Day of Lucknow Central Convent school. Samvidhan assumes that Aadhya has made the complaint and has a huge showdown with her. But this misunderstanding leads to an unexpected friendship. Could this be the start of a new romance between the two sidekicks?

episodes.title: Bulati Hai Magar...
episodes.description: Aadhya and Sam form an organic connection and discover they have a lot in common. The once-enemies now talk all day on their phones and through hidden messages left in their favourite book in the school library for each other. When they team up for a flying model competition, their chemistry only gets stronger. But does Aadhya have the same feelings about Sam, or is he just another friend?

episodes.title: Maa Ki Aankh
episodes.description: Sam realises that he is in love for the first time and decides to propose to her. As Aadhya's strict mother Vandita joins school as a substitute teacher, bad timing and luck continue to be his fatal foes. As a worried Aadhya distances herself from Sam, and misunderstandings follow, Sam becomes anxious about Aadhya's blossoming friendship with Sahil, the most popular senior and aspiring poet.

episodes.title: Mera Pehla Pehla Valentine Hai
episodes.description: Students and teachers alike, including Sam and Aadhya, are prepping for their Valentine's Day dates at Lucknow Central Convent. However, Aadhya's father's sudden visit on February 14th throws Sam and Aadhya's preparations into chaos. Will Aadhya be able to make it to Sam's romantic night packed of surprises, or will another surprise catch them off guard and them to question their relationship?

episodes.title: Final Exam
episodes.description: When Sahil, the most popular senior in school, becomes a huge bone of contention between Sam and Aadhya, Sam decides to break up with Aadhya, leaving her completely shocked and confused. All this right in the middle of their final exams. Will Sam ever be able to get over his insecurities and stop comparing his sidekick self to Sahil or will he let go of his first love?

episodes.title: Sam Kahan Hai?
episodes.description: As the school reopens after summer vacations, Aadhya is confronted with some harsh realities, and Sahil is appointed as the leader of the delegation to represent LCC at Celesta Interschool Cultural Festival that is to be hosted by current champions and archrivals Francis Convent School. While Aadhya tries to cope and deal with the shock, something is brewing to heal her. But will that be enough?

episodes.title: Naam Wahi, Dosti Nayi
episodes.description: In their first interaction, Aadhya declines the help offered by Samarth. On the other hand, while Prateek's and Zoya's differences come out into the open as Sahil begins auditioning for Celesta, Jaz finds an opportunity to get closer to Sahil. As the team brainstorms on the topic for Triveni, the main event of Celesta, Aadhya recognises a friend in Samarth.

episodes.title: Emotions Ki Wrong Delivery
episodes.description: While Sahil struggles to assert control over his indisciplined team and finds a friend in Jaz who motivates him, Aadhya faces embarrassment at school due to a personal message getting leaked, which she blames Samarth for. Feeling dejected by him, she finds a friend in her mother who helps her understand things in context while Samarth gets into his first school fight.

episodes.title: Chemistry
episodes.description: Aadhya reaches out and mends things with Samarth. Sahil gets a hint of how Jaz feels about him and Prateek learns his lesson as Jaz and Zoya indulge in a catfight as they audition for debate team on the topic of love. While Prateek and Zoya patch up and Aadhya and Sahil engage in a bitter argument, Father Lawrence announces a mandatory test for all team members to retain their place in the team.

episodes.title: Time Time Ki Baat Hai
episodes.description: As the practise sessions extend beyond school hours, Zoya encourages Jaz to express her feelings for Sahil. Samarth makes Aadhya sneak out of school and surprises her only to be surprised himself. The LCC team suffers a last minute setback as they lose a topic to Francis Convent due to late submission.

episodes.title: Winners and Losers
episodes.description: Team LCC manages to find a topic after a last-minute setback but finds itself on slippery ground as the cracks within the team widen and they lag behind on the points table.While Sahil finds a way to keep the team united and competitive, Samarth realises the stakes on his shoulders for the team's victory.The competition closes with a surprise as our characters are confronted with revelations.

episodes.title: Azaadi
episodes.description: With the board exams concluding, Father Lawrence offers the students of standards 11 and 12 to use their summer holidays for an exciting summer exchange programme- Young Tarang, at Don Roberts School, Dehradun, which brings a smile to Aadhya's face, and she gets on to the task of persuading Zoya and Jaz, who are unsure about the trip.

episodes.title: Ice Breaker
episodes.description: Aadhya and Samarth reunite after manoeuvring through months of long-distance relationship, and are set to finally spend some quality time with each other as others forge some new associations at summer camp.

episodes.title: Surprise Ya Shock
episodes.description: Samarth tries to plan the best birthday for Aadhya, full of surprises. However, little does he know that while his best efforts seem to fall flat, he'll eventually be left shocked himself.

episodes.title: Saavdhaani Hati Durghatna Ghati
episodes.description: As Samarth tries hard to recover from the shock, his equation with Aadhya continues to go downhill. While Aadhya tries her best to make the most of her time with Samarth by managing to get him inducted as a volunteer in Young Tarang, others in the group also struggle with their insecurities as new associations take over the existing bonds.

episodes.title: Dil Dosti Dooriyan
episodes.description: As the camp enters its final leg, on one hand, Aadhya and Samarth contemplate the future of their relationship, while on the other hand, some friends patch up to set out on a new adventure. However, things get worse when a few misadventures damage LCC's reputation, and they find themselves on the verge of a premature exit from the camp.

episodes.title: Picture Abhi Baaki Hai Mere Dost
episodes.description: The LCC gang survives the storm with some interference from their faculties and manages to conclude the summer camp successfully. However, as they are set to return to Lucknow, while some new friendships come to a sweet end, Aadhya and Samarth meet to discuss the future of their relationship. But little does Aadhya know that just when she feels that her life is driven by her decisions.

episodes.title: Meri Tumhari
episodes.description: Mala Kumari, a top-tier star in the Hindi film industry accuses reputed filmaker Divendu Khurana, of sexually assaulting her. As the court battle uncovers areas that are not all black and white, Kashaf attempts to find justice for Mala while Deepak defends Divendu Khurana in his plea for innocence.

episodes.title: Finisher
episodes.description: A 19-year-old engineering student brutally kills a cab driver. Despite it being an open and shut murder case, Kashaf takes it up and eventually finds the motive behind his act. Shubhangi, LN Khanna's granddaughter, joins Deepak's team against the will of her cousin, Shubhrat. An SMS that would damage the reputation of Kashaf's father, Justice Munawwar Quaze, goes viral.

episodes.title: Paani
episodes.description: Deepak is representing a cola company accused of causing a drought in a village in Maharashtra. Kashaf and Vandana are on the other side. Under pressure from Bhalla, Deepak hires a private investigator to dig deeper into the allegations against Justice Quaze. Deepak and Shubhangi start getting romantically involved. Shubhrat finds a way to damage Deepak's reputation in KKA.

episodes.title: Spermaa
episodes.description: A woman gets fired from a startup company on grounds of misconduct and behavioural issues. She approaches Kashaf and Vandana for legal help. Shubhrat Khanna's girlfriend, Ria Singh, breaks shocking news that damages the Quaze family's reputation. The environment at KKA becomes grim with the ever growing rivalry between Deepak and Shubhrat. Ria and Shubhrat decide to take Deepak down together.

episodes.title: Aalaap
episodes.description: A group of music directors decide to sue a guy who's come up with a music software that samples music from various songs to create a new song. Kashaf holds a press conference to prove her father's innocence. Deepak tries to rekindle old flames with Kashaf while on the music case in Mumbai... Abhijeet notices it all. Ria and Shubhrat make their first move on bringing Deepak down.

episodes.title: Ehno
episodes.description: Deepak hands over her first independent case to Shubhangi. She is to defend a driverless car company that's accused of causing an accident. A bitter Abhijeet opens up a can of worms about Deepak. Kashaf confronts her mother about a past incident that's haunted her. Ria goes to Himachal to dig deeper into the Bhalla case. Shubhangi sees Deepak and Kashaf together and gets upset.

episodes.title: Deep Waters
episodes.description: Deepak's brother-in-law seeks his help about a case which involves a Private Security Agent killing himself. Deepak takes the case to Kashaf and Vandana while LN Khanna and Shubhangi defend the private security company in an MP court. Bhalla warns Deepak to shut Ria Singh's investigation down. Shubhrat finds a 'nail in the coffin' moment to end Deepak's career in KKA.

episodes.title: Plan Your Baby
episodes.description: A couple accuses an IVF clinic of giving them a damaged embryo, resulting in their son being born with a disability. Kashaf manages to confront the demons from her past. Deepak goes back to his village to find out more about Bhalla's history. A powerful acquaintance of Bhalla gets involved in the case. Parvathy gives Deepak shocking information about the Quaze case.

episodes.title: Alola
episodes.description: Shubhangi takes up the case of her friends who want to sue a dating app for fraud and cheating. Shubhrat convinces Diraaj and Shamsher to fire Deepak from KKA. Justice Quaze gets a threat letter. He tells Kashaf about it and that Deepak is swimming with sharks in murky waters. She confronts Deepak about it.

episodes.title: Guilt
episodes.description: Kashaf decides to leave the Quaze house after getting some devastating information. Deepak goes to Mumbai in search of his childhood friend who might have more leads about the Bhalla case. Shubhrat calls for a meeting of the partners of KKA to vote Deepak out. Quaze gets another threat, this time with a casualty. A final verdict is given on the Bhalla case and consequences follow.

episodes.title: Almost Okay
episodes.description: When a suspicious shipwreck draws the eyes of the law, the fractured Buckley family must put aside their grievances to cover their tracks.

episodes.title: Taking Control
episodes.description: Cane and Harlan take bigger risks to keep the business running. Bree seeks proof to confirm her suspicions about her family.

episodes.title: Playing with Fire
episodes.description: As Harlan re-enters a risky alliance tied to the family's past, Belle makes quiet moves to protect what's left of their legacy.

episodes.title: You Can't Trust a Buckley
episodes.description: Cane works to contain the growing fallout at home. Harlan connects with a new player — and learns the rules of the game have changed.

episodes.title: I'm a Hugger
episodes.description: As pressure mounts and operations get riskier, Belle and Harlan struggle to keep a low profile. Old wounds resurface between Cane and Bree.

episodes.title: Hunting Season
episodes.description: Belle receives upsetting news about the family's future. A hunting trip troubles the fragile alliance between Harlan and Grady. Bree makes a confession.

episodes.title: Nice Try
episodes.description: Hoping to regain control of his operation, Harlan tries to outmaneuver an imminent threat. A violent warning shakes the Buckley family to its core.

episodes.title: Lost at Sea
episodes.description: As tensions flare, a dangerous standoff at sea brings the Buckleys face-to-face with their enemies.

episodes.title: Episode 9
episodes.description: Episode 9 of The Waterfront

episodes.title: Bhookha Shehar
episodes.description: The lives of two estranged friends, Jende, a cop, and Peter, a journalist, turn upside down with the murder of a gay sex worker at the Mahim toilet. This leads them to embark on a thrilling journey exploring the 'hungry' yet 'deadly' city of Mumbai.

episodes.title: Hisaab Barabar
episodes.description: As the murder of another victim sends shock waves around town, life brings Jende face-to-face with Peter, as he is suspicious of Sunil's being involved in the crime. To add to this, Sunil has also been missing for a few days.

episodes.title: Baap Bada Ya Beta
episodes.description: A serial killer is on the loose, and the next target is the cop itself. While stress levels rise at work, Jende's conflict with his father intensifies, distancing him from his other family members. Peter reaches out to an old friend.

episodes.title: Do Se Dosti
episodes.description: Sunil comes back and proves his innocence to Jende. As Peter and Jende's world collide, old wounds are reopened, and differences are resolved. By letting bygones be bygones, their friendship is rekindled. But a vicious future lies ahead for both.

episodes.title: Pappu Ka Bhoot
episodes.description: As the shadow of doom falls on the police itself, two cops from Jende's team meet a fateful end. As the pressure mounts on Jende, he starts suspecting Peter's involvement in the murders. Peter starts challenging his notions about the LGBTQ community.

episodes.title: Honey trapping
episodes.description: As Jende and Peter get a whiff of the 'honey trapping' racket run by the police, the chase to find the culprit gets even tougher. While Rabbani's reality is revealed to her family, Peter and Jende are also hit hard by a truth bomb.

episodes.title: Jhootha Sach
episodes.description: Peter's conflict with Sunil intensifies as he demands to know more about his personal life. Rabbani is jolted by the news of the suicide of her partner. Peter and Jende find the culprit behind these murders, but he escapes in the nick of time.

episodes.title: Barabari Ki Baari
episodes.description: The police up their ante to find the criminal on the run. Peter supports his son, and Jende stands up for Rabbani against the indiscriminate acts of his superior. Peter and Jende solve the case to find themselves on the cusp of another 'beginning'.

episodes.title: The Wrong Side of Goodbye
episodes.description: Retired Det. Harry Bosch, now a Private Investigator, is hired by aging billionaire Whitney Vance to handle a personal matter with major implications. When the man who ordered her murder a year and a half ago walks free, a devastated Honey “Money” Chandler teams Bosch to fix injustice. Maddie Bosch, still finding her footing as a rookie patrol cop, is assigned to a hard-charging Training Officer.

episodes.title: Pumped
episodes.description: Honey Chandler’s return to the courtroom continues as she fights to defend a homeless man wrongly accused of murder. Bosch zeroes in on Carl Rogers and locates an important character connected to Vance’s haunted past. Maddie and her Training Officer, Reina Vasquez, have their first caper as partners.

episodes.title: Message in a Bottle
episodes.description: Bosch and Chandler’s pursuit of Carl Rogers unexpectedly intersects with Russian organized crime. A chilling crime scene in Thai Town forces Maddie to face the limits of her job.

episodes.title: Horseshoes and Hand Grenades
episodes.description: As Bosch digs deeper into Whitney Vance’s past, other powerful forces at play monitor his every move. Chandler defends a man in a case of wrongful arrest. Carl Rogers finds himself is forced to hatch a new scheme. Maddie wrestles with the emotional toll of her job.

episodes.title: Plan B
episodes.description: The Whitney Vance story takes a surprise turn, complicating Bosch’s investigation. Bosch and Chandler plot to turn the tables on Rogers. Maddie struggles with taking her job home with her.

episodes.title: Chain of Authenticity
episodes.description: Will Carl Rogers outmaneuver Bosch and Chandler and escape justice once again? Maddie Bosch faces every cop’s biggest fear.

episodes.title: One of Your Own
episodes.description: Bosch takes up a murder case once thought solved by the LAPD. Maddie’s pulled into the department’s pursuit of a cop shooter. Chandler wrestles with the fallout of Carl Rogers.

episodes.title: Bloodline
episodes.description: As the Vance case enters a new phase, Bosch faces an escalating threat. A controversial police shooting ensnares both Maddie and Chandler.

episodes.title: Cat Got a Name?
episodes.description: The truth behind Whitney Vance’s death finally comes to light. Maddie helps with a major break in the Screen Cutter case. Chandler builds her best case against the LAPD.

episodes.title: Always/All Ways
episodes.description: Bosch reaches a dangerous end game in the Vance case. Chandler courts an unlikely ally in her wrongful death suit. Maddie pays the cost of getting too involved with her work.

episodes.title: The Lady Vanishes
episodes.description: Maddie’s gone missing, and it’s all hands on deck to find her. Bosch allies with Chandler, Mo, and an old friend in a race against the clock to save his daughter’s life.

episodes.title: Zzyzx
episodes.description: The Screen Cutter attempts to bargain with Bosch and Chandler, who go to extremes to locate Maddie before it’s too late.

episodes.title: Inside Man
episodes.description: Chandler enlists Bosch to defend a man accused of a brutal crime. Back on the job, Maddie struggles to find her footing. The FBI sets its sights on Bosch and Chandler.

episodes.title: Musso & Frank
episodes.description: Bosch digs into the Lexi Parks murder. Chandler’s new case attracts all the wrong attention. Maddie accepts an exciting assignment that partners her once again with Reina Vasquez.

episodes.title: Hollywood Forever
episodes.description: Bosch follows a hunch in the Parks case, but it backfires on him. Maddie hits the streets with Vasquez in her first CRU caper. Mo meets his match at a hackers' conference. Chandler starts playing the long game against the FBI. Ellis and Long keep a close eye on Bosch and Chandler.

episodes.title: Dos Matadores
episodes.description: Bosch looks into another murder that might be tied to the Parks case. Chandler clashes with the DA over the fate of David Foster. Kurt Dockweiler's sentencing looms over Maddie. Mo hatches a risky scheme to help Jade Quinn. Ellis and Long begin to feel the heat.

episodes.title: I Miss Vin Scully
episodes.description: Bosch starts to unravel the Lexi Parks murder, with potentially dangerous consequences. Chandler tries to outmaneuver the Feds as the case against her hangs in the balance. Ellis and Long get a little too close for comfort.

episodes.title: Seventy-Four Degrees in Belize
episodes.description: Everything comes to light in the Parks murder case. The FBI hit Bosch and Chandler where it hurts.

episodes.title: Escape Plan
episodes.description: Bosch and Chandler secure key witnesses against Ellis and Long. Chandler enters her endgame with the Feds. With Ellis in the wind, Maddie and CRU are tasked with protecting Bosch.

episodes.title: A Step Ahead
episodes.description: Bosch ensures the Lexi Parks case reaches its just conclusion. Chandler considers a big career change with the help of an old acquaintance. Maddie wrestles with the fallout of her first officer-involved shooting. Mo faces a serious ultimatum with the FBI.

episodes.title: Goes Where It Goes
episodes.description: Bosch must stop a serious threat to Chandler's run for DA. Maddie and Vasquez are drawn into a follow-home robbery case. An investigation commences into Bosch's possible involvement in Kurt Dockweiler's suspicious death.

episodes.title: Bosching Bosch
episodes.description: Bosch takes on the case of a missing family of four. Chandler seeks to flip a powerful campaign donor. The follow-home robbers scheme as the cops get closer. Jimmy Robertson digs deeper into the Bosch investigation.

episodes.title: Blankie
episodes.description: Bosch continues his investigation into the Gallagher family disappearance, focusing on Stephen Gallagher's business. Infighting in the follow-home robbery crew gives Vasquez and Maddie a lead. Chandler's association with Bosch comes under scrutiny, threatening her campaign.

episodes.title: Whippoorwills
episodes.description: Chandler and her team do damage control after the debate. Maddie and Vasquez zero in on the loot from the robberies. Bosch answers to the grand jury. Robertson and Lopez bring Preston Borders to LA to testify.

episodes.title: F***ing Politics
episodes.description: After the Gallagher case grows more complicated, Bosch focuses on discovering the fate of the family. Maddie and Vasquez set a trap for the follow-home crew. Chandler and team make the final push before the DA election. Political calculations impede Robertson and Lopez’s case work.

episodes.title: Broken Order
episodes.description: A month after the election, Chandler’s first big case as DA is prosecuting a cop killer. Bosch is brought on to help shore up the case. A break in the follow-home case leads Vasquez to a startling discovery.

episodes.title: Welcome to the Other Side
episodes.description: Chandler comes under fire from the chief of police. Bosch works a Juan Doe case he thinks may be connected to another murder, while Mo tries to locate Finbar McShane. Vasquez confirms her suspicions, while Maddie continues working the follow-home case.

episodes.title: La Zona Rosa
episodes.description: Bosch and Lopez continue investigating the Juan Doe case. Chandler begins to win the trust of her team. Maddie and Vasquez zero in on the follow-home crew.

episodes.title: Badlands
episodes.description: Bosch enlists an old war buddy to bring down Finbar McShane, but Maddie worries her father may cross a dangerous line. Vasquez deals with the emotional fallout of the follow-home cases. Chandler takes charge of a high-stakes case.

episodes.title: Dig Down
episodes.description: Bosch clashes with RHD detective Renee Ballard as they attempt to catch the "flower girls" serial killer before another victim is claimed.

episodes.title: Tell Me Sweet Little Lies
episodes.description: Every summer, Cadence Sinclair cherishes her time with her cousins Mirren and Johnny and her best friend Gat on Beechwood Island. At sixteen, what begins as their usual summer of mischief transforms when Cadence and Gat fall in love, while adult tensions rise in her family. She doesn't know this fairy tale will end with her alone on the beach, injured and with no memory of how she got there.

episodes.title: Wrap Her Up in a Package of Lies
episodes.description: Following her mysterious accident, Cadence has suffered a year of illness, amnesia, and loneliness, having had no contact with The Liars. Returning to Beechwood for answers, she finds even her closest friends won't discuss the summer she can't remember. But the island begins triggering memories of Summer 16, starting with a Father's Day celebration marred by rivalry, betrayal, and heartbreak.

episodes.title: The Ties Were Black, the Lies Were White
episodes.description: Having remembered a family tragedy, Cadence presses The Liars for answers. Mirren reveals a crush gone awry, Johnny recalls an unwanted visitor, and Gat recounts their relationship's painful turn. Tension between the aunts continues to rise, and Cadence suspects at least one Liar is hiding something, questioning whether what happened last summer was an accident at all.

episodes.title: The Fourth of You Lie
episodes.description: As the Sinclairs prepare for a quiet Fourth of July, Cadence investigates one of The Liars, uncovering memories of last year's crowded celebration. While the Sinclair sisters vied for their father's approval, The Liars navigated their romantic lives and Ed surprised Carrie. In present day, Cadence discovers a shocking truth about one Liar, leading to a confrontation as explosive as the fireworks.

episodes.title: Lying Together in a Silver Lining
episodes.description: Unsettled by a series of painful memories, Cadence tries to enjoy what's left of her summer – even if it means distracting herself with a potentially dangerous stunt. Despite her best efforts, she remembers a stormy day from Summer 16 when rising seas and frustrations threatened every Sinclair, exposing the family's darker side and forcing Gat and Cadence to confront their unspoken feelings.

episodes.title: When Lies Gives You Lemons
episodes.description: Unable to continue keeping secrets from her, Gat finally opens up to Cadence about his perspective on the island – one that doesn't always reflect the fairy-tale nostalgia of her own experience. While they head into town in search of answers, Gat recounts his memories of an honored Sinclair tradition – Tipper's Lemon Hunt – and the unplanned visit from his mother that made him question everything.

episodes.title: Everybody Knows That the Captain Lied
episodes.description: More uncertain than ever, Cadence reluctantly joins Harris on an excursion, triggering memories of their final confrontation in Summer 16. During a tense family dinner, The Liars confront their mothers about family secrets. In the aftermath of shocking revelations, The Liars mourn their once-beloved childhood playground and unite in an attempt to save their fracturing family.

episodes.title: My Friends Are Lying in the Sun
episodes.description: Cadence devises a plan to trigger her latent memories of the final hours before her traumatic accident, but she can't do it alone – she must convince the reluctant Johnny, Mirren, and Gat to help her, even if it means risking everything. But as the truth begins to come back to her in fits and starts, Cadence realizes that she, herself, has been the biggest Liar of all.
