episodes.title: Winter Is Coming
episodes.description: Jon Arryn, the Hand of the King, is dead. King Robert Baratheon plans to ask his oldest friend, Eddard Stark, to take Jon's place. Across the sea, Viserys Targaryen plans to wed his sister to a nomadic warlord in exchange for an army.

episodes.title: The Kingsroad
episodes.description: While Bran recovers from his fall, Ned takes only his daughters to Kings Landing. Jon Snow goes with his uncle Benjen to The Wall. Tyrion joins them.

episodes.title: Lord Snow
episodes.description: Lord Stark and his daughters arrive at King's Landing to discover the intrigues of the king's realm.

episodes.title: Cripples, Bastards, and Broken Things
episodes.description: Eddard investigates Jon Arryn's murder. Jon befriends Samwell Tarly, a coward who has come to join the Night's Watch.

episodes.title: The Wolf and the Lion
episodes.description: Catelyn has captured Tyrion and plans to bring him to her sister, Lysa Arryn, at The Vale, to be tried for his, supposed, crimes against Bran. Robert plans to have Daenerys killed, but Eddard refuses to be a part of it and quits.

episodes.title: A Golden Crown
episodes.description: While recovering from his battle with Jamie, Eddard is forced to run the kingdom while Robert goes hunting. Tyrion demands a trial by combat for his freedom. Viserys is losing his patience with Drogo.

episodes.title: You Win or You Die
episodes.description: Robert has been injured while hunting and is dying. Jon and the others finally take their vows to the Night's Watch. A man, sent by Robert, is captured for trying to poison Daenerys. Furious, Drogo vows to attack the Seven Kingdoms.

episodes.title: The Pointy End
episodes.description: Eddard and his men are betrayed and captured by the Lannisters. When word reaches Robb, he plans to go to war to rescue them. The White Walkers attack The Wall. Tyrion returns to his father with some new friends.

episodes.title: Baelor
episodes.description: Robb goes to war against the Lannisters. Jon finds himself struggling on deciding if his place is with Robb or the Night's Watch. Drogo has fallen ill from a fresh battle wound. Daenerys is desperate to save him.

episodes.title: Fire and Blood
episodes.description: With Ned dead, Robb vows to get revenge on the Lannisters. Jon must officially decide if his place is with Robb or the Night's Watch. Daenerys says her final goodbye to Drogo.

episodes.title: The North Remembers
episodes.description: As Robb Stark and his northern army continue the war against the Lannisters, Tyrion arrives in King’s Landing to counsel Joffrey and temper the young king’s excesses.  On the island of Dragonstone, Stannis Baratheon plots an invasion to claim his late brother’s throne, allying himself with the fiery Melisandre, a strange priestess of a stranger god.  Across the sea, Daenerys, her three young dragons, and the khalasar trek through the Red Waste in search of allies, or water.  In the North, Bran presides over a threadbare Winterfell, while beyond the Wall, Jon Snow and the Night’s Watch must shelter with a devious wildling.

episodes.title: The Night Lands
episodes.description: In the wake of a bloody purge in the capital, Tyrion chastens Cersei for alienating the king’s subjects.  On the road north, Arya shares a secret with Gendry, a Night’s Watch recruit.  With supplies dwindling, one of Dany’s scouts returns with news of their position.  After nine years as a Stark ward, Theon Greyjoy reunites with his father Balon, who wants to restore the ancient Kingdom of the Iron Islands.  Davos enlists Salladhor Saan, a pirate, to join forces with Stannis and Melisandre for a naval invasion of King’s Landing.

episodes.title: What is Dead May Never Die
episodes.description: At the Red Keep, Tyrion plots three alliances through the promise of marriage.  Catelyn arrives in the Stormlands to forge an alliance of her own, but King Renly, his new wife Margaery, and her brother Loras Tyrell have other plans.  At Winterfell, Luwin tries to decipher Bran’s dreams.

episodes.title: Garden of Bones
episodes.description: Joffrey punishes Sansa for Robb’s victories, and Tyrion scrambles to temper the king’s cruelty. Catelyn entreats Stannis and Renly to unite against the Lannisters. Dany and her khalasar arrive at the prosperous city of Qarth. Tyrion coerces a relative into being his eyes and ears. Arya and Gendry are taken to Harrenhal, where their lives are in the hands of Ser Gregor Clegane. Stannis orders Davos to smuggle Melisandre into a secret cove.

episodes.title: The Ghost of Harrenhal
episodes.description: The Baratheon rivalry ends, driving Catelyn to flee and Littlefinger to act. At King’s Landing, Tyrion’s source alerts him to Joffrey’s defense plan - and a mysterious secret weapon. Theon sails to the Stony Shore to prove he’s worthy to be called Ironborn. At Harrenhal, Arya receives a promise from Jaqen H’ghar, one of the prisoners she saved from the Gold Cloaks. The Night’s Watch arrive at the Fist of the First Men, an ancient ringfort where they hope to stem the wildings' advance.

episodes.title: The Old Gods and the New
episodes.description: Theon seizes control of Winterfell. Jon captures a wildling, named Ygritte and is given a chance to prove himself. At King's Landing, after the Lannisters send Myrcella off to be married, the people begin to turn against King Joffrey. Arya comes face to face with a surprise visitor. Daenerys looks to buy ships to sail for the Seven Kingdoms.

episodes.title: A Man Without Honor
episodes.description: Jamie meets a distant relative. Daenerys receives an invitation to the House of the Undying. Theon leads a search party. Jon loses his way in the wilderness. Cersei counsels Sansa.

episodes.title: The Prince of Winterfell
episodes.description: Betrayal befalls Robb. Jon and Qhorin are taken prisoner by the wildlings. Theon receives a visitor at Winterfell and must make an important decision. Meanwhile, Stannis is just days away from reaching King's Landing and Tyrion prepares for his arrival. At Harrenhal, Arya, Gendry and Hot Pie plan their escape.

episodes.title: Blackwater
episodes.description: Tyrion and the Lannisters fight for their lives as Stannis’ fleet assaults King’s Landing.

episodes.title: Valar Morghulis
episodes.description: Tyrion awakens to a changed situation. King Joffrey doles out rewards to his subjects. As Theon stirs his men to action, Luwin offers some final advice. Brienne silences Jaime. Arya receives a gift from Jaqen. Dany goes to a strange place. Jon proves himself to Qhorin.

episodes.title: Valar Dohaeris
episodes.description: Jon meets the King-Beyond-the-Wall while his Night Watch Brothers flee south. In King's Landing, Tyrion wants a reward, Margaery shows her charitable nature, Cersei arranges a dinner party, and Littlefinger offers to help Sansa. Across the Narrow Sea, Daenerys starts her journey west.

episodes.title: Dark Wings, Dark Words
episodes.description: Sansa says too much. Shae asks Tyrion for a favor. Jaime finds a way to pass the time, while Arya encounters the Brotherhood Without Banners.

episodes.title: Walk of Punishment
episodes.description: Tyrion shoulders new responsibilities. Jon is taken to the Fist of the First Men. Daenerys meets with the slavers. Jaime strikes a deal with his captors.

episodes.title: And Now His Watch Is Ended
episodes.description: Trouble brews among the Night's Watch at Craster's. Margaery takes Joffrey out of his comfort zone. Arya meets the leader of the Brotherhood. Varys plots revenge on an old foe. Theon mournfully recalls his missteps. Daenerys deftly orchestrates her exit from Astapor.

episodes.title: Kissed by Fire
episodes.description: The Hound is judged by the gods. Jaime is judged by men. Jon proves himself. Robb is betrayed. Tyrion learns the cost of weddings.

episodes.title: The Climb
episodes.description: Tywin plans strategic unions for the Lannisters. Melisandre pays a visit to the Riverlands. Robb weighs a compromise to repair his alliance with House Frey. Roose Bolton decides what to do with Jaime Lannister. Jon, Ygritte, and the Wildlings face a daunting climb.

episodes.title: The Bear and the Maiden Fair
episodes.description: Daenerys exchanges gifts with a slave lord outside of Yunkai. As Sansa frets about her prospects, Shae chafes at Tyrion’s new situation. Tywin counsels the king, and Melisandre reveals a secret to Gendry. Brienne faces a formidable foe in Harrenhal.

episodes.title: Second Sons
episodes.description: King’s Landing hosts a wedding, and Tyrion and Sansa spend the night together. Daenerys tries to persuade the Second Sons to join her against Yunkai. Stannis releases Davos from the dungeons. Sam and Gilly meet an older gentleman.

episodes.title: The Rains of Castamere
episodes.description: The Lannisters send their regards.

episodes.title: Mhysa
episodes.description: Bran and company travel beyond the Wall. Sam returns to Castle Black. Jon says goodbye to Ygritte. Jaime returns to King's Landing. The Night's Watch asks for help from Stannis. Daenerys waits to see if she is a conqueror or a liberator.

episodes.title: Two Swords
episodes.description: Tyrion welcomes a guest to King’s Landing. At Castle Black, Jon Snow finds himself unwelcome. Dany is pointed to Meereen, the mother of all slave cities. Arya runs into an old friend.

episodes.title: The Lion and the Rose
episodes.description: Tyrion lends Jaime a hand. Joffrey and Margaery host a breakfast. At Dragonstone, Stannis loses patience with Davos. Ramsay finds a purpose for his pet. North of the Wall, Bran sees where they must go.

episodes.title: Breaker of Chains
episodes.description: Tyrion ponders his options. Tywin extends an olive branch. Sam realizes Castle Black isn’t safe, and Jon proposes a bold plan. The Hound teaches Arya the way things are. Dany chooses her champion.

episodes.title: Oathkeeper
episodes.description: Dany balances justice and mercy. Jaime tasks Brienne with his honor. Jon secures volunteers while Bran, Jojen, Meera and Hodor stumble on shelter.

episodes.title: First of His Name
episodes.description: After Tommen is crowned the King of the Seven Kingdoms, Cersei and Tywin plan the Crown's next move. Meanwhile, Dany weighs her future plans regarding Westeros and Slaver's Bay. Sansa and Lord Baelish arrive at the Eyrie and Jon Snow along with men from the Night's Watch attacks Craster's Keep.

episodes.title: The Laws of Gods and Men
episodes.description: Stannis makes a deal with the Iron Bank of Braavos. Yara and her troops storm the Dreadfort to free Theon. Meanwhile, Daenerys meets Hizdar zo Loraq and her other supplicants. And the day of Tyrion's trial has come where Tyrion faces his father.

episodes.title: Mockingbird
episodes.description: Tyrion gains an unlikely ally; Daario asks Dany to allow him to do what he does best; Jon's warnings about the vulnerability of the Wall are ignored; Brienne follows a new lead.

episodes.title: The Mountain and the Viper
episodes.description: Unexpected visitors arrive in Mole's Town. With assistance from Theon, Ramsay proves himself to his father, Lord Bolton. Littlefinger's motives are questioned when Sansa reveals the fate of Lysa Arryn to other lords of the Vale. Daenerys finds out a secret about Jorah Mormont. Tyrion's fate is decided.

episodes.title: The Watchers on the Wall
episodes.description: Night gathers, and now my watch begins.

episodes.title: The Children
episodes.description: Circumstances change after an unexpected arrival from north of the Wall. Dany must face harsh realities. Bran learns more about his destiny. Tyrion sees the truth about his situation.

episodes.title: The Wars to Come
episodes.description: Cersei and Jaime adjust to a world without Tywin. Varys reveals a conspiracy to Tyrion. Dany faces a new threat to her rule. Jon is caught between two kings.

episodes.title: The House of Black and White
episodes.description: Arya arrives in Braavos. Podrick and Brienne run into trouble on the road. Cersei fears for her daughter's safety in Dorne as Ellaria Sand seeks revenge for Oberyn's death. Stannis tempts Jon. An adviser tempts Daenerys.

episodes.title: High Sparrow
episodes.description: In Braavos, Arya sees the Many-Faced God. In King's Landing, Queen Margaery enjoys her new husband. Tyrion and Varys walk the Long Bridge of Volantis.

episodes.title: Sons of the Harpy
episodes.description: The Faith Militant grow increasingly aggressive. Jaime and Bronn head south. Ellaria and the Sand Snakes vow vengeance.

episodes.title: Kill the Boy
episodes.description: Dany makes a difficult decision in Meereen. Jon recruits the help of an unexpected ally. Brienne searches for Sansa. Theon remains under Ramsay's control.

episodes.title: Unbowed, Unbent, Unbroken
episodes.description: Arya trains. Jorah and Tyrion run into slavers. Trystane and Myrcella make plans. Jaime and Bronn reach their destination. The Sand Snakes attack.

episodes.title: The Gift
episodes.description: Jon prepares for conflict. Sansa tries to talk to Theon. Brienne waits for a sign. Stannis remains stubborn. Jaime attempts to reconnect with family.

episodes.title: Hardhome
episodes.description: Arya makes progress in her training. Sansa confronts an old friend. Cersei struggles. Jon travels.

episodes.title: The Dance of Dragons
episodes.description: Stannis confronts a troubling decision. Jon returns to The Wall. Mace visits the Iron Bank. Arya encounters someone from her past. Dany reluctantly oversees a traditional celebration of athleticism.

episodes.title: Mother's Mercy
episodes.description: Stannis marches. Dany is surrounded by strangers. Cersei seeks forgiveness. Jon is challenged.

episodes.title: The Red Woman
episodes.description: The fate of Jon Snow is revealed. Daenerys meets a strong man. Cersei sees her daughter once again.

episodes.title: Home
episodes.description: Bran trains with the Three-Eyed Raven. In King’s Landing, Jaime advises Tommen. Tyrion demands good news, but has to make his own. At Castle Black, the Night’s Watch stands behind Thorne. Ramsay Bolton proposes a plan, and Balon Greyjoy entertains other proposals.

episodes.title: Oathbreaker
episodes.description: Daenerys meets her future. Bran meets the past. Tommen confronts the High Sparrow. Arya trains to be No One. Varys finds an answer. Ramsay gets a gift.

episodes.title: Book of the Stranger
episodes.description: Tyrion strikes a deal. Jorah and Daario undertake a difficult task. Jaime and Cersei try to improve their situation.

episodes.title: The Door
episodes.description: Tyrion seeks a strange ally. Bran learns a great deal. Brienne goes on a mission. Arya is given a chance to prove herself.

episodes.title: Blood of My Blood
episodes.description: An old foe comes back into the picture. Gilly meets Sam’s family. Arya faces a difficult choice. Jaime faces off against the High Sparrow.

episodes.title: The Broken Man
episodes.description: The High Sparrow eyes another target. Jaime confronts a hero. Arya makes a plan. The North is reminded.

episodes.title: No One
episodes.description: While Jaime weighs his options, Cersei answers a request. Tyrion's plans bear fruit. Arya faces a new test.

episodes.title: Battle of the Bastards
episodes.description: As the Starks prepare to fight, Davos loses something dear. Ramsay plays a game. Daenerys faces a choice.

episodes.title: The Winds of Winter
episodes.description: Tyrion counsels Daenerys on the upcoming campaign. Jon and Sansa discuss their future. Trials begin in King's Landing.

episodes.title: Dragonstone
episodes.description: Jon organizes the defense of the North. Cersei tries to even the odds. Daenerys comes home.

episodes.title: Stormborn
episodes.description: Daenerys receives an unexpected visitor. Jon faces a revolt. Tyrion plans the conquest of Westeros.

episodes.title: The Queen's Justice
episodes.description: Daenerys holds court. Tyrion backchannels. Cersei returns a gift. Jaime learns from his mistakes.

episodes.title: The Spoils of War
episodes.description: Daenerys fights back. Jaime faces an unexpected situation. Arya comes home.

episodes.title: Eastwatch
episodes.description: Tyrion tries to find a way to make Daenerys listen to reason while Jon plans a dangerous new mission.

episodes.title: Beyond the Wall
episodes.description: Jon and his team go beyond the wall to capture a wight. Daenerys has to make a tough decision.

episodes.title: The Dragon and the Wolf
episodes.description: A meeting is held in King's Landing. Problems arise in the North.

episodes.title: Winterfell
episodes.description: Arriving at Winterfell, Jon and Daenerys struggle to unite a divided North. Jon Snow gets some big news.

episodes.title: A Knight of the Seven Kingdoms
episodes.description: The battle at Winterfell is approaching. Jaime is confronted with the consequences of the past. A tense interaction between Sansa and Daenerys follows.

episodes.title: The Long Night
episodes.description: The Night King and his army have arrived at Winterfell and the great battle begins. Arya looks to prove her worth as a fighter.

episodes.title: The Last of the Starks
episodes.description: In the wake of a costly victory, Jon and Daenerys look to the south as Tyrion eyes a compromise that could save countless lives.

episodes.title: The Bells
episodes.description: Daenerys brings her forces to King's Landing.

episodes.title: The Iron Throne
episodes.description: In the aftermath of the devastating attack on King's Landing, Daenerys must face the survivors.

episodes.title: Mallikajaan: The Queen of Heeramandi
episodes.description: As Mallikajaan reigns over her courtesans, rebellion grows on the streets. Alamzeb has her first brush with love. Wali shares key information with Bibbo.

episodes.title: Fareedanjaan: The Challenger Returns
episodes.description: Heartbroken by a nawab, Lajjo turns to drink and dance to win back her former lover. Mallikajaan reveals a dark secret as her past catches up with her.

episodes.title: Waheedajaan - Scarred for Life
episodes.description: The return of Fareedan to Khwabgah raises tensions as Mallikajaan schemes to cling onto her control. Waheedan makes a bold move of her own.

episodes.title: Alamzeb: The Innocent Pawn
episodes.description: As her dance debut approaches, Alam questions her place at Heeramandi. Saima unwittingly earns Mallikajaan's ire and Fareedan strikes back.

episodes.title: Tajdar: The Lover’s Dilemma
episodes.description: As Mallikajaan and the courtesans fervently search for Alam, Tajdar comes to her rescue. Meanwhile, an enraged Waheedan has a proposal for Fareedan.

episodes.title: Tajdar & Alamzeb: Nation vs. Love
episodes.description: Alam and Tajdar’s romance intensifies as a rebellion is being hatched. Mallikajaan and Fareedan uncover dark and disturbing secrets about each other.

episodes.title: Bibbojaan - Long Live the Revolution
episodes.description: Cartwright’s scheme against the courtesans unfolds. Seeking a future with Alam, Tajdar approaches Mallikajaan — but her approval comes at a price.

episodes.title: Heeramandi: The Swan Song
episodes.description: The fight for freedom reaches the steps of Heeramandi — for both the courtesans and the country. Will the battle end in victory or result in ruination?

episodes.title: Episode 1
episodes.description: Detective Hansaem suspects Ena after she fails to remember anything about her uncle's murder.

episodes.title: Episode 2
episodes.description: A puzzle piece arrives on the same day as a murder, and Hansaem suspects it’s no coincidence.

episodes.title: Episode 3
episodes.description: Ena and Hansaem warily work together to solve the case.

episodes.title: Episode 4
episodes.description: A prime suspect emerges, but things aren't what they seem.

episodes.title: Episode 5
episodes.description: Another puzzle piece arrives, and a new murder case unfolds.

episodes.title: Episode 6
episodes.description: The meaning behind the drawings on the puzzle pieces is uncovered.

episodes.title: Episode 1
episodes.description: When cleaner Ria is hired by mysterious businesswoman Fran, an unlikely friendship is formed. But when Fran's advice leads to tragedy, Ria's life is changed forever.

episodes.title: Episode 2
episodes.description: Ria faces the police while trying to pick up the pieces with Lee. But that will mean cutting Fran off entirely. Can she ever go back to her old life?

episodes.title: Episode 3
episodes.description: Fran offers Ria an exciting promotion, but doubts set in when unsettling revelations come to light that call her motives into question.

episodes.title: Episode 4
episodes.description: Ria finds herself a fugitive on the run. She must stay one step ahead of the police – and Fran – long enough to repair old relationships and discover the evidence that will clear her.

episodes.title: Hell Hath No Fury Like a Man Wronged!
episodes.description: Ready to settle a score, big shot Abhimanyu Nayak arrives in Goa. Back in the past, Shiva’s reunion with his BFF gang ignites the chapter of love, lies and deceit.

episodes.title: The Vendetta
episodes.description: At the casino, Abhimanyu weighs in on his first move. Flashbacks reveal how a romantic date night draws Shiva into a deadly web as he gets framed for a murder.

episodes.title: Tables Have Turned
episodes.description: The aftereffects of his arrest leave Shiva reeling with frame-ups and betrayals. While Tara wrestles with painful memories of her own, Abhimanyu takes charge at the casino.

episodes.title: My Love Is Not a Lie
episodes.description: With her son Kartik missing, a frail and frightened Tara begins the search.  A look into the past offers Tara’s side of the love story, unveiling disturbing secrets.

episodes.title: D-Day
episodes.description: Armed with the ‘perfect heist’ plan, Michael, JK, and Tara brace for their next moves. Ahead of a charity event, Abhimanyu and Michael get into a heated confrontation.

episodes.title: The Godfather
episodes.description: While Shiva is left grilling in prison, his friends-turned-foes start anew after a successful heist. Amidst the uncertainty, Shiva finds his guiding light in the form of Bhau.

episodes.title: Best Served Cold
episodes.description: Conflicts of the past resurface as Abhimanyu and JK have a man-to-man conversation. Drowned in his sorrows, Shiva has one choice to make: give up or retaliate!

episodes.title: Reincarnation
episodes.description: At Tara’s party, Abhimanyu concocts his plan of action. In the past, Bhau’s orchestrated mayhem offers Shiva a second chance at life - a rebirth!

episodes.title: We Are Family
episodes.description: While Tara grows frantic about Divya’s deteriorating health, Abhimanyu reminisces the sufferings of his loved ones. At the prison, a plot to kill Bhau is set in motion.

episodes.title: A Way Back Home
episodes.description: Tension mounts between JK and the Ranes over reopening Shiva’s case. Back home, Abhimanyu finds solace in his father’s embrace. And now, he is all set for his next move!

episodes.title: Is Love a Trap?
episodes.description: Flashbacks reveal how love becomes a hurdle in Abhimanyu’s plan of vengeance. As he storms into Tara’s life again, the resolution for revenge is clear - one way or another!

episodes.title: The Loophole
episodes.description: Looking for answers, Michael dredges up Abhimanyu’s close associate Rana’s story. While he aims to connect the dots, Abhimanyu forms an unlikely bond with Divya.

episodes.title: Men with a Past!
episodes.description: While Abhimanyu and Rana deal with the ghosts of their past, Divya wrestles with her feelings of love. At the casino, Abhimanyu senses an opportunity to get back at Tara.

episodes.title: Of Lost Love and Vengeance
episodes.description: Tension simmers as Abhimanyu pushes Tara to recall the past wounds. While Gargi senses a conspiracy, Abhimanyu answers a big question: What after revenge?

episodes.title: A Mother's Heart
episodes.description: With Gargi’s arrival at the dinner party, Abhimanyu’s identity is at risk of disclosure. Following his hunch, Michael inches dangerously close to the truth.

episodes.title: Fate Is Blind
episodes.description: Bhau warns Abhimanyu to lay low! JK-Gargi-Abhimanyu’s confrontation at the Rane house dredges up past wounds, new revelations, and changing destinies.

episodes.title: The Gameplan
episodes.description: A crucial intel about Abhimanyu makes JK plot his next moves. Meanwhile, Abhimanyu’s growing bond with Tara and Divya spirals into emotional turmoil.

episodes.title: Show of Power
episodes.description: While Bhau guides Abhimanyu on his next plan of action, JK sets his sights on Abhimanyu’s hotel project. A deadly attack at Tara’s casino puts everyone on edge!

episodes.title: The Night I Met You Again
episodes.description: After the casino attack, JK and Abhimanyu seek shelter at the old-yet-familiar Adda. Broken from within, Tara finds solace in a heart-to-heart talk with Abhimanyu.

episodes.title: Blood Ties
episodes.description: Tara grows increasingly concerned when Michael claims to have killed her father. Back at the Rane house, Abhimanyu reminisces painful memories of the past.

episodes.title: Follow the Commander
episodes.description: Abhimanyu keeps things platonic with Divya while Michael’s quest for the truth intensifies. Keeping Abhimanyu out of the loop, Bhau sets a new plan in motion.

episodes.title: Can I Get Over Her?
episodes.description: JK overlooks Michael’s findings about Abhimanyu. Back at the casino, JK’s revelation about wanting a second child leaves Abhimanyu wrestling with pent-up feelings.

episodes.title: Innocent Love
episodes.description: Michael presses on JK’s insecurity, sowing doubts about Kartik’s biological father. While Divya revels in new-found love, Abhimanyu must reconsider his immoral choices.

episodes.title: Cheaters Will Prosper
episodes.description: DNA findings reveal the truth about Kartik’s parentage, leaving JK on edge. Ready to get back at Tara, Abhimanyu remains persistent about his love trap for Divya.

episodes.title: There Will Be Blood
episodes.description: Using Divya as a pawn, Abhimanyu wrestles with a tough choice - act or retreat. Ahead of the D-day, an unexpected tragedy awaits everyone. And this may ruin it all!

episodes.title: Why Did You Betray Me?
episodes.description: Forging a business partnership with JK and Tara, Abhimanyu makes it clear - the vendetta will continue! Determined to unravel the conspiracy, Mert embarks on a quest of his own.

episodes.title: Don’t Dig Your Own Grave!
episodes.description: Mert’s quest to clear Shiva’s name brings him to the jail, where he discovers a crucial intel. As he gets dangerously close to the truth, Bhau takes matters into his own hands.

episodes.title: Let Me Tell You A Story…
episodes.description: To thwart Mert’s investigation, Bhau orchestrates a calculated move. Tara’s world crumbles after finding a videotape that reveals what unfolded on the night of the bank robbery.

episodes.title: My Love Is A Lie
episodes.description: Hit hard by reality, Tara tries to retrospect and seeks refuge at Gargi’s house. While Michael closes in on Bhau, Abhimanyu clears the truth about his growing closeness to Tara.

episodes.title: My Brother Is A Murderer!
episodes.description: Seizing an opportunity, Abhimanyu manages to create a rift between Tara and JK. Things spiral out of control when Mert publishes an article naming Shiva as the murderer.

episodes.title: The Castle Is Falling
episodes.description: A well-timed strategy helps Abhimanyu sow seeds of mistrust between JK and Michael. As old connections begin to alter, he sets his sights on the next target - Tara.

episodes.title: My Game, My Rules
episodes.description: The old player—RC—rises to power, using the videotape to secure control over JK and Michael. Meanwhile, Abhimanyu puts the final touches on his plan to take over Tara’s casinos!

episodes.title: Your Love Is My Solace
episodes.description: Tara wrestles with her growing feelings for Abhimanyu, unknowingly falling for his trap. The trio—RC, Michael, and JK—reflect on setting a ploy for Abhimanyu.

episodes.title: Will You Die For Your Brother?
episodes.description: Revenge is his only motto! A new threat looms over the Rane house with Pakya’s arrival. The truth about Tara and RC’s relationship makes Abhimanyu reconsider his plan.

episodes.title: It’s a Devil’s World
episodes.description: All the pieces fall into place as Pakya gets his hands on the videotape. But a tragedy befalls, pushing Abhimanyu and everyone to the edge. And this may change it all!

episodes.title: I Embrace Death!
episodes.description: Ready to bury his past once and for all, Abhimanyu declares the death of Shiva. Tension flares as Tara receives an anonymous call—Kartik has been kidnapped!

episodes.title: Time’s Ticking On You
episodes.description: Amid mounting pressure, Bhau assigns JK a critical task to save Kartik. And a trap is laid! JK runs into trouble with the police after getting framed at a crime scene.

episodes.title: Let’s Rewind The Clock
episodes.description: Using Tara as the pawn, Abhimanyu inches closer to put an end to the JK chapter. A tense scene unfolds in the courtroom as Tara testifies against JK. And Karma hits back!

episodes.title: All Eyes On You
episodes.description: The intimate picture of Abhimanyu and Tara makes everything clear. While Michael readies to expose him, Divya’s world comes crashing down. A big setback looms over Abhimanyu!

episodes.title: I Am The Destroyer!
episodes.description: Revelations and regrets surface! Tara wrestles with her past and present choices after a fallout with Divya. At the jail, Abhimanyu confronts JK and reveals it all.

episodes.title: Only Innocents Will Suffer
episodes.description: A sudden tragedy pushes Tara on the edge, while JK faces an unexpected visitor. Abhimanyu proposes marriage to Tara, which hints at a new turning point!

episodes.title: Upar Neeche
episodes.description: After breaking a tooth while hunting for blood, Rumi crosses paths with Roy, a timid dentist. Kartik, an outcast cop, looks into a mysterious case.

episodes.title: The Cutmundus
episodes.description: Roy's rare blood sparks interest from Rumi's clan, as Sreela is sent after him. Kartik’s case sends a signal to a secret cabal of vampire hunters.

episodes.title: Climate Change
episodes.description: When a vampire is killed, an awakened Ora bans access to the human world above ground. Hell-bent on revenge, Rumi seeks help from an unlikely source.

episodes.title: The Test
episodes.description: Badshah is taken underground. Kartik learns about his father's past from Luna Luka. At a family dinner, Roy grows suspicious over Rumi's true nature.

episodes.title: Darinda
episodes.description: Roy struggles with his feelings for Rumi. The Cutmundus plot to uncover the vampires' secrets, while Rumi ponders grief, love and loss of her past.

episodes.title: Tyajet Kularthe Purusham
episodes.description: The death of a Cutmundus member leads Luna down a vengeful path. Believing that Roy is a vampire, a desperate Kartik resorts to blackmail.

episodes.title: Meet the Parents
episodes.description: Dinner at the Roy's turns into a night of drunken revelry, while Rumi and Roy take an intimate step. Later, Badshah's revelation puts Rumi in danger.

episodes.title: No. 30
episodes.description: Rumi is faced with a devastating ultimatum — go after Luna, or lose Roy forever. A figure from Luna's past returns to her life.

episodes.title: The Pilot
episodes.description: As four misfit kids vow to find their missing classmate, Major Leroy Hanlon arrives to a mixed reception at Derry Air Force Base.

episodes.title: The Thing in the Dark
episodes.description: While Charlotte and Will navigate their new life in Derry, Ronnie worries about her father's fate.

episodes.title: Now You See It
episodes.description: As Leroy, Pauly, and Dick search for a new dig site, the kids attempt to get visual proof of the phenomena they've been experiencing.

episodes.title: The Great Swirling Apparatus of Our Planet's Function
episodes.description: As the kids face increasingly terrifying experiences, Charlotte attempts to advocate for Hank, and General Shaw escalates his efforts.

episodes.title: Neibolt Street
episodes.description: Leroy moves his family to the base for safety. While the tribal Keepers strategize how to contain increased aggression in town, the military descends on Neibolt Street, and the kids head into the sewers with their own objective.

episodes.title: Red Light, Green Light
episodes.description: Hoping to win easy money, a broke and desperate Gi-hun agrees to take part in an enigmatic game. Not long into the first round, unforeseen horrors unfold.

episodes.title: Hell
episodes.description: Split on whether to continue or quit, the group holds a vote. But their realities in the outside world may prove to be just as unforgiving as the game.

episodes.title: The Man with the Umbrella
episodes.description: A few players enter the next round — which promises equal doses of sweet and deadly — with hidden advantages. Meanwhile, Jun-ho sneaks his way inside.

episodes.title: Stick to the Team
episodes.description: As alliances form among the players, no one is safe in the dorm after lights-out. The third game challenges Gi-hun's team to think strategically.

episodes.title: A Fair World
episodes.description: Gi-hun and his team take turns keeping guard through the night. The masked men encounter trouble with their co-conspirators.

episodes.title: Gganbu
episodes.description: Players pair off for the fourth game. Gi-hun grapples with a moral dilemma, Sang-woo chooses self-preservation and Sae-byeok shares her untold story.

episodes.title: VIPS
episodes.description: The Masked Leader welcomes VIP guests to the facility for a front-row viewing of the show. In the fifth game, some players crack under pressure.

episodes.title: Front Man
episodes.description: Ahead of the last round, distrust and disgust run deep among the finalists. Jun-ho makes a getaway, determined to expose the game's dirty secrets.

episodes.title: One Lucky Day
episodes.description: The final round presents another cruel test — but this time, how it ends depends on just one player. The game's creator steps out of the shadows.

episodes.title: Bread and Lottery
episodes.description: A vengeful Gi-hun makes a U-turn at the airport. Later, in his hideout, he intensifies his search for the elusive recruiter who is seeking new players.

episodes.title: Halloween Party
episodes.description: Gi-hun finally gets hold of an invitation, marked for Halloween day. In a tense moment facing Jun-ho, they reveal their truths to each other.
New players gather for a chance to win 45.6 billion won. After an intense first round, the survivors' fates hang in the balance — down to one final vote.

episodes.title: Six Legs
episodes.description: The players prepare for the next game: a six-legged pentathlon, where each team member must clear a mini-game to survive — or face collective elimination.

episodes.title: One More Game
episodes.description: Kang No-eul earns enemies for her unruly actions. Nerves fray to the breaking point as the remaining players vote on whether to move to the next round.

episodes.title: O ﻿ X
episodes.description: Jun-ho and his team prepare to infiltrate a suspicious island. As monetary stakes and tensions rise, players split into two opposing factions.

episodes.title: Friend or Foe
episodes.description: The remaining players strategize on how to survive the night. Gi-hun proposes a risky plan — but he will need trustworthy allies to carry it out.

episodes.title: Keys and Knives
episodes.description: No-eul infiltrates a dangerous operation with a risky plan. A new game is announced: hide-and-seek, where one group holds a key and the other a knife.

episodes.title: The Starry Night
episodes.description: The games resume, and Gi-hun fixates on confronting Kang Dae-ho. Meanwhile, Kim Jun-hee faces a sudden crisis that pushes her willpower to its limits.

episodes.title: It's Not Your Fault
episodes.description: Jun-ho's team gets close to finding the island. Jang Geum-ja makes a desperate plea to Gi-hun to help Jun-hee. The VIPs discuss a cruel proposal.
Even as Gi-hun supports Jun-hee amid rising tensions, she must make a pivotal decision. Before the final game, the Front Man gives Gi-hun an ultimatum.
No-eul tries to gain the upper hand in negotiations, but her plans backfire. Gi-hun faces a moral crossroads, testing his limits — how far will he go?

episodes.title: Humans Are...
episodes.description: As Jun-ho races to reach the island, tensions peak in the final round. The last players face an impossible situation in the closing minutes of the game.

episodes.title: Pilot
episodes.description: When an unassuming high school chemistry teacher discovers he has a rare form of lung cancer, he decides to team up with a former student and create a top of the line crystal meth in a used RV, to provide for his family once he is gone.

episodes.title: Cat's in the Bag...
episodes.description: Walt and Jesse attempt to tie up loose ends. The desperate situation gets more complicated with the flip of a coin. Walt's wife, Skyler, becomes suspicious of Walt's strange behavior.

episodes.title: ...And the Bag's in the River
episodes.description: Walter fights with Jesse over his drug use, causing him to leave Walter alone with their captive, Krazy-8. Meanwhile, Hank has a scared straight moment with Walter Jr. after his aunt discovers he has been smoking pot. Also, Skylar is upset when Walter stays away from home.

episodes.title: Cancer Man
episodes.description: Walter finally tells his family that he has been stricken with cancer. Meanwhile, the DEA believes Albuquerque has a new, big time player to worry about. Meanwhile, a worthy recipient is the target of a depressed Walter's anger, and Jesse makes a surprise visit to his parents home.

episodes.title: Gray Matter
episodes.description: Walter and Skyler attend a former colleague's party. Jesse tries to free himself from the drugs, while Skyler organizes an intervention.

episodes.title: Crazy Handful of Nothin'
episodes.description: The side effects of chemo begin to plague Walt. Meanwhile, the DEA rounds up suspected dealers.

episodes.title: A No Rough Stuff Type Deal
episodes.description: Walter accepts his new identity as a drug dealer after a PTA meeting. Elsewhere, Jesse decides to put his aunt's house on the market and Skyler is the recipient of a baby shower.

episodes.title: Seven Thirty-Seven
episodes.description: Walt and Jesse are vividly reminded of Tuco’s volatile nature, and try to figure a way out of their business partnership. Hank attempts to mend fences between the estranged Marie and Skyler.

episodes.title: Grilled
episodes.description: Walt and Jesse find themselves in close quarters with an unhinged Tuco. Marie and Hank comfort Skyler, who is distraught over Walt’s disappearance. Hank pays a visit to Mrs. Pinkman on some not-so-official business.

episodes.title: Bit by a Dead Bee
episodes.description: Walt and Jesse become short on cash when they try to cover their tracks. Meanwhile, the DEA has a lead that could them straight to Walt and Jesse.

episodes.title: Down
episodes.description: Walt attempts to reconnect with his family, while Jesse struggles to rebuild his life.

episodes.title: Breakage
episodes.description: Hank suffers from the aftermath of his encounter with Tuco. Meanwhile, Jesse hires a crew to get their product out on the streets.

episodes.title: Peekaboo
episodes.description: Walt's secret is in jeopardy when Skyler thanks Gretchen for paying for his treatment.

episodes.title: Negro y Azul
episodes.description: Jesse and Walt discuss expanding into new territories; Hank struggles to fit in; Skyler pursues a new job opportunity; Jesse gets to know his landlord.

episodes.title: Better Call Saul
episodes.description: Walt and Jesse seek advice from a shady attorney when Badger gets in trouble with the law; the DEA believes they have caught up with "Heisenberg" ; Hank returns.

episodes.title: 4 Days Out
episodes.description: Walt and his family wait for news after he undergoes a PET-CT scan. Walt follows Saul's advice; Jesse's relationship with Jane is put on hold when he and Walt head to the desert for a marathon of cooking.

episodes.title: Over
episodes.description: Walt and Hank get into a heated argument at a party. Skyler opens up to her boss. Jane hides her relationship with Jesse from her father.

episodes.title: Mandala
episodes.description: As the end of her pregnancy finds Skyler conflicted about her feelings, a dealer's death forces Walt to look for somewhere to unload a load of meth.

episodes.title: Phoenix
episodes.description: As Walt explores money laundering options, he and Jesse spar over the profits from their latest deal. Jesse and Jane clash with her father. Walt makes a fatal decision.

episodes.title: ABQ
episodes.description: Skyler confronts Walt about his secrecy; Jesse falls apart; and Jane's grief-stricken father takes action that results in further tragedy.

episodes.title: No Más
episodes.description: Walt faces a new threat, on a new front and deals with an increasingly angry Skyler, who must consider what to do next with her life and the kids. Meanwhile, Jesse comes face-to-face with some startling self-revelations.

episodes.title: Caballo sin Nombre
episodes.description: Despite ever-increasing tension between Walt and Skyler, he pulls out all the stops in an effort to reconcile with the family. Elsewhere, Saul is instrumental in getting Jesse involved in a most-unusual investment opportunity.

episodes.title: I.F.T.
episodes.description: Walt ignores Skyler's demands, furthering the rift between them and pushing her to break bad. Still suffering from panic and anxiety attacks, Hank crosses a line at work.

episodes.title: Green Light
episodes.description: Walt loses control as he reacts to Skyler's news, endangering his job and relationships with Saul and Jesse. Hank throws himself into his blue meth investigation. Jesse enacts a new plan.

episodes.title: Más
episodes.description: Gus increases his efforts to lure Walt back into business, forcing a rift between Walt and Jesse. Skyler doubts her new relationship. Marie confides in Skyler about her concern for Hank's well-being.

episodes.title: Sunset
episodes.description: Walt settles into his new surroundings; Walt, Jr. wants answers about his parents' relationship; Hank's investigation causes problems for Walt and Jesse.

episodes.title: One Minute
episodes.description: Hank's increasing volatility forces a confrontation with Jesse and trouble at work. Skyler pressures Walt to make a deal. Gus' actions have severe consequences.

episodes.title: I See You
episodes.description: The family waits for news about Hank. While Jesse covers at the lab, Walt attempts to placate Gus. After witnessing a disturbing outburst, Walt worries he and his family are in danger.

episodes.title: Kafkaesque
episodes.description: As Hank's hospital bills stack up, Skyler hatches a plan. Walt and Gus come to a better understanding. Jesse, looking for more independence, pursues a new opportunity.

episodes.title: Fly
episodes.description: Walt becomes obsessed with a contaminant in the lab and refuses to finish the cook until it is eliminated. A frustrated Jesse attempts to get Walt back on track.

episodes.title: Abiquiu
episodes.description: Skyler gets involved with Walt's business. Hank struggles with his recovery. Jesse makes a startling discovery after meeting a girl at group therapy.

episodes.title: Half Measures
episodes.description: Against Walt's advice, Jesse lashes out. Fearing for Jesse's safety, Walt takes drastic action to intervene and tragic event leads to a shocking confrontation.

episodes.title: Full Measure
episodes.description: With Jesse on the run and Mike in hot pursuit, Walt negotiates a bargain with Gus and concocts a disturbing plan to provide for his and Jesse's safety.

episodes.title: Box Cutter
episodes.description: Walt and Jesse face the deadly consequences of their actions. Skyler deals with a puzzling disappearance, as Marie struggles to help Hank with his recovery.

episodes.title: Thirty-Eight Snub
episodes.description: Walt attempts to form a new alliance as he plans his next move. Skyler pushes Walt towards a business opportunity, in hopes of protecting the family.

episodes.title: Open House
episodes.description: Events spiral out of control at Jesse's place. Skyler reluctantly asks for Saul's help. Marie returns to an old pastime and a friend asks Hank for help.

episodes.title: Bullet Points
episodes.description: The Cartel takes steps to gain the upper hand. Walt and Skyler share an embarrassing secret with the rest of the family. Jesse's activities draw unwanted attention.

episodes.title: Shotgun
episodes.description: When Jesse goes missing, Walt fears the worst. Skyler has an unlikely reunion. Hank shares some bad news with Detective Tim Roberts.

episodes.title: Cornered
episodes.description: Skyler makes an unsettling discovery. Walter, Jr. pushes his dad into a questionable purchase. Jesse offers Mike some unexpected help.

episodes.title: Problem Dog
episodes.description: A frustrated Walt gambles on a risky new plan. Skyler's business venture hits a snag. Hank recruits Walter, Jr. for an unusual outing.

episodes.title: Hermanos
episodes.description: Skyler develops an unusual solution to her money troubles. Hank enlists Walt to investigate a theory. Walt's impatience with Jesse grows.

episodes.title: Bug
episodes.description: Skyler's past mistakes come back to haunt her. Gus takes action to thwart his rivals. Jesse seeks Walt's help, with mixed results.

episodes.title: Salud
episodes.description: Walt's family worries when he doesn't turn up for Walter, Jr.'s 16th birthday. Jesse is forced to put his lab skills to the test without Mr. White's help.

episodes.title: Crawl Space
episodes.description: Walt takes drastic action to protect his secret and Gus. Skyler's efforts to solve Ted's financial problems hit a wall.

episodes.title: End Times
episodes.description: Hank pushes Gomez to pursue one last lead, while Walt struggles to protect the family. Jesse gets alarming news and rushes to meet with Mr. White.

episodes.title: Face Off
episodes.description: Walt and Jesse team up to take on Gus. With Saul's help, Walt finds an unexpected ally.

episodes.title: Live Free or Die
episodes.description: As Walt deals with the aftermath of the Casa Tranquila explosion, Hank works to wrap up his investigation of Gus' empire.

episodes.title: Madrigal
episodes.description: Walt and Jesse pursue an unlikely business partner. The DEA filters through various leads in hopes of finding something.

episodes.title: Hazard Pay
episodes.description: Walt and Jesse formulate a new business plan. Walt shares a secret with Marie.

episodes.title: Fifty-One
episodes.description: Walt celebrates another birthday. Skyler contemplates her options, and an associate puts a crimp in Walt and Jesse's business strategy.

episodes.title: Dead Freight
episodes.description: Walt's team gets creative to obtain the methylamine they need to continue their operation.

episodes.title: Buyout
episodes.description: Walt, Jesse, and Mike struggle over the future of their business, as occupational hazards weigh on Jesse.

episodes.title: Say My Name
episodes.description: Walt takes control of business matters; Mike deals with the consequences of his actions.

episodes.title: Gliding Over All
episodes.description: Walt takes care of loose ends; Walt makes a dangerous decision.

episodes.title: Blood Money
episodes.description: As Walt and Jesse adjust to life out of the business, Hank grapples with a troubling lead.

episodes.title: Buried
episodes.description: While Skyler's past catches up with her, Walt covers his tracks. Jesse continues to struggle with his guilt.

episodes.title: Confessions
episodes.description: Jesse decides to make a change, while Walt and Skyler try to deal with an unexpected demand.

episodes.title: Rabid Dog
episodes.description: An unusual strategy starts to bear fruit, while plans are set in motion that could change everything.

episodes.title: To'hajiilee
episodes.description: Things heat up for Walt in unexpected ways.

episodes.title: Ozymandias
episodes.description: Everyone copes with radically changed circumstances.

episodes.title: Granite State
episodes.description: Events set in motion long ago move toward a conclusion.

episodes.title: Felina
episodes.description: All bad things must come to an end.

episodes.title: Chapter One: The Vanishing of Will Byers
episodes.description: On his way home from a friend's house, young Will sees something terrifying. Nearby, a sinister secret lurks in the depths of a government lab.

episodes.title: Chapter Two: The Weirdo on Maple Street
episodes.description: Lucas, Mike and Dustin try to talk to the girl they found in the woods. Hopper questions an anxious Joyce about an unsettling phone call.

episodes.title: Chapter Three: Holly, Jolly
episodes.description: An increasingly concerned Nancy looks for Barb and finds out what Jonathan's been up to. Joyce is convinced Will is trying to talk to her.

episodes.title: Chapter Four: The Body
episodes.description: Refusing to believe Will is dead, Joyce tries to connect with her son. The boys give Eleven a makeover. Nancy and Jonathan form an unlikely alliance.

episodes.title: Chapter Five: The Flea and the Acrobat
episodes.description: Hopper breaks into the lab while Nancy and Jonathan confront the force that took Will. The boys ask Mr. Clarke how to travel to another dimension.

episodes.title: Chapter Six: The Monster
episodes.description: A frantic Jonathan looks for Nancy in the darkness, but Steve's looking for her, too. Hopper and Joyce uncover the truth about the lab's experiments.

episodes.title: Chapter Seven: The Bathtub
episodes.description: Eleven struggles to reach Will, while Lucas warns that "the bad men are coming." Nancy and Jonathan show the police what Jonathan caught on camera.

episodes.title: Chapter Eight: The Upside Down
episodes.description: Dr. Brenner holds Hopper and Joyce for questioning while the boys wait with Eleven in the gym. Back at Will's, Nancy and Jonathan prepare for battle.

episodes.title: Chapter One: MADMAX
episodes.description: As the town preps for Halloween, a high-scoring rival shakes things up at the arcade, and a skeptical Hopper inspects a field of rotting pumpkins.

episodes.title: Chapter Two: Trick or Treat, Freak
episodes.description: After Will sees something terrible on trick-or-treat night, Mike wonders whether Eleven's still out there. Nancy wrestles with the truth about Barb.

episodes.title: Chapter Three: The Pollywog
episodes.description: Dustin adopts a strange new pet, and Eleven grows increasingly impatient. A well-meaning Bob urges Will to stand up to his fears.

episodes.title: Chapter Four: Will the Wise
episodes.description: An ailing Will opens up to Joyce -- with disturbing results. While Hopper digs for the truth, Eleven unearths a surprising discovery.

episodes.title: Chapter Five: Dig Dug
episodes.description: Nancy and Jonathan swap conspiracy theories with a new ally as Eleven searches for someone from her past. “Bob the Brain” tackles a difficult problem.

episodes.title: Chapter Six: The Spy
episodes.description: Will's connection to a shadowy evil grows stronger, but no one's quite sure how to stop it. Elsewhere, Dustin and Steve forge an unlikely bond.

episodes.title: Chapter Seven: The Lost Sister
episodes.description: Psychic visions draw Eleven to a band of violent outcasts and an angry girl with a shadowy past.

episodes.title: Chapter Eight: The Mind Flayer
episodes.description: An unlikely hero steps forward when a deadly development puts the Hawkins Lab on lockdown, trapping Will and several others inside.

episodes.title: Chapter Nine: The Gate
episodes.description: Eleven makes plans to finish what she started while the survivors turn up the heat on the monstrous force that's holding Will hostage.

episodes.title: Chapter One: Suzie, Do You Copy?
episodes.description: Summer brings new jobs and budding romance. But the mood shifts when Dustin's radio picks up a Russian broadcast, and Will senses something is wrong.

episodes.title: Chapter Two: The Mall Rats
episodes.description: Nancy and Jonathan follow a lead, Steve and Robin sign on to a secret mission, and Max and Eleven go shopping. A rattled Billy has troubling visions.

episodes.title: Chapter Three: The Case of the Missing Lifeguard
episodes.description: With El and Max looking for Billy, Will declares a day without girls. Steve and Dustin go on a stakeout, and Joyce and Hopper return to Hawkins Lab.

episodes.title: Chapter Four: The Sauna Test
episodes.description: A code red brings the gang back together to face a frighteningly familiar evil. Karen urges Nancy to keep digging, and Robin finds a useful map.

episodes.title: Chapter Five: The Flayed
episodes.description: Strange surprises lurk inside an old farmhouse and deep beneath the Starcourt Mall. Meanwhile, the Mind Flayer is gathering strength.

episodes.title: Chapter Six: E Pluribus Unum
episodes.description: Dr. Alexei reveals what the Russians have been building, and Eleven sees where Billy has been. Dustin and Erica stage a daring rescue.

episodes.title: Chapter Seven: The Bite
episodes.description: With time running out -- and an assassin close behind -- Hopper's crew races back to Hawkins, where El and the kids are preparing for war.

episodes.title: Chapter Eight: The Battle of Starcourt
episodes.description: Terror reigns in the food court when the Mind Flayer comes to collect. But down below, in the dark, the future of the world is at stake.

episodes.title: Chapter One: The Hellfire Club
episodes.description: El is bullied at school. Joyce opens a mysterious package. A scrappy player shakes up D&D night.

episodes.title: Chapter Two: Vecna's Curse
episodes.description: A plane brings Mike to California — and a dead body brings Hawkins to a halt. Nancy goes looking for leads. A shaken Eddie tells the gang what he saw.

episodes.title: Chapter Three: The Monster and the Superhero
episodes.description: Murray and Joyce fly to Alaska, and El faces serious consequences. Robin and Nancy dig up dirt on Hawkins' demons. Dr. Owens delivers sobering news.

episodes.title: Chapter Four: Dear Billy
episodes.description: Max is in grave danger... and running out of time. A patient at Pennhurst asylum has visitors. Elsewhere, in Russia, Hopper is hard at work.

episodes.title: Chapter Five: The Nina Project
episodes.description: Owens takes El to Nevada, where she's forced to confront her past, while the Hawkins kids comb a crumbling house for clues. Vecna claims another victim.

episodes.title: Chapter Six: The Dive
episodes.description: Behind the Iron Curtain, a risky rescue mission gets underway. The California crew seeks help from a hacker. Steve takes one for the team.

episodes.title: Chapter Seven: The Massacre at Hawkins Lab
episodes.description: As Hopper braces to battle a monster, Dustin dissects Vecna's motives — and decodes a message from beyond. El finds strength in a distant memory.

episodes.title: Chapter Eight: Papa
episodes.description: Nancy has sobering visions, and El passes an important test. Back in Hawkins, the gang gathers supplies and prepares for battle.

episodes.title: Chapter Nine: The Piggyback
episodes.description: With selfless hearts and a clash of metal, heroes fight from every corner of the battlefield to save Hawkins — and the world itself.

episodes.title: Chapter One: The Crawl
episodes.description: November, 1987. The gang evades the military to scour the Upside Down for Vecna — but fails to notice a threat lurking closer to home.

episodes.title: Chapter Two: The Vanishing of...
episodes.description: After a vicious attack at the Wheeler home, Mike and Nancy confront the cost of secrecy, while El and Hopper embark on a rescue mission.

episodes.title: Chapter Three: The Turnbow Trap
episodes.description: Will gains unique insight into Vecna's next move, giving the crew an opportunity to set a trap. Holly explores her new surroundings.

episodes.title: Chapter Four: Sorcerer
episodes.description: The military tightens its grip on the town. Mike, Lucas and Robin orchestrate a daring escape. El comes face-to-face with the enemy.

movies.title: John Wick
movies.description: Ex-hitman John Wick comes out of retirement to track down the gangsters that took everything from him.
movies.cast: Keanu Reeves, Michael Nyqvist, Alfie Allen, Willem Dafoe, Dean Winters, Adrianne Palicki, Omer Barnea, Toby Leonard Moore, Daniel Bernhardt, Bridget Moynahan

movies.title: The Shawshank Redemption
movies.description: Imprisoned in the 1940s for the double murder of his wife and her lover, upstanding banker Andy Dufresne begins a new life at the Shawshank prison, where he puts his accounting skills to work for an amoral warden. During his long stretch in prison, Dufresne comes to be admired by the other inmates -- including an older prisoner named Red -- for his integrity and unquenchable sense of hope.
movies.cast: Tim Robbins, Morgan Freeman, Bob Gunton, William Sadler, Clancy Brown, Gil Bellows, James Whitmore, Mark Rolston, Jeffrey DeMunn, Larry Brandenburg

movies.title: The Godfather
movies.description: Spanning the years 1945 to 1955, a chronicle of the fictional Italian-American Corleone crime family. When organized crime family patriarch, Vito Corleone barely survives an attempt on his life, his youngest son, Michael steps in to take care of the would-be killers, launching a campaign of bloody revenge.
movies.cast: Marlon Brando, Al Pacino, James Caan, Robert Duvall, Richard S. Castellano, Diane Keaton, Talia Shire, Gianni Russo, Sterling Hayden, John Marley

movies.title: The Dark Knight
movies.description: Batman raises the stakes in his war on crime. With the help of Lt. Jim Gordon and District Attorney Harvey Dent, Batman sets out to dismantle the remaining criminal organizations that plague the streets. The partnership proves to be effective, but they soon find themselves prey to a reign of chaos unleashed by a rising criminal mastermind known to the terrified citizens of Gotham as the Joker.
movies.cast: Christian Bale, Heath Ledger, Aaron Eckhart, Michael Caine, Maggie Gyllenhaal, Gary Oldman, Morgan Freeman, Monique Gabriela Curnen, Ron Dean, Cillian Murphy

movies.title: Pulp Fiction
movies.description: A burger-loving hit man, his philosophical partner, a drug-addled gangster's moll and a washed-up boxer converge in this sprawling, comedic crime caper. Their adventures unfurl in three stories that ingeniously trip back and forth in time.
movies.cast: John Travolta, Samuel L. Jackson, Uma Thurman, Bruce Willis, Ving Rhames, Harvey Keitel, Eric Stoltz, Tim Roth, Amanda Plummer, Maria de Medeiros

movies.title: Forrest Gump
movies.description: A man with a low IQ has accomplished great things in his life and been present during significant historic events—in each case, far exceeding what anyone imagined he could do. But despite all he has achieved, his one true love eludes him.
movies.cast: Tom Hanks, Robin Wright, Gary Sinise, Sally Field, Mykelti Williamson, Michael Conner Humphreys, Hanna Hall, Haley Joel Osment, Siobhan Fallon Hogan, Rebecca Williams

movies.title: Inception
movies.description: Cobb, a skilled thief who commits corporate espionage by infiltrating the subconscious of his targets is offered a chance to regain his old life as payment for a task considered to be impossible: "inception", the implantation of another person's idea into a target's subconscious.
movies.cast: Leonardo DiCaprio, Joseph Gordon-Levitt, Ken Watanabe, Tom Hardy, Elliot Page, Dileep Rao, Cillian Murphy, Tom Berenger, Marion Cotillard, Pete Postlethwaite

movies.title: Fight Club
movies.description: A ticking-time-bomb insomniac and a slippery soap salesman channel primal male aggression into a shocking new form of therapy. Their concept catches on, with underground "fight clubs" forming in every town, until an eccentric gets in the way and ignites an out-of-control spiral toward oblivion.
movies.cast: Edward Norton, Brad Pitt, Helena Bonham Carter, Meat Loaf, Jared Leto, Zach Grenier, Holt McCallany, Eion Bailey, Richmond Arquette, David Andrews

movies.title: The Matrix
movies.description: Set in the 22nd century, The Matrix tells the story of a computer hacker who joins a group of underground insurgents fighting the vast and powerful computers who now rule the earth.
movies.cast: Keanu Reeves, Laurence Fishburne, Carrie-Anne Moss, Hugo Weaving, Gloria Foster, Joe Pantoliano, Marcus Chong, Julian Arahanga, Matt Doran, Belinda McClory

movies.title: GoodFellas
movies.description: The true story of Henry Hill, a half-Irish, half-Sicilian Brooklyn kid who is adopted by neighbourhood gangsters at an early age and climbs the ranks of a Mafia family under the guidance of Jimmy Conway.
movies.cast: Robert De Niro, Ray Liotta, Joe Pesci, Lorraine Bracco, Paul Sorvino, Frank Sivero, Tony Darrow, Mike Starr, Frank Vincent, Chuck Low

movies.title: The Lord of the Rings: The Return of the King
movies.description: As armies mass for a final battle that will decide the fate of the world--and powerful, ancient forces of Light and Dark compete to determine the outcome--one member of the Fellowship of the Ring is revealed as the noble heir to the throne of the Kings of Men. Yet, the sole hope for triumph over evil lies with a brave hobbit, Frodo, who, accompanied by his loyal friend Sam and the hideous, wretched Gollum, ventures deep into the very dark heart of Mordor on his seemingly impossible quest to destroy the Ring of Power.​
movies.cast: Elijah Wood, Ian McKellen, Viggo Mortensen, Sean Astin, Andy Serkis, Dominic Monaghan, Billy Boyd, John Noble, David Wenham, Miranda Otto

movies.title: Star Wars
movies.description: Princess Leia is captured and held hostage by the evil Imperial forces in their effort to take over the galactic Empire. Venturesome Luke Skywalker and dashing captain Han Solo team together with the loveable robot duo R2-D2 and C-3PO to rescue the beautiful princess and restore peace and justice in the Empire.
movies.cast: Mark Hamill, Harrison Ford, Carrie Fisher, Peter Cushing, Alec Guinness, Anthony Daniels, Kenny Baker, Peter Mayhew, David Prowse, James Earl Jones

movies.title: Interstellar
movies.description: The adventures of a group of explorers who make use of a newly discovered wormhole to surpass the limitations on human space travel and conquer the vast distances involved in an interstellar voyage.
movies.cast: Matthew McConaughey, Anne Hathaway, Michael Caine, Jessica Chastain, Casey Affleck, Wes Bentley, Topher Grace, Mackenzie Foy, Ellen Burstyn, John Lithgow

movies.title: The Silence of the Lambs
movies.description: Clarice Starling is a top student at the FBI's training academy.  Jack Crawford wants Clarice to interview Dr. Hannibal Lecter, a brilliant psychiatrist who is also a violent psychopath, serving life behind bars for various acts of murder and cannibalism.  Crawford believes that Lecter may have insight into a case and that Starling, as an attractive young woman, may be just the bait to draw him out.
movies.cast: Jodie Foster, Anthony Hopkins, Scott Glenn, Ted Levine, Anthony Heald, Brooke Smith, Diane Baker, Kasi Lemmons, Frankie Faison, Tracey Walter

movies.title: Saving Private Ryan
movies.description: As U.S. troops storm the beaches of Normandy, three brothers lie dead on the battlefield, with a fourth trapped behind enemy lines. Ranger captain John Miller and seven men are tasked with penetrating German-held territory and bringing the boy home.
movies.cast: Tom Hanks, Tom Sizemore, Edward Burns, Barry Pepper, Adam Goldberg, Vin Diesel, Giovanni Ribisi, Jeremy Davies, Matt Damon, Ted Danson

movies.title: The Green Mile
movies.description: A supernatural tale set on death row in a Southern prison, where gentle giant John Coffey possesses the mysterious power to heal people's ailments. When the cell block's head guard, Paul Edgecomb, recognizes Coffey's miraculous gift, he tries desperately to help stave off the condemned man's execution.
movies.cast: Tom Hanks, David Morse, Bonnie Hunt, Michael Clarke Duncan, James Cromwell, Michael Jeter, Graham Greene, Doug Hutchison, Sam Rockwell, Barry Pepper

movies.title: Se7en
movies.description: Two homicide detectives are on a desperate hunt for a serial killer whose crimes are based on the "seven deadly sins" in this dark and haunting film that takes viewers from the tortured remains of one victim to the next. The seasoned Det. Somerset researches each sin in an effort to get inside the killer's mind, while his novice partner, Mills, scoffs at his efforts to unravel the case.
movies.cast: Morgan Freeman, Brad Pitt, Gwyneth Paltrow, John Cassini, Peter Crombie, Reg E. Cathey, R. Lee Ermey, Daniel Zacapa, Andrew Kevin Walker, George Christy

movies.title: The Prestige
movies.description: A mysterious story of two magicians whose intense rivalry leads them on a life-long battle for supremacy -- full of obsession, deceit and jealousy with dangerous and deadly consequences.
movies.cast: Hugh Jackman, Christian Bale, Michael Caine, Piper Perabo, Rebecca Hall, Scarlett Johansson, Samantha Mahurin, David Bowie, Andy Serkis, Daniel Davis

movies.title: The Departed
movies.description: To take down South Boston's Irish Mafia, the police send in one of their own to infiltrate the underworld, not realizing the syndicate has done likewise. While an undercover cop curries favor with the mob kingpin, a career criminal rises through the police ranks. But both sides soon discover there's a mole among them.
movies.cast: Leonardo DiCaprio, Matt Damon, Jack Nicholson, Mark Wahlberg, Martin Sheen, Ray Winstone, Vera Farmiga, Anthony Anderson, Alec Baldwin, Kevin Corrigan

movies.title: Gladiator
movies.description: After the death of Emperor Marcus Aurelius, his devious son takes power and demotes Maximus, one of Rome's most capable generals who Marcus preferred. Eventually, Maximus is forced to become a gladiator and battle to the death against other men for the amusement of paying audiences.
movies.cast: Russell Crowe, Joaquin Phoenix, Connie Nielsen, Oliver Reed, Richard Harris, Derek Jacobi, Djimon Hounsou, David Schofield, John Shrapnel, Tomas Arana

movies.title: The Lion King
movies.description: Young lion prince Simba, eager to one day become king of the Pride Lands, grows up under the watchful eye of his father Mufasa; all the while his villainous uncle Scar conspires to take the throne for himself. Amid betrayal and tragedy, Simba must confront his past and find his rightful place in the Circle of Life.
